{"id": "49269", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49269", "title": "Zaelas", "text": "Zaelas is a &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt; who used to be a member of the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20the%20Eyeless\"&gt;Cult of the Eyeless&lt;/a&gt;, but has since left them to become one of the Cult Outcasts. He can be found in the Lair of the Cult Outcasts, a closed-off section of &lt;a href=\"The%20Old%20Tunnels\"&gt;The Old Tunnels&lt;/a&gt; that requires &lt;a href=\"Gaal%27s%20Key\"&gt;Gaal's Key&lt;/a&gt; to open the Door to the Inner Chambers.Being an ex-cultist, he is blind and no longer has the benefits of a \"type\" of \"sight\" granted by his former god.\n\"You have no idea what it is like to be blind and hunted!\"\nGameplay.\nGiven the chance he will tell you his story.\n\"I am Zaelas, and I have been assisting Sassar in researching the rod below... Oh, please! Now that we have run from the cult we are truly blinded! ...we cannot retrieve it! The cult will come for us... they'll throw us in the Pit of the Faithless! Please... Speak to Sassar again and tell him you'll help us!\""}
{"id": "35552", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35552", "title": "Zakee Rafeha", "text": "Zakee Rafeha is the barkeep at the &lt;a href=\"The%20Zephir\"&gt;local tavern&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Amkethran\"&gt;Amkethran&lt;/a&gt;, offering the usual services. Zakee has his finger on the pulse of the villagers in Amkethran, and has knowledge of the current climate regarding Balthazar, visitors to the monastery, problems with supplies, crack downs on the Smugglers and rumors. He is a good source of information for the party. Later in your adventure, after facing &lt;a href=\"Abazigal\"&gt;Abazigal&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sendai\"&gt;Sendai&lt;/a&gt;, you will be able to gain information from Zakee on how to get into Balthazar's monastery. \nThe Zephir.\nZakee's most notable item for sale is the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Ioun%20Stone\"&gt;Silver Ioun Stone&lt;/a&gt;."}
