{"id": "34120", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34120", "title": "Zallanora", "text": "Zallanora is a &lt;a href=\"lawful%20evil\"&gt;lawful evil&lt;/a&gt; / &lt;a href=\"lawful%20neutral\"&gt;neutral&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"elven\"&gt;elven&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"conjurer\"&gt;conjurer&lt;/a&gt; and one of the strongest amongst &lt;a href=\"Cowled%20Wizards\"&gt;Cowled Wizards&lt;/a&gt; enforcers. She comes after &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; for the crime of casting &lt;a href=\"spells\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt; unlicensed within Athkatla. Her meddling is the ultimate attempt from the Wizards to control the spellcasting of the Bhaalspawn's party. If defeated, they will turn a blind eye on any future arcane spell cast on the streets.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes revisions to Zallanora. She may be a level 30 Necromancer (could also be a Conjurer, Enchanter or Invoker). A new AI script is assigned, incorporating the \"Smarter Mages\" component, as well as responding to the game difficulty setting. Hardcore and Insane difficulty will see her utilizing Mage &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class abilities&lt;/a&gt; commensurate with her experience. Her memorized spells are changed, with a lean toward the Necromancy school.\nWhen hostilities begin, She will be provided with a series of initial buffs (previously cast) including &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Blades\"&gt;Energy Blades&lt;/a&gt; for an equipped weapon to use between spell casting, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity Abjuration&lt;/a&gt; (or Dispel Shield with the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;SR&lt;/a&gt; mod), &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Cold%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Protection From Cold (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Acid%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Protection From Acid (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magic%20Energy\"&gt;Protection From Magic Energy&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlao a conjured Skeleton Warrior will appear alongside her. \nOne second later a &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Contingency\"&gt;Chain Contingency&lt;/a&gt; will deploy with &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Shield\"&gt;Spell Shield&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Mantle\"&gt;Improved Mantle&lt;/a&gt; (or \"Moment of Prescience\" with the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;SR&lt;/a&gt; mod). \nFrom then on her actions will be predicated based on the AI's threat assessment and vulnerabilities of the party. No doubt a time stop will be cast, and several spells launched during that pause, possibly with Improved Alacrity.\nZallanora has the following ready for instance use:\nShe has several HLA's ready to use, (and will use) depending on the difficulty setting, including: &lt;a href=\"Comet\"&gt;Comet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Breath%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Dragon's Breath (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Blades%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Energy Blades (wizard)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Alacrity\"&gt;Improved Alacrity&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Dark%20Planetar\"&gt;Summon Dark Planetar&lt;/a&gt;. The party will most likely see the Planetar brought forth after five rounds or during the timestop pause. So, beware this powerful mage."}
