{"id": "2780", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2780", "title": "Zeke", "text": "Zeke is a con artist who is found at the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Carnival\"&gt;Carnival&lt;/a&gt; standing between the &lt;a href=\"Carnival%20Shops%23AR4908\"&gt;melee weapons tent&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Carnival%20Shops%23AR4909\"&gt;ranged weapons tent&lt;/a&gt;. He offers an overpriced &lt;a href=\"Stone%20to%20Flesh%20Scroll\"&gt;Stone to Flesh Scroll&lt;/a&gt; that would free the nearby cleric &lt;a href=\"Branwen\"&gt;Branwen&lt;/a&gt;, who was turned to stone by &lt;a href=\"Tranzig\"&gt;Tranzig&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce you've bought the scroll from him he will leave.\nYou can also charm him and use his own scroll from his quick slot, use your own scroll to unpetrify Branwen, or you can &lt;a href=\"pickpocket\"&gt;pickpocket&lt;/a&gt; Zeke for the scroll.\nDialogue.\n\"Come one, come all! Take a look at the stone warrior maiden. How long has she been trapped in this petrified form, no one knows! Be the first to learn, for the mere price of 500 gold. For that small amount of money, I shall give you a magic scroll, and with this scroll you can release the maiden from her stone prison. Think of the gratitude she would feel to her saviors. Perhaps she's a princess from some far-off land, or maybe a powerful sorceress in search of a concubine. You can't afford not to know! Buy the scroll!\""}
{"id": "52133", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52133", "title": "Zelma", "text": "Zelma is pickpocket lurking outside the &lt;a href=\"Elfsong%20Tavern\"&gt;Elfsong Tavern&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sorcerous%20Sundries\"&gt;Sorcerous Sundries&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "49936", "revid": "265897", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49936", "title": "Zhadroth", "text": "Zhadroth is a &lt;a href=\"lich\"&gt;lich&lt;/a&gt; trapped in &lt;a href=\"Kanaglym\"&gt;Kanaglym&lt;/a&gt;, in another plane of existence. If using one of three charges of the &lt;a href=\"Spectacles%20of%20Spectacle\"&gt;Spectacles of Spectacle&lt;/a&gt;, one can pull him into the &lt;a href=\"Prime%20Material%20Plane\"&gt;Prime Material Plane&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf released, one is rewarded with a &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Regeneration\"&gt;Ring of Regeneration&lt;/a&gt;, if killed also the &lt;a href=\"Robe%20of%20Arcane%20Aptitude\"&gt;Robe of Arcane Aptitude&lt;/a&gt;. Keep in mind that the conditions for the two dialogue options that actually start a fight with Zhadroth to appear are very restrictive (the rest of the party members don't matter, as the game checks for 'player1', who's always the bhaalspawn, even if party order is changed):\n-The first dialogue option that starts a fight can only be accessed by non-blackguard clerics and paladins of any alignment.\n-The second option to start a fight can only be accessed by non-clerics/paladins with 24 or more &lt;a href=\"Lore\"&gt;Lore&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis means that blackguard bhaalspawn (as well as any non-cleric/paladin lacking a mean to raise their lore) have no way to pick a fight with the lich, as it will teleport away as soon as the dialogue is over.\nAfter being released an &lt;a href=\"Endless%20Watcher\"&gt;Endless Watcher&lt;/a&gt;, who stood watch for centuries, will appear across the bridge over the chasm. Greatly angered over the freed lich, it will attack. Unless told Zhadroth is destroyed, then it will reward the &lt;a href=\"Astral%20Crossbow\"&gt;Astral Crossbow&lt;/a&gt;.\nA battle with the Watcher ends by Zhadroth trapping it with a spell, and departing with words mentioning being even with his liberators, and if &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; should ever ascend, that they'd look kindly upon the pain soon to be inflicted upon the betrayers of H'Catha.\nZhadroth is vulnerable to the &lt;a href=\"The%20Secret%20Revealed%20%28item%29\"&gt;The Secret Revealed&lt;/a&gt; from Chapter Eight, functionally disabling his spellcasting and protections.\nAchievements.\nZhadroth is a potential candidate for spending all charges of the &lt;a href=\"Spectacles%20of%20Spectacle\"&gt;Spectacles of Spectacle&lt;/a&gt;, thus earning the following:"}
{"id": "34779", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34779", "title": "Zhalimar Cloudwulfe", "text": "Zhalimar Cloudwulfe is one of six servants of &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%20Anchev\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt;, all of whom are located on the fifth floor of the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne%20Headquarters\"&gt;Iron Throne Headquarters&lt;/a&gt; and are under orders from Sarevok to eliminate &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; permanently. He will most likely be encountered during the quest &lt;a href=\"Investigating%20the%20Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Investigating the Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt; and will fight alongside &lt;a href=\"Aasim\"&gt;Aasim&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Alai\"&gt;Alai&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Diyab\"&gt;Diyab&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gardush\"&gt;Gardush&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Naaman\"&gt;Naaman&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"doppelganger\"&gt;doppelganger&lt;/a&gt; (in the guise of &lt;a href=\"Emissary%20Tar\"&gt;Emissary Tar&lt;/a&gt;).\nHe appears to be the \"de facto\" leader of the group and is the only one who will engage the party in brief conversation.\nWhen &lt;a href=\"Charmed\"&gt;Charmed&lt;/a&gt;, Zhalimar Cloudwulfe has nothing to say beyond that which is available in the dialogue options.\nGameplay.\nZhalimar is a formidable fighter with very high strength and a powerful halberd.\nIn combat, if his nearest enemy is a short distance away, he will equip his &lt;a href=\"Composite%20Longbow\"&gt;Composite Longbow&lt;/a&gt; and attack at range. Otherwise he will fight in melee using &lt;a href=\"Suryris%27s%20Blade\"&gt;Suryris's Blade +2&lt;/a&gt;.\nNotes.\nIn the original release of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, Zhalimar's Suryris's Blade +2 was referred to as a Halberd +2. It is the same item, simply with a name change in ."}
