{"id": "37343", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37343", "title": "Ziatar", "text": "Ziatar is a female of blood who belongs to the &lt;a href=\"Cyric\"&gt;Cyric&lt;/a&gt; cult dwelling in the &lt;a href=\"ruined%20Temple%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;ruined Temple of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt; near &lt;a href=\"Boareskyr%20Bridge\"&gt;Boareskyr Bridge&lt;/a&gt;. She is the half-sister of &lt;a href=\"Morentherene\"&gt;Morentherene&lt;/a&gt;.\nInteractions.\nWhen initially spoken to, Ziatar can be coaxed into revealing that the Cyricists at the temple have come under attack in some fashion, but she will inevitably become hostile.\nCombat.\nZiatar battles with a &lt;a href=\"Two-Handed%20Sword%20%2B1\"&gt;Two-Handed Sword +1&lt;/a&gt; (despite her &lt;a href=\"Classes\"&gt;class&lt;/a&gt; restrictions) and &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt; spellcasting, as well as the ability to exhale her own &lt;a href=\"poison\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt;ous breath weapon. In the beginning, she will cast &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Defensive%20Harmony\"&gt;Defensive Harmony&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Draw Upon Holy Might&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Resist%20Fire%20and%20Cold\"&gt;Resist Fire and Cold&lt;/a&gt; all together on herself, in some kind of contigency. Then she will start attacking either with &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Fear\"&gt;Dragon Fear&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Green%20Dragon%20Breath\"&gt;Green Dragon Breath&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Unholy%20Blight\"&gt;Unholy Blight&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Command\"&gt;Greater Command&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Entangle\"&gt;Entangle&lt;/a&gt;, and other spells, or with melee attacks in her attempt to take the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; down. When she has taken enough &lt;a href=\"damage\"&gt;damage&lt;/a&gt;, she will make skilled use of her &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; and healing spells to keep herself alive.\nUsually all surviving cultists in the temple will also become hostile when she does, but there might be exceptions."}
