{"id": "4760", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4760", "title": "Zone of Sweet Air", "text": "Zone of Sweet Air is a 3rd level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt; only usable by &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt;s. It dispels cloud-based effects in the area (meaning in the entire current map; the caster does not have to stand inside the cloud effect).\n&lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Cernd\"&gt;Cernd&lt;/a&gt; may cast this spell in all games except the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" (since this spell didn't exist yet), despite it normally being restricted from &lt;a href=\"druid\"&gt;druid&lt;/a&gt;s.\nGameplay.\nZone of Sweet Air instantly cancels the following clouds:\n&lt;a href=\"Abi-Dalzim%27s%20Horrid%20Wilting\"&gt;Abi-Dalzim's Horrid Wilting&lt;/a&gt; and the Topaz Dragon Breath from The Black Pits II's can also be cancelled as their projectile travels to its destination, if the Zone of Sweet Air spell is timed right.\nNote.\nA dragon's &lt;a href=\"Wing%20Buffet\"&gt;Wing Buffet&lt;/a&gt; ability incorporates the Zone of Sweet Air into its effects, so use of this ability clears the same clouds as the spell does.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has removed \"Zone of Sweet Air\" from the game and is replaced by two new spells. The first is one is available as a level 2 divine spell available only to Druid/Ranger/Shaman classes. The second is a level 3 divine spell available only to Cleric/Paladin classes. They are similar, but not exactly the same. See below:\nGust of Wind (Druid/Ranger/Shaman version)\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Evocation\nSphere: Elemental (Air)\nRange: Personal\nDuration: Instant\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nThis spell creates a severe blast of air that originates from the caster, affecting all enemies in its path. Those within 6 feet must save vs. breath or be blown back by the force of the gust and knocked unconscious for 1 round. In addition, this spell will disperse all clouds (including magically created vapors such as Cloudkill) in the caster\u2019s current area.\nGust of Wind (Cleric/Paladin version):\nLevel: 3\nSchool: Abjuration\nSphere: Wards, Elemental (Air)\nRange: Personal\nDuration: Instant\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nThis spell creates a severe blast of air that originates from the caster, affecting all enemies in its path. Those within 6 feet must save vs. breath at -2 or be blown back by the force of the gust and knocked unconscious for 1 round. In addition, this spell will disperse all clouds (including magically created vapors such as Cloudkill) in the caster\u2019s current area."}
{"id": "7491", "revid": "1855630", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7491", "title": "Zordral", "text": "Zordral is a witch hating mage who is found in a &lt;a href=\"Bentha%27s%20Tent\"&gt;tent&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Carnival\"&gt;Carnival&lt;/a&gt; where he's preparing to execute the mage &lt;a href=\"Bentha\"&gt;Bentha&lt;/a&gt;.\nZordral's Witchhunt.\nInside the tent you will find Zordral and his soon to be victim Bentha. Choosing dialog options #1 and #1 will taunt him into attacking your party first. Zordral fights primarily with magic, and knows many spells. Generally he will start the fight by casting Mirror Image, followed by Horror and multiple Melf's Acid Arrows.\nOnce Zordral is dead, talk to Bentha. You can ask for a trinket or say that good deed is reward enough. This yields you an &lt;a href=\"Antidote\"&gt;Antidote&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Heroism\"&gt;Potion of Heroism&lt;/a&gt; respectively.\nIf you fail to save Bentha, you can loot both potions from her body, as well as a &lt;a href=\"Mage%20Robe%20of%20Electrical%20Resistance\"&gt;Mage Robe of Electrical Resistance&lt;/a&gt; and other minor loot.\nGameplay.\nMage Book.\nZordral has a number of &lt;a href=\"Wizard%20spells\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt; memorized and will use most of them.\nHe also has abnormally low Save vs. Spell so he cannot be easily disabled."}
