{"id": "29977", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29977", "title": "Zorl (Shadows of Amn)", "text": "Zorl is a &lt;a href=\"lawful%20evil\"&gt;lawful evil&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"male\"&gt;male&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; and one of the two &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s of &lt;a href=\"the%20Hatchetman%27s%20Party\"&gt;the Hatchetman's Party&lt;/a&gt;, a group of thugs that are encountered in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Sewers%20%28Temple%20District%29\"&gt;sewers&lt;/a&gt;. The group is standing in the north, next to the secret door to the corridor that leads to the &lt;a href=\"Illithid%20Hideout%20in%20the%20Sewers\"&gt;illithid hideout&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nPriest Scroll.\nIn addition to the &lt;a href=\"Priest%20spells%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;spells from his Priest Scroll&lt;/a&gt;, Zorl will start combat with a &lt;a href=\"Chant\"&gt;Chant&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Strength%20of%20One\"&gt;Strength of One&lt;/a&gt;, both focused on himself and uninterruptible. If &lt;a href=\"The%20Hatchetman%27s%20Party\"&gt;party members of him&lt;/a&gt; fall below certain percentages of their &lt;a href=\"Hit%20Dice\"&gt;health&lt;/a&gt;, he will use healing spells:\nThe &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;, he has also memorized, won't be used.\nMod content.\nPeople involved.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some revisions to Zorl. He is assigned a default SCS \"Smarter Cleric\" script for more intelligent combat behavior, threat recognition and targeting decision logic. Divine spell casting choices are changed, focusing on buffing himself and allies, and removing debilitating effects. \nAs a 12th level Cleric he is assigned 1 pip in Mace weapon Proficiency and 1 pip in the Sword and shield fighting style. Random SCS treasure is also placed in his inventory. Zorl will attempt to cast healing spells on hurt allies, and self, and seek to cast disabling cleric spells at enemies such as &lt;a href=\"Command\"&gt;Command&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Silence\"&gt;Silence&lt;/a&gt;. He is able to use all spells in his memory, and his focus is healing and buffing his allied group members. He will attempt to disperse any cloud attacks with a &lt;a href=\"Zone%20of%20Sweet%20Air\"&gt;Zone of Sweet Air&lt;/a&gt;. He will summon forth an &lt;a href=\"Aerial%20servant%20%28creature%29\"&gt;Aerial servant (creature)&lt;/a&gt; to assist. Zorl will not engage in melee unless approached and forced to. He will apply buffs and enhancements on his allies, such &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Defensive%20Harmony\"&gt;Defensive Harmony&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Strength%20of%20One\"&gt;Strength of One&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bless\"&gt;Bless&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chant\"&gt;Chant&lt;/a&gt; and similar. Zorl is a support cleric, in much the same manner as the player may have one in their party."}
