{"id": "32448", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32448", "title": "Circlets", "text": ""}
{"id": "5975", "revid": "283670", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5975", "title": "Circus Tent", "text": "The Circus Tent is a tent structure that is located in the &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; district of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;. Two side quests take place inside the tent:\nUnder the Illusion Spell.\nWhen the party enters the tent they will discover an area that is affected by a very powerful illusion spell. Further exploration of this area will reveal that it contains four large areas that vastly surpass the volume of the real tent as seen from its exterior.\nIllusion Exterior Area.\nThis is the area the party enters into first. It contains a large, blue-hued, ornately patterned, domed tent-looking structure that's surrounded by water, with a wide bridge leading to its horseshoe-arched entrance. When walking over the bridge, a &lt;a href=\"Genie%20%28Circus%20Tent%29\"&gt;Genie&lt;/a&gt; will greet the party. He will allow passage over the bridge if given the correct answer to his first or second riddle, or the party will have to kill him. Answering the first riddle gives the most experience points while killing the genie gives the least.\nIf the party chooses to explore the wide, exterior walkway that circles the outside of the domed structure, they will encounter several &lt;a href=\"Shadow\"&gt;Shadow&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Werewolf\"&gt;Werewolf&lt;/a&gt; creatures. The werewolves are illusions while the shadows are real undead that will deal real damage and can &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;drain strength&lt;/a&gt; with a successful hit. Killing each shadow gives the party .\nAs for the illusionary werewolves, as long as the party does not attack or cause damage to them by a hostile action, the werewolves cannot do any damage when they strike. However, if they receive any damage, their illusionary attacks change to real attacks and then they can hurt the party. Killing the werewolves gives no XP.\nFirst floor.\nUpon entering this large circular area, the party is first greeted by the winged elf &lt;a href=\"Aerie\"&gt;Aerie&lt;/a&gt; who has been transformed by an illusion spell into an &lt;a href=\"Ogre\"&gt;Ogre&lt;/a&gt;. She will ask to be freed from the illusion with the help of a &lt;a href=\"The%20Ogre%27s%20Sword\"&gt;key&lt;/a&gt; which can be obtained from some &lt;a href=\"Peasant%20%28Circus%20Tent%29\"&gt;Peasants&lt;/a&gt; who are located nearby.\nA woman named &lt;a href=\"Hannah\"&gt;Hannah&lt;/a&gt; is also in this area, appearing as a &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Spider\"&gt;Giant Spider&lt;/a&gt;, again by the illusions of this odd place. As part of the \"Find the boy's mother inside the circus tent\" side quest, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; can inform her that her &lt;a href=\"Giran\"&gt;son&lt;/a&gt; is safe and is waiting for her outside the tent.\nAfter dealing with Aerie one way or another, the party will encounter the &lt;a href=\"Pleasure%20Slave\"&gt;Pleasure Slave&lt;/a&gt; who is standing in front of another large horseshoe-arched doorway, and who has some bizarre announcements and warnings to offer up to the party during conversation. Afterwards, the party can proceed to the next area through the doorway.\nSecond floor.\nThis area is another large circular room that contains more illusionary werewolves and real shadows and the party will be instantly attacked by the creatures upon entry. After killing all the monsters, the genie from the bridge will re-appear on the stairs to congratulate the party on their progress and question them on their willingness to proceed with the \"little game\". Regardless of the party's answer, he'll eventually leave via a dimension door and the party is free to proceed up the stairs to the next doorway.\nThird floor.\nThis last doorway leads to yet another circular room in which the gnome illusionist &lt;a href=\"Kalah\"&gt;Kalah&lt;/a&gt;, in the guise of an &lt;a href=\"Ogre%20Mage\"&gt;Ogre Mage&lt;/a&gt;, awaits the party. The gnome &lt;a href=\"Quayle\"&gt;Quayle&lt;/a&gt;, a former companion from &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, is also here, having been transformed into a &lt;a href=\"Mustard%20Jelly\"&gt;Mustard Jelly&lt;/a&gt;. Kalah will taunt the party while two shadows and another werewolf attack. Only Kalah needs to be killed to break his illusion spell.\nAfter the Spell is Broken.\nWith Kalah's illusion broken, the inside of the circus tent reverts back to its normal appearance. A dying Kalah, having changed back to his regular gnome appearance, is found lying on the floor of the tent. After some brief banter he'll die for good.\nKalah's Loot.\nKalah's body will lie on the ground for some time, allowing the party the chance to search it for the following items:\nCharacters.\nAerie will be here if she didn't join the group during the investigation quest. Hannah will also appear here as her normal self and upon being spoken to, she'll thank the party for helping her before leaving the tent to rejoin her son. Quayle is also here looking like his normal self.\nMod content.\nMods.\nInstalling the &lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Unfinished Business (Baldur's Gate II)&lt;/a&gt; Mod and the component called &lt;a href=\"Kalah%20%26amp%3B%20What%20He%20Was%20Promised\"&gt;Kalah &amp; What He Was Promised&lt;/a&gt; is a new quest that follows up on the Circus Tent quest. How did Kalah get such amazing Illusionary Powers? Why did he create a realm inside the Circus Tent? The mod sends the party to find out, leading to a potentially challenging and satisfying conclusion."}
{"id": "48215", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48215", "title": "Citizen", "text": "Four Citizen representatives of the local peasantry demand to have an audience with &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; in the Ward's capacity as , if the requirements for gaining the &lt;a href=\"De%27Arnise%20Keep\"&gt;keep&lt;/a&gt; as a &lt;a href=\"stronghold\"&gt;stronghold&lt;/a&gt; have been met.\nRecent flooding has resulted in death and widespread destruction throughout the land and the locals want the current ruler of the keep helping to pay for the cost of rebuilding their farms and repairing the dikes.\nProviding meager help or failure to provide any help at all will leave the locals in a increasing sate of unrest, and increase the risk of revolt."}
