{"id": "51219", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51219", "title": "Claire", "text": "Claire is a courtesan in the employ of &lt;a href=\"Galvena\"&gt;Galvena&lt;/a&gt;. She is also a lover of &lt;a href=\"Sanik\"&gt;Sanik&lt;/a&gt;, a sea faring merchant encountered in the &lt;a href=\"The%20Vulgar%20Monkey\"&gt;Brynnlaw's Inn&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nClaire is currently being held against her will in the Brothel prison. She is grave danger there. To free her, the party needs to access the Brothel, and then venture within to find Claire, and effect a rescue, if possible. Claire is reported to have information that may assist the party in finding a method to access Spellhold to rescue Imoen. \nThis is covered in more detail on the &lt;a href=\"Getting%20inside%20the%20asylum\"&gt;Getting inside the asylum&lt;/a&gt; page."}
{"id": "4880", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4880", "title": "Clairvoyance", "text": "The\u00a0Clairvoyance\u00a0spell reveals the geography of the whole area map.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this spell to themself only.\nWhen the spell casting is complete the caster has a brief series of swirling lighting, color fade and a \"True Sight\" style graphic animation rendered over their sprite.\nThe spell reveals the current map area in which the spell is cast, allowing the player to peruse the entire geographical features on the map, excluding any creatures that may be on it.\nThe spell doesn't technically remove the \"fog of war\", which will remain and can be cleared through normal exploration.\nAlthough normally this spell only works outdoors, if you cast it from a scroll it'll also work indoors or underground.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition \"Clairvoyance\" Wizard spell requires that the locale to be viewed must be known\u2014familiar or obvious. See the External links for further information.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its effects, range and duration. See below for description:\nClairvoyance\nLevel: 3\nSchool: Divination\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 2 turns\nCasting Time: 3\nArea of Effect: Caster\nSaving Throw: None\nThis spell grants an unnatural perception of things to come. Once Clairvoyance is cast, the caster receives instantaneous warnings of impending danger or harm. He becomes impossible to surprise and cannot be backstabbed. In addition, the spell gives a general idea of what action might be taken to best protect oneself, granting a +2 insight bonus to AC and saves vs. breath. The effects last for the duration of the spell and cannot be dispelled."}
