{"id": "49933", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49933", "title": "Cless Ironeye", "text": "Cless Ironeye is a character from in the &lt;a href=\"Rasaad%27s%20Journey\"&gt;Rasaad's Journey&lt;/a&gt; questline.\nGameplay.\nShe is a member of the &lt;a href=\"Vagrant%20Blades\"&gt;Vagrant Blades&lt;/a&gt; located on the &lt;a href=\"Abandoned%20Amphitheater\"&gt;Abandoned Amphitheater&lt;/a&gt; map adjacent to a set of ruins where they have emerged from a recent Dungeon exploration.\nCless is a Shadowdancer with all of that thief kit's abilities. If hostilities develop and given the opportunity, she will use her shadowstep ability to set up backstabbing attacks on vulnerable opponents. She is wearing a magical amulet and belt. Cless has some dialogue with those who interrupt their in-group argument. These dialogue selections will determine the direction of the encounter with the Vagrant Blades.\nCless uses the general thief script in this game and is also scripted to use her two Shadowstep innate abilities. She will try and set up backstabbing attacks on detected enemies in range. This will occur if she can successfully Hide and attack from stealth, using her kit's \"Hide in plain site\" ability. She has an adjusted &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt; x3 damage modifier.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a new script for Cless. It combines backstabbing attempts and potion usage. She will use an &lt;a href=\"Oil%20of%20Speed\"&gt;Oil of Speed&lt;/a&gt; to become hasted, and also use her shadowstep and hide in plain site ability. If wounded to a certain threshold she will quaff a healing potion (twice).\nSCS changed her weapon proficiencies to 2 pips in scimitar, and 3 pips in two-weapon style. Cless will have an improved THAC0 now, but it will still be fairly mediocre."}
{"id": "2125", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2125", "title": "Clinic", "text": "The Clinic can be found in the southeast corner of &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt;, between the main gate and the &lt;a href=\"Storage%20Cellars\"&gt;Storage Cellars&lt;/a&gt;.\nInvolvement.\nPrologue.\nIn the &lt;a href=\"Prologue\"&gt;Prologue&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Priest%20of%20Oghma%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;Priest of Oghma&lt;/a&gt; offers healing once in the form of a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Healing&lt;/a&gt;, while a second potion can be acquired from him.\nChapter Six.\nAfter returning to Candlekeep in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Six\"&gt;Chapter Six&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fuller\"&gt;Fuller&lt;/a&gt; holds guard here.\nLoot.\nA desk next to a bed contains a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Healing&lt;/a&gt;."}
