{"id": "5126", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5126", "title": "Cloak of Fear", "text": "Cloak of Fear is a 4th level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt; that creates a momentary aura of fear around the caster.\nGameplay.\nEnemy creatures in the AoE are exposed to the &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; status effect.\nCompared to the 2nd level wizard spell &lt;a href=\"Horror\"&gt;Horror&lt;/a&gt;, Cloak of Fear has shorter range (none vs 40 ft.), smaller area of effect (15 ft. vs 30 ft. radius), slower casting (6 vs 2), and shorter duration of effect (4 vs 10 rounds). The only advantage is that it can bypass &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe&lt;/a&gt; as it's a higher-level spell.\nThe spell is flagged as a \"Hostile\" spell but its fear radiating power doesn't illicit a reaction from neutral creatures.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this divine spell, revising its spell school, casting time, area of effect, spell effects and duration. See below for description:\nCloak of Fear\nLevel: 4\nSchool: Conjuration\nSphere: Charm\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: 6\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: Special\nCloak of Fear empowers the caster to radiate a personal aura of fear out to a 6\u2019 radius. All enemies not immune to fear within this aura suffer -2 penalty to attack rolls, and each round they must roll a successful saving throw vs. spell or run away in panic for 1 round. Party members are immune to the effects of the aura."}
{"id": "13953", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13953", "title": "Cloak of Minor Arcana", "text": "Cloak of Minor Arcana is an item dropped by &lt;a href=\"Porios\"&gt;Porios&lt;/a&gt; inside of the &lt;a href=\"Korlasz%20Family%20Tomb\"&gt;Korlasz Family Tomb&lt;/a&gt;, after he is either killed or convinced to turn himself in to the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt;. It appears in \"\".\nThis item adds +1 to the Caster level of &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer\"&gt;Sorcerer&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Bard\"&gt;Bard&lt;/a&gt;s wearing it. Additionally, the cloak adds + 10 to the wearer's &lt;a href=\"Lore\"&gt;Lore&lt;/a&gt;. It comes with 10 charges for the generation of scrolls.\nUsing a charge has a 34% chance of generating one of &lt;a href=\"Alveus%27s%20notes\"&gt;Alveus's notes&lt;/a&gt;; otherwise, it will generate a scroll of one of the following spells: &lt;a href=\"Blindness\"&gt;Blindness&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Identify%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Identify&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Blur\"&gt;Blur&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Glitterdust\"&gt;Glitterdust&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Knock\"&gt;Knock&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Clairvoyance\"&gt;Clairvoyance&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dire%20Charm\"&gt;Dire Charm&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Monster%20Summoning%20I\"&gt;Monster Summoning I&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Slow\"&gt;Slow&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "14901", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14901", "title": "Cloak of Mirroring", "text": "The Cloak of Mirroring grants immunity to all spells, abilities and weapon on-hit effects of the &lt;a href=\"Offensive%20damage%20type\"&gt;Offensive damage type&lt;/a&gt;, unless they come from the wearer. This includes area-of-effect spells.\nIn the &lt;a href=\"Enhanced%20Edition\"&gt;Enhanced Edition&lt;/a&gt;, it also grants immunity to extra spells selected explicitly by &lt;a href=\"Beamdog\"&gt;Beamdog&lt;/a&gt; independently from their type. For this curated list displayed in the infobox to the right, immunity works even with the wearer's own spells.\nList of offensive damage attacks.\nSome of those attacks have both a physical and a magical part - in this case only the magical part of the attack is blocked. For example, the Cloak blocks the electrical damage from &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Blade\"&gt;Energy Blade&lt;/a&gt;, but not their slasing damage. It blocks the fire damage from &lt;a href=\"Melf%27s%20Minute%20Meteors\"&gt;Melf's Minute Meteors&lt;/a&gt;, but not their piercing damage.\nAs this list shows, not all damaging spells are included, for example the Cloak will not protect against &lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Breath%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Dragon's Breath (spell)&lt;/a&gt; in current editions.\nMod Content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod and the \"Gameplay Tweaks\" component moves the Cloak of Mirroring to . It is now worn by &lt;a href=\"Vongoethe\"&gt;Vongoethe&lt;/a&gt;, who gains all of the Cloak's passive power. In version 32 of SCS, the Cloak was worn by the Watcher's Keep Demilich instead.\nSCS's \"Smarter Beholders\" component changes how beholders react to the Cloak of Mirroring. The beholders can now use their telekinesis power to steal the Cloak of Mirroring and the Shield of Balduran. They don't do it in the first couple of rounds, then they have a 1/3 chance per round (per beholder). The idea isn't to make the items useless but to block the move of just giving them to one person and sending them in. If it annoys you, you can turn it off at the console: set DMWWDisableBeholderTheft to 1.\nSCS and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod make changes to Dragon Breath weapon attacks and ensure the breath spell school is \"Generalist Mage\" and \"Secondary Type\" is \"None\". This means that the cloak will no longer protect against dragon breath attacks."}
