{"id": "14645", "revid": "3418306", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14645", "title": "Cloakwood", "text": ""}
{"id": "13429", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13429", "title": "Cloakwood Druids", "text": "The Third Cloakwood, also known as Cloakwood Druids, is an area in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". After the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Nest\"&gt;Cloakwood Nest&lt;/a&gt; area, this area feels positively idyllic. Wildlife encounters are few and mostly non-venomous, and rest is mostly uninterrupted. If you're not interested in the companions and/or experience, the zone can be skipped and just head east to get to &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Wyverns\"&gt;Cloakwood Wyverns&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nThe local &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Druid\"&gt;Shadow Druid&lt;/a&gt; faction's dealings with the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt; have made them unusually hostile, even to\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt;'s pacifist &lt;a href=\"Harpers\"&gt;druid faction&lt;/a&gt;, and Shadow Druids will be hostile if she is in the group. If Jaheira is in your party, you may only speak to\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Eldoth\"&gt;Eldoth&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Laskal\"&gt;Laskal&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Faldorn\"&gt;Faldorn&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0without being attacked on sight.\nThe bridge and the remains of ancient roads suggest that this part of the Cloakwood was once less of a wilderness area than now. Patterns in the routes the roads follow even suggest that some of the impenetrable wooded areas, for example at coordinates &lt;a href=\"Coordinates\"&gt;1750, 1300&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Coordinates\"&gt;300, 1550&lt;/a&gt; may conceal foundations of ancient buildings.\nMod content.\nMods:.\nWith the mod (EET) installed, this area is named Cloakwood Grove."}
{"id": "4388", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4388", "title": "Cloakwood Forest", "text": "The Cloakwood Forest, otherwise known as The Cloakwood or simply Cloak Wood, is a relatively small forest due south of the city &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, or directly north-east of the citadel &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt;. During the game \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\", the forest is composed of five areas on the &lt;a href=\"World%20Map\"&gt;World Map&lt;/a&gt; which cannot be explored by &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; prior to &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Four\"&gt;Chapter Four&lt;/a&gt;, and must then be subsequently traversed in order to advance the main story-line. Many side quests may be discovered and completed while making this journey.\nThe first area is entered by heading west from the &lt;a href=\"Friendly%20Arm%20Inn\"&gt;Friendly Arm Inn&lt;/a&gt;, with each subsequent area only reachable from the previous area; there are no shortcuts once the areas are fully explored, and upon reaching the 'heart' of the forest, one must travel back the way they came. Thus, a single one-way trip takes 64 hours, and is seldom completed without being interrupted at least once by a waylaid encounter.\nIndividual areas.\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nCompanions.\nFour potential companions can be found within the Cloakwood:"}
{"id": "13425", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13425", "title": "Cloakwood Lodge", "text": "The First Cloakwood, also known as Cloakwood Lodge, is an area in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". This area is distant enough from the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt; presence deep within the forest that it is protected by the relatively pacifist druid faction led by Archdruid &lt;a href=\"Seniyad\"&gt;Seniyad&lt;/a&gt;, rather than the more intolerant &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Druids\"&gt;Shadow Druids&lt;/a&gt; found further within. It is not, however, without its tensions with the nobles from the city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; who use it as a hunting preserve. These tensions have recently taken a homicidal turn, with one nobleman and one druid winding up dead, and each side blaming the other.\nMod content.\nMods:.\nWith the mod (EET) installed, this area is named simply Cloakwood."}
{"id": "22983", "revid": "3539497", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22983", "title": "Cloakwood Mine", "text": ""}
{"id": "13653", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13653", "title": "Cloakwood Mine level 1", "text": "Cloakwood Mine level 1 is the first of four levels of the ancient mine that lies below the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines\"&gt;Cloakwood Mines&lt;/a&gt; area which is accessible during the events of \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". It's the area of the mine where the iron ore is actively mined and, where'in a river plug is also located that can potentially flood the place if opened.\nThe area is quite similar to the first few levels of the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;Nashkel Mines&lt;/a&gt;, with scattered &lt;a href=\"Miner%20%28Cloakwood%20Mines%29\"&gt;miners&lt;/a&gt; and the occasional &lt;a href=\"Guard%20%28Iron%20Throne%29%23Swordsmen\"&gt;Swordsman guard&lt;/a&gt;, with two significant differences; the miners are enslaved against their will, and the guards are under the employ of the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt; and thus hostile towards &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;.\nThere are seven guards on this level, identical to most others that have been recently encountered in that they are enemies from the get go. However, there are also three &lt;a href=\"Guard%20%28Iron%20Throne%29%23Light%20guards\"&gt;Light guards&lt;/a&gt; with various dialogue options. Of these three, one can be charmed to reveal the location of &lt;a href=\"Davaeorn\"&gt;Davaeorn&lt;/a&gt; (similar to the storehouse guard on the surface), while another may be allowed to flee or will otherwise call for backup.\nThey oversee approximately twenty-three slaves, seven of which are unique, five of them being named - &lt;a href=\"Faber\"&gt;Faber&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Andarsson\"&gt;Andarsson&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Canticle\"&gt;Canticle&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Tipian\"&gt;Tipian&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Phaersis\"&gt;Phaersis&lt;/a&gt; - yet offer little significant information. The rest will likely offer a standard greeting of \"Those aren't Blacktalons\" or \"Help us please. Free us!\" Oddly enough, the two miners who are unique yet aren't named contribute substantially to the primary story-line; one is located in the northeast part of the level next to the river plug, with the second found in the southwest section of the level."}
{"id": "13644", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13644", "title": "Cloakwood Mine level 2", "text": "Cloakwood Mine level 2 is the second of four levels of the ancient mine that lies below the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines\"&gt;Cloakwood Mines&lt;/a&gt; area which is accessible during the events of \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\".\nOn this level of the mine are three guard rooms and a dining room for the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Guard%20%28Iron%20Throne%29\"&gt;Guards&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0a kitchen, storage rooms and prison cells."}
{"id": "13667", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13667", "title": "Cloakwood Mine level 3", "text": "Cloakwood Mine level 3 is where the iron ore is smelted and forged into weapons and armor. There are also bedrooms, barracks, a temple, an armory and other rooms.\nThe party is greeted by four &lt;a href=\"Guard%20%28Iron%20Throne%29%23Swordsmen\"&gt;Swordsman guards&lt;/a&gt;, two &lt;a href=\"Hobgoblin\"&gt;Hobgoblin (fighters)&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Hobgoblin%20Elite\"&gt;Hobgoblin Elite&lt;/a&gt; upon entering the level. Further exploration reveals four &lt;a href=\"Guard%20%28Iron%20Throne%29%23Light%20guards\"&gt;Light guards&lt;/a&gt; scattered throughout the level and random spawning hobgoblins (both fighters and &lt;a href=\"Hobgoblin%20%28archer%29\"&gt;archers&lt;/a&gt;) and hobgoblin elite encountered frequently, usually in groups of 3-5. \nThe light guard in the temple room will ask: \"Are you here to pay homage to our dread lord?\". If the answer is yes, he will ask to choose between 4 evil gods. The answer \"Cyric\" will make him leave, otherwise he turns hostile.\n&lt;a href=\"Slave\"&gt;Slave&lt;/a&gt;s are encountered in the forge room , the circular room, the dining/kitchen room , and the ogre room .\nThe guard room in the lower southeast section of the level contains the entrance point to &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mine%20level%204\"&gt;Level 4&lt;/a&gt; of the mine.\nTreasure.\nBedroom 1.\nContainer 1 -&lt;br&gt;\n - Empty&lt;br&gt;\n - &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Agate%20Gem\"&gt;Fire Agate Gem&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n - &lt;a href=\"Shocking%20Grasp\"&gt;Shocking Grasp&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Sleep\"&gt;Sleep&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nContainer 2 - &lt;a href=\"Acid%20Arrow\"&gt;Acid Arrow&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20of%20Biting\"&gt;Arrow of Biting&lt;/a&gt; , 23 &lt;br&gt;\nContainer 3 - Empty&lt;br&gt;\nContainer 4 - Fire Agate Gem , &lt;a href=\"Jasper%20Gem\"&gt;Jasper Gem&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nBedroom 2.\nContainer 5 - &lt;a href=\"Mace\"&gt;Mace&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dagger\"&gt;Dagger&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nContainer 6 - &lt;a href=\"Waterstar%20Gem\"&gt;Waterstar Gem&lt;/a&gt;, 112 &lt;br&gt;\nContainer 7 - &lt;a href=\"Bloodstone%20Ring\"&gt;Bloodstone Ring&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nContainer 8 - &lt;a href=\"Garnet%20Gem\"&gt;Garnet Gem&lt;/a&gt;, 31 &lt;br&gt;\nBedroom 3.\nContainer 9 - &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Mirrored%20Eyes\"&gt;Potion of Mirrored Eyes&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Strength\"&gt;Potion of Strength&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nContainer 10 - 19 &lt;br&gt;\nContainer 11 - &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nContainer 12 - &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Fire%20Giant%20Strength\"&gt;Potion of Fire Giant Strength&lt;/a&gt;, 119 &lt;br&gt;\nArmory.\nContainer 13 - &lt;a href=\"Large%20Shield\"&gt;Large Shield&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shield\"&gt;Medium Shield&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br&gt;\nContainer 14 - Large Shield , &lt;a href=\"Small%20Shield\"&gt;Small Shield&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nContainer 15 - &lt;br&gt;\n - &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Mail\"&gt;Chain Mail&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n - &lt;a href=\"Splint%20Mail\"&gt;Splint Mail&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nContainer 16 - &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword\"&gt;Bastard Sword&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Long%20Sword\"&gt;Long Sword&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Two-handed%20Sword\"&gt;Two-handed Sword&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nContainer 17 - &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Axe\"&gt;Battle Axe&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Halberd\"&gt;Halberd&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spear\"&gt;Spear&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nContainer 18 - Battle Axe, Halberd , &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Axe\"&gt;Throwing Axe&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br&gt;\nContainer 19 - &lt;br&gt;\n - &lt;a href=\"Studded%20Leather%20Armor\"&gt;Studded Leather Armor&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n - &lt;a href=\"Splint%20Mail\"&gt;Splint Mail&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nContainer 20 - &lt;br&gt;\n - Chain Mail&lt;br&gt;\n - Splint Mail&lt;br&gt;\nContainer 21 - &lt;br&gt;\n - &lt;a href=\"Studded%20Leather%20Armor%20%2B1\"&gt;Studded Leather Armor +1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n - &lt;a href=\"Plate%20Mail\"&gt;Plate Mail&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nOffice.\nContainer 22 - Empty&lt;br&gt;\nContainer 23 - 13 &lt;br&gt;\nBarracks 1.\nContainer 24 - &lt;a href=\"Composite%20Longbow\"&gt;Composite Longbow&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nContainer 25 - Dagger, Long Sword&lt;br&gt;\nContainer 26 - Long Sword, 21 &lt;br&gt;\nContainer 27 - &lt;a href=\"Sunstone%20Gem\"&gt;Sunstone Gem&lt;/a&gt;, 26 &lt;br&gt; \nContainer 28 - &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Acid%20%28protection%20scroll%29\"&gt;Protection From Acid&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Scroll%20of%20Weakness\"&gt;Cursed Scroll of Weakness&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nContainer 29 - &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Magic%20Protection\"&gt;Potion of Magic Protection&lt;/a&gt;, 29 &lt;br&gt;\nBarracks 2.\nContainer 30 - &lt;a href=\"Spear%20%2B1\"&gt;Spear +1&lt;/a&gt;, 354 &lt;br&gt;\nContainer 31 - &lt;a href=\"Flamedance%20Ring\"&gt;Flamedance Ring&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lynx%20Eye%20Gem\"&gt;Lynx Eye Gem&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shandon%20Gem\"&gt;Shandon Gem&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Star%20Diopside%20Gem\"&gt;Star Diopside Gem&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nContainer 32 - Dagger, 23 &lt;br&gt;\nContainer 33 - Halberd&lt;br&gt;\nContainer 34 - Halberd, 15 &lt;br&gt;\nContainer 35 - Dagger, Halberd&lt;br&gt;\nTemple.\nContainer 36 - &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Healing&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Potion of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nContainer 37 - &lt;a href=\"Elixir%20of%20Health\"&gt;Elixir of Health&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Stone%20Giant%20Strength\"&gt;Potion of Stone Giant Strength&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "13672", "revid": "286120", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13672", "title": "Cloakwood Mine level 4", "text": "Level 4 of the Cloakwood Mine, the deepest tier, holds the private quarters of the mine's overseer: the &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Davaeorn\"&gt;Davaeorn&lt;/a&gt;.\nWalkthrough.\n\"Guard\".\nAfter entering the quarters in the northeast from the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mine%20level%203\"&gt;third level&lt;/a&gt;, a short corridor opens to an office room where the party will be \"greeted\" by Davaeorn's personal &lt;a href=\"Guard%20%28Iron%20Throne%29%23Heavy%20guards\"&gt;guard&lt;/a&gt;. Dialogue is short and he will inevitably become hostile. There will be no alarm.\n\"Corridor traps\".\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nBehind a secret door in the the guard's office there is a corridor that leads to the southwest which contains five floor traps:\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"Davaeorn\".\nWhen the end of the corridor is reached, near the final trap, Davaeorn comes into sight \u2014 &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;protected from normal missiles&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;mirror imaged&lt;/a&gt;, he threatens &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and immediately becomes hostile. He will now \u2013 and up to two times later \u2013 use a &lt;a href=\"Dimension%20Door\"&gt;Dimension Door&lt;/a&gt;; for an overview of his offensive &lt;a href=\"Wizard%20spells%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt;, see &lt;a href=\"Davaeorn\"&gt;his own article&lt;/a&gt;. However, there are no further traps or enemies in the vicinity, so letting party members chase him is safe.\nAfter defeating him and looting the important &lt;a href=\"Key%20to%20River%20Plug\"&gt;Key to River Plug&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 along with three letters from &lt;a href=\"Rieltar%20Anchev\"&gt;Rieltar&lt;/a&gt; about someone named &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%20Anchev\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt;, his relations to the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt; and the location of the organizations headquarters in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 the rest of Davaeorn's quarters can be safely sacked for many and other interesting items, including:\nIn one of the two unlocked chests in the now cleared treasury, Gorion's Ward will find a scroll for &lt;a href=\"Knock\"&gt;Knock&lt;/a&gt;ing \u2013 which might come in handy for the chest in Davaeorn's bedroom that is locked at a high difficulty. (See &lt;a href=\"%23Treasure\"&gt;below&lt;/a&gt; for a detailed listing of locks and loot.)\nWhen finally nearing the elevator that leads back up to the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mine%20level%201\"&gt;first level&lt;/a&gt;, the narrator will interrupt to introduce the player to &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Five\"&gt;Chapter Five&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Wyrm%27s%20Crossing\"&gt;Wyrm's Crossing&lt;/a&gt; is revealed on the &lt;a href=\"World%20Map\"&gt;World Map&lt;/a&gt;. The party now might leave the mine \u2013 and close &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Four\"&gt;this chapter&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href=\"Flooding%20the%20Cloakwood%20Mine\"&gt;flooding it&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "5448", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5448", "title": "Cloakwood Mines", "text": "The Cloakwood Mine area, labelled simply as Mine on the &lt;a href=\"World%20Map\"&gt;World Map&lt;/a&gt;, is an area within the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood\"&gt;Cloakwood Forest&lt;/a&gt; during \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". It's an old iron mine which was originally the home of the dwarven Orothair clan, yet most members were killed when they accidentally breached an underground river, subsequently flooding the mine. At present, the mine has been secretly retrofitted and is currently in full operation by the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt;. Their work force is made up of mostly enslaved men, most of which have been taken prisoner during caravan raids, with a few even tasked with making weapons and armor from the iron ore that has been mined or stolen from raids.\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Davaeorn\"&gt;Davaeorn&lt;/a&gt; is the leader of operations at the mine, running things from its deepest depths.\nThe immediate area surrounding the Motte-and-bailey fortification is relatively peaceful, with the occasional wild group of &lt;a href=\"Tasloi\"&gt;Tasloi&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Wolf\"&gt;Wolves&lt;/a&gt; appearing. The party may also meet patrols of Iron Throne &lt;a href=\"Guard%20%28Iron%20Throne%29%23Swordsmen\"&gt;Guards&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Blacktalon%20Elite\"&gt;Blacktalon Elite&lt;/a&gt;. The unique guard\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Lakadaar\"&gt;Lakadaar&lt;/a&gt; is encountered north of the fortification, and will hail &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; upon sight; he may be scared away at the mention of &lt;a href=\"Wyvern\"&gt;Wyvern&lt;/a&gt;s, but will otherwise attack with four comrades backing him up - despite this special circumstance, he's practically identical to any other Iron Throne guard.\nThe fortification is entirely surrounded by a moat and is comprised of two \"islands\" surrounded by water with only one wooden bridge as the only entrance to the area. This bridge is located due south of the entry point to this area. The first island includes a stable with &lt;a href=\"horse\"&gt;horse&lt;/a&gt;s, a &lt;a href=\"Barracks%20%28Cloakwood%20Mines%29\"&gt;barracks&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines%20Storehouse\"&gt;storehouse&lt;/a&gt;, along with an encounter with &lt;a href=\"Drasus\"&gt;Drasus&lt;/a&gt; and his formidable group of hired adventurers. Within each building is a low-tier guard with some helpful information; one immediately flees before pointing the party in the direction of the mine entrance via dialogue, while the second will be hostile, but will point the party in the direction of Davaeorn via dialogue after being charmed. The second island merely contains the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines%20Shed\"&gt;entrance&lt;/a&gt; to the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mine%20level%201\"&gt;mines&lt;/a&gt;, serving as a guard-post type structure when viewed from the outside.\nJournal Entry.\nEntering this area for the first time marks the &lt;a href=\"Important%20Events%23Cloakwood\"&gt;Important Events:&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=\"Important%20Events%23Cloakwood\"&gt;Cloakwood&lt;/a&gt; entry in your Journal as completed, and creates the &lt;a href=\"Important%20Events%23Crippling%20Cloakwood\"&gt;Important Events:&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=\"Important%20Events%23Crippling%20Cloakwood\"&gt;Crippling Cloakwood&lt;/a&gt; journal entry."}
{"id": "46923", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46923", "title": "Cloakwood Mines Shed", "text": "The Cloakwood Mines Shed houses the entrance to the mine. It is located in the second compound of the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines\"&gt;Cloakwood Mines&lt;/a&gt; area. Inside is a set of stairs that lead to the Lift which provides access to the mine. There are two &lt;a href=\"Guard%20%28Iron%20Throne%29%23Swordsmen\"&gt;guards&lt;/a&gt; keeping watch as well.\nThe chest is locked and contains two &lt;a href=\"Long%20Sword\"&gt;Long Sword&lt;/a&gt;s and 58 . The barrel is empty.\nThe Lift.\nAt the bottom of the stairs is a door that leads to the Lift.\n&lt;br&gt;\nActivating the Lift will take the party to the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mine%20level%201\"&gt;first level&lt;/a&gt; of the mine.\n&lt;br&gt;\nLevel 1 entrance point\nThe Lift is also available for exiting the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mine%20level%204\"&gt;fourth level&lt;/a&gt; of the mine. It is located next to &lt;a href=\"Davaeorn\"&gt;Davaeorn&lt;/a&gt;'s bedroom. It will take the party back to the first level of the mine, whereupon it must be accessed again to reach the shed.\n&lt;br&gt;\nLevel 4 exit point"}
{"id": "46916", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46916", "title": "Cloakwood Mines Storehouse", "text": "This is the small, non-descript building located next to the &lt;a href=\"Barracks%20%28Cloakwood%20Mines%29\"&gt;barracks&lt;/a&gt; in the first compound of the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines\"&gt;Cloakwood Mines&lt;/a&gt;. The door is hidden from view and faces towards the path leading to the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines%20Shed\"&gt;shed&lt;/a&gt; which houses the lift for the mine. There's not a sign for it on the map either. And there are no lootable containers in the building. The only occupant is a single &lt;a href=\"Guard%20%28Iron%20Throne%29%23Light%20guards\"&gt;guard&lt;/a&gt; who appears to be slacking off. Upon seeing a &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; member he says:\nAnd then he immediately turns hostile and attacks. He is armed with a &lt;a href=\"Long%20Sword\"&gt;Long Sword&lt;/a&gt; and wears a &lt;a href=\"Leather%20Armor\"&gt;Leather Armor&lt;/a&gt;. If he is &lt;a href=\"charmed\"&gt;charmed&lt;/a&gt;, he has this to say:"}
{"id": "13428", "revid": "286096", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13428", "title": "Cloakwood Nest", "text": "The Cloakwood Nest, also known as Second Cloakwood, is an area in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". Its shape is a reference to Mediterranean Europe, with the east peninsula being Italy's \"boot\" and the west Spain and Portugal.\nGameplay.\nWeb traps abound. Even spiders, which are so weak compared with other enemies of the same &lt;a href=\"XP\"&gt;XP&lt;/a&gt;, can easily kill characters that cannot defend themselves. One way to avoid traps is to retreat slightly from any encounter, forcing the creatures to come to you, rather than you pursuing them into a trap.\nSurvival in this area, particularly in the &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Nest\"&gt;spider nest&lt;/a&gt;, will likely be difficult without a decent supply of\u00a0potions such as &lt;a href=\"Antidote\"&gt;Antidote&lt;/a&gt;s\u00a0or\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Elixir%20of%20Health\"&gt;Elixir of Health&lt;/a&gt;.\nTreasure.\n&lt;a href=\"Spider%27s%20Bane\"&gt;Spider's Bane&lt;/a&gt; is a reward from Tiber's side quest\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Spiders%20in%20the%20Cloakwood\"&gt;Spiders in the Cloakwood&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Rashad%27s%20Talon\"&gt;Rashad's Talon&lt;/a&gt;, cursed ring\u00a0and leather armor, are located on the ground on the lower south-east peninsula. \nMod content.\nMods:.\nWith the mod (EET) installed, this area is named Cloakwood Falls."}
