{"id": "39227", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39227", "title": "Clovista", "text": "Clovista is one of half a dozen would-be adventurers who joined the Coalition against &lt;a href=\"Caelar%20Argent\"&gt;Caelar Argent&lt;/a&gt; and her &lt;a href=\"Shining%20Crusade\"&gt;Shining Crusade&lt;/a&gt; during the events of .\nTraining.\nWhen approached as part of the quest &lt;a href=\"Troop%20Train\"&gt;Troop Train&lt;/a&gt;, if &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; is sufficiently intelligent, they can deduce that Clovista is fighting inefficiently by attempting to mimic the standards of the &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;s around her instead of playing to her strengths. If the party includes &lt;a href=\"Glint%20Gardnersonson\"&gt;Glint Gardnersonson&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"M%27Khiin%20Grubdoubler\"&gt;M'Khiin Grubdoubler&lt;/a&gt;, they will automatically explain in their own distinct ways that she needs to accept that she is not as big or strong as a human, and must play to her size advantages in order to triumph. This is how she counts as successfully trained in order to complete this quest."}
{"id": "2813", "revid": "49746547", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2813", "title": "Club", "text": "Clubs are hard, wooden sticks, which can be used by all classes, except &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"sorcerer\"&gt;sorcerer&lt;/a&gt;s. They are characteristically weapons for druids, which are either armed with clubs or quarterstaves. Clubs require 5 strength and have their own proficiency, except in classic &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, where they fall under blunt weapons. This item appears in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nTry &lt;a href=\"The%20Tweaks%20Anthology\"&gt;The Tweaks Anthology&lt;/a&gt; modification and install the component that allows:\nUniversal Clubs\nBGEE, BG2EE, IWDEE, EET, BG, BG2, IWD, BGT, Tutu, IWD-in-BG2\nFrom the description of a basic club in BG2: 'Anyone can find a good stout piece of wood and swing it'--so why can't mages use clubs? This tweak allows mages to wield clubs as well as gain a proficiency point in clubs. This component will affect all items in the game, including items introduced by mods."}
