{"id": "20365", "revid": "978785", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20365", "title": "Club +3, Blackblood", "text": ""}
{"id": "5388", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5388", "title": "Club of Detonation", "text": "Club of Detonation is an unique Club +3 which was added in but obtainable in as well. It is dropped (but not used) by the &lt;a href=\"Aurumach%20Rilmani\"&gt;Aurumach Rilmani&lt;/a&gt; on\u00a0the fifth floor of &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20%28area%29\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt;. It has a multitude of unique characteristics, including +3 fire damage every time it hits its target, a 20% chance it will deal an additional +10 fire damage, and a 7% chance a &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt; is detonated by the weapon dealing 5d6 damage, or half that with a successful Save vs. Spell. However - unlike a normal enchanted club - it has no bonus to speed factor. The weapon can be upgraded by &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt; which requires a &lt;a href=\"Batalista%27s%20Passport\"&gt;Ring of Fire Resistance&lt;/a&gt; and some gold.\nUpgrade.\nThe upgraded Club of Detonation is a unique Club +5 with further improved unique effects. It now inflicts +5 fire damage every time it hits its target with a 30% chance it will deal an additional +15 fire damage, and has a 5% chance to create a &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt; explosion dealing 10d6 fire damage with a save vs. spell for half. It is also 2 lbs lighter than before, but its speed factor remains on par with a non-magical club."}
