{"id": "25545", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=25545", "title": "Coalition Camp", "text": "The Coalition Camp is an in \"\".\nThe alliance set for the battle with the &lt;a href=\"The%20Crusade\"&gt;crusade&lt;/a&gt;, there are a number of quests starting from here, and when you leave the camp you'll eventually trigger an &lt;a href=\"Canyon%20Ambush\"&gt;encounter&lt;/a&gt; with a mercenary group led by a powerful &lt;a href=\"Shadowy%20Figure\"&gt;Shadowy Figure&lt;/a&gt;. Also be aware that by returning here after triggering &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Ten%20%E2%80%93%20Allied%20Siege%20Camp\"&gt;certain events&lt;/a&gt; (e.g., turning Belben hostile, poisoning the crusader supplies, witnessing the discussion between Hephernann and Belhifet) is a \"point of no return\", you have little choice but to leave what's left undone to proceed into .\nMoving On.\nAfter &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; has confronted &lt;a href=\"Belben\"&gt;Belben&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Basement\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Basement&lt;/a&gt;, their next arrival at the camp will trigger a cutscene where &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; will be confronted by the heads of the Alliance. This will then lead to a sequence of dialogue involving an ultimately failed attempt at a parlay with &lt;a href=\"Caelar%20Argent\"&gt;Caelar Argent&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Dead%20Man%27s%20Pass\"&gt;Dead Man's Pass&lt;/a&gt;, before triggering a combat encounter detailed on the page &lt;a href=\"Siege%20of%20the%20Camp\"&gt;Siege of the Camp&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce this combat encounter is successfully completed, the Alliance will launch a strike against &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle&lt;/a&gt;, transitioning the game to &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Eleven%20%E2%80%93%20Dragonspear%20Castle%20Battle\"&gt;Chapter 11&lt;/a&gt;. Once this happens, the Coalition Camp and all other areas accessible from it will no longer be accessible."}
