{"id": "48363", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48363", "title": "Cohn Ta'glaen", "text": "Cohn Ta'glaen is a male &lt;a href=\"Fledgling%20Vampire\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt; who is found in &lt;a href=\"Bodhi%27s%20Hideout\"&gt;Bodhi's Hideout&lt;/a&gt; within the &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs\"&gt;Lower Tombs&lt;/a&gt;, if you have decided to &lt;a href=\"Perform%20Bodhi%27s%20Tasks%20to%20Receive%20Her%20Aid\"&gt;side with Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt;/Vampire guild war. He is something of a confident of Bodhi's and seems to be the individual who is in charge of delineating the daily tasks to the \"help\". \nAttacking him doesn't appear to upset Bodhi in the least, although if wounded sufficiently he'll escape actual destruction in gas cloud form, presumably to reform again somewhere in the future, although not appearing again in the game.\nDialogue.\n\"Greetings. I trust you have found your welcome adequate, if not exactly warm. I am Master Cohn Ta'glaen. If you choose to address me, call me Master Cohn.\"\nAll further attempts at conversation result in:\n\"I have nothing more to say until the mistress bids it. Feel fortunate, for we do not often even bother acknowledging our disregard for such as you.\""}
{"id": "26935", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26935", "title": "Cohrvale", "text": "Cohrvale and his companion &lt;a href=\"Bregg\"&gt;Bregg&lt;/a&gt; are found northeast of the right entrance to &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;Athkatla Slums&lt;/a&gt;.\nFoul mouthed Cohrvale will initiate a dialogue with &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and can be taunted into a fight for a quick 6000 + 4000 experience. You can also get in a fight if you don't taunt him. It's easy to get into a fight with Cohrvale.\nDialogue.\nCohrvale: Out of my way, you there!\nBregg: Calm down, Cohrvale. Mr. F. don't like ye killin' people in the streets.\nCohrvale: Shut your mouth, dwarf! As for you, I said get your stinkin' hide out of my way!\n&lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;: 3. Keep barking, dog. Just watch that your little keeper doesn't yank on your leash too hard.\nCohrvale: Those foul words will be your last! Ye'll die this day!\nBregg: Now ye've done it, blasted fool! Couldn't ye see he was armed?\nNote: Cohrvale has no weapon proficiency in battle axe or axes assigned. He does have grandmastery in small swords weapon proficiency (but doesn't use one). \nMod content.\nPeople involved.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod changes Cohrvale, and assigns a default SCS tactical AI script for better combat behavior. Additionally, 4 pips in battle axe weapon proficiency and 2 pips in sword and shield style are given to match up with a 7th level fighter's experience. SCS random treasure is also supplied."}
{"id": "31318", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31318", "title": "Cold Fury", "text": "Cold Fury +2 is an enchanted which can be found in \"\".\nAcquisition.\nThis unique halberd can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20vs.%20Giants%20Waylay\"&gt;Dragon vs. Giants Waylay&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0random encounter area, if the &lt;a href=\"Hill%20Giant\"&gt;Hill Giant&lt;/a&gt;s are not attacked by the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; and the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Young%20Green%20Dragon\"&gt;Young Green Dragon&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0is killed. The two\u00a0Hill Giants\u00a0that were attacking the dragon will call in reinforcements,\u00a0one of which is a &lt;a href=\"Hill%20Giant%20Leader\"&gt;Hill Giant Leader&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0who\u00a0drops the Cold Fury when slain.\nGameplay.\nCold Fury does additional cold damage (1d2) to any creature and can slow \"fire-dwelling and fire-using creatures\" for 3 rounds on a failed save vs spell.\nDespite the elaborate in-game description, \"fire-dwelling and fire-using creatures\" are simply those that have 100% or more fire resistance, including creatures whose resistance has been temporarily improved by &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Fire\"&gt;Protection From Fire&lt;/a&gt;, for example."}
