{"id": "24589", "revid": "41451052", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24589", "title": "Cold damage", "text": "Cold damage is one of the 10 main &lt;a href=\"Damage\"&gt;damage types&lt;/a&gt; of the game, typically inflicted by spells or on-hit effects caused by weapons like the &lt;a href=\"Flail%20of%20Ages\"&gt;Flail of Ages&lt;/a&gt;. A weapon would cause &lt;a href=\"Physical%20damage\"&gt;Physical damage&lt;/a&gt; provided it goes through &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt;, and then an additional effect could add elemental damage.\nProtection from cold.\nThrough the use of certain spells, items or abilities, it is possible to reduce the amount of damage, afflicted by cold.\nSpells.\n&lt;a href=\"Spells\"&gt;Spells&lt;/a&gt; usually offer only temporary protection from cold, in varying degrees.\nItems.\n&lt;a href=\"Item\"&gt;Item&lt;/a&gt;s, as long as equipped, offer a constant protection from cold. By wearing more than one of these, 100% resistance or even more is quite possible. Consumable items only give temporary protection.\nAbilities.\nThere are a few that can offer temporary or constant protection from cold.\n\u2026 incomplete!\nDamage from cold.\nMany spells are based on cold, as well as some abilities, and items may deal bonus or even pure cold damage.\nSpells.\nDue to their purpose of healing and supporting, the arsenal of cold-based spells is much smaller for &lt;a href=\"priest\"&gt;priest&lt;/a&gt;s than for &lt;a href=\"wizard\"&gt;wizard&lt;/a&gt;s.\n\u2026 incomplete!\nItems.\nRegular weapons with cold damage, besides ammunition for bows, weren't introduced until \"\".\nAbilities.\n\u2026 incomplete!\nCreatures, protected from cold.\nSome have a natural resistance against cold damage, some have special &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt;s equipped that protect them.\n\u2026 incomplete!\nCreatures, dealing cold damage.\nThere are a number of that always or by will are able to deal cold damage, either naturally, via spells or through special &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt;s in their &lt;a href=\"Inventory\"&gt;equipment&lt;/a&gt;.\n\u2026 incomplete!"}
