{"id": "4868", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4868", "title": "Cone of Cold", "text": "The Cone of Cold spell creates a cone-shaped blast of extreme cold emanating from the wizard's hand.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a designated point on the area map to aim the cone towards using the targeting cursor.\nWhen the spell casting is finished the projectile propagates toward the targeting point, in an arc that spreads and widens as the distance increases from the caster.\nThe spell's projectile is one of the slower moving ones in the game, and this can lead to inaccurate misses when attempting to affect desired targeting of various creatures that are moving on the battle map. \nSometimes the cone envelopes all, none, or some of the intended targets - this spell may take some practice to use effectively. \nAny creature caught in the cone will be exposed to the &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;Cold damage&lt;/a&gt;, although a successful &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spells reduces the damage by half.\nThis spell can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Evocation&lt;/a&gt;, and the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Mirroring\"&gt;Cloak of Mirroring&lt;/a&gt;.\nFor fast moving player characters, it is feasible to outrun the spell's cone and evade getting exposed.\nIn Baldur's Gate 2, the &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Frost\"&gt;Wand of Frost&lt;/a&gt; applies a version of this spell (not in BG1, where the wand behaves differently). \nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeon's and Dragons 2nd Edition Cone of Cold Wizard spell is cast with a cone range that scales upwards with the caster's level. See the External links for further information.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its casting time, effects, saving throw, arc degree effect area and description. See below for description:\nCone of Cold\nLevel: 5\nSchool: Evocation\nRange: Special\nDuration: Instant\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: Breath half\nWhen this spell is cast, it causes a cone-shaped spray of extreme cold to spring forth from the wizard\u2019s hand. The cone is 30 feet in length and spread out in a horizontal arc of 60 degrees in front of the wizard. It drains heat and causes 1d4+1 points of damage per level of experience of the wizard (to a maximum of 15d4+15 at level 15), with a save vs. breath at -4 allowed for half damage."}
{"id": "13084", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13084", "title": "Confronting Tranzig", "text": "Confronting Tranzig is an important quest in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Three\"&gt;Chapter Three&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"\". This quest may first appear in your journal when you read the letters carried by &lt;a href=\"Mulahey\"&gt;Mulahey&lt;/a&gt; (although this event does not always trigger for unknown reasons):\u00a0\nA journal entry may also result from rumors gathered in &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt;:\u00a0\nEven if there you have no journal entry for this quest, you will be led to it by the Important Events: Tranzig journal entry, and it will show up in your journal as a completed quest.\nWhen you meet with &lt;a href=\"Tranzig\"&gt;Tranzig&lt;/a&gt; in his room at &lt;a href=\"Feldepost%27s%20Inn\"&gt;Feldepost's Inn&lt;/a&gt; in Beregost, two outcomes are possible:"}
{"id": "42283", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42283", "title": "Confused", "text": "Description.\nThe character is out of control and can't see the difference between friend and foe. They randomly alternate between standing still, walking randomly, or attacking the nearest person regardless of whether it is friend or foe. If they attack an ally, that ally will retaliate unless you disable AI.\nImmunity.\n&lt;onlyinclude&gt;The following items and spells provide immunity to becoming &lt;a href=\"confused\"&gt;confused&lt;/a&gt;:\n&lt;br&gt;\nNotes.\nOne version of &lt;a href=\"Hexxat%27s%20Amulet\"&gt;Hexxat's Amulet&lt;/a&gt; also provides immunity. This is the version that she is wearing in \"bat form\". The actual item she is wearing at the time is transformedto this extra powerful version to prevent any attack from succeeding, so she gets safely to the coffin.\nUpon being restored from being not-really-dead, the item is transformed back into the original amulet.&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;\nIf the \"confused\" effect was caused by a spell (see \"Causes\"), it can also be blocked by defenses against that specific spell. For example, a &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; would protect against &lt;a href=\"Confusion%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Confusion (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; (level 4 spell) but not against &lt;a href=\"Chaos\"&gt;Chaos&lt;/a&gt; (level 5 spell). &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Enchantment&lt;/a&gt; protects against both, but not against confusion from &lt;a href=\"Sphere%20of%20Chaos\"&gt;Sphere of Chaos&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Umber%20Hulk\"&gt;Umber Hulks&lt;/a&gt;.\nRemoval.\nOngoing confusion can be removed by &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Restoration\"&gt;Greater Restoration&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Exaltation\"&gt;Exaltation&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Shaman\"&gt;Shaman&lt;/a&gt; spell &lt;a href=\"Spiritual%20Clarity\"&gt;Spiritual Clarity&lt;/a&gt;, or the &lt;a href=\"Bard\"&gt;Bard&lt;/a&gt;-exclusive item &lt;a href=\"Tangled%20Strings\"&gt;Tangled Strings&lt;/a&gt;."}
