{"id": "13257", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13257", "title": "Conster", "text": "Conster is a 16th level mage who is a loyal servant of the red dragon &lt;a href=\"Firkraag\"&gt;Firkraag&lt;/a&gt;. He is found with the dragon in the dragon's &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Hideout\"&gt;lair&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt;. He will be fought either solo in the holding cells room in &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Maze\"&gt;Firkraag's Maze&lt;/a&gt;, or in a rushed encounter with Firkraag.\nGameplay.\nFirkraag and his mage Conster face the party side by side the first time &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; visits the dragon's hideout. Conster will not speak before his master does.\nThrough various dialogue choices with Firkraag, the party may eventually make it clear to the dragon that they cannot leave without Garren Windspear's child (who is still upstairs locked in a cell). Firkraag, does not at the moment, wish to kill the party and is willing to let the party live their life. He warns the party though:\nConster speaks a line of dialogue, and teleports back upstairs. He'll be ready for the party when they come back to rescue the child. \nOn the other hand, if the party attacks either Conster or Firkraag himself within the dragon's hideout - then both the mage and dragon will immediately go hostile and attack the party as well. From a game challenge standpoint, this is the most difficult scenario since the party will face two opponents at the same time, instead only the one. If the party set out to destroy Firkraag, then this can be done without regret - in fact it will achieve all the party's goals. That is, unless the PC is a &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; and will be pursuing the &lt;a href=\"Paladin%20Stronghold%20Duties\"&gt;Paladin Stronghold Duties&lt;/a&gt;, and then the optimal time to attack Firkraag may be later.\nConster will apply a battery of instantly cast spells at the start of conflict (uninterruptible). These include &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Minor Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Normal Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity Invocation&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mislead\"&gt;Mislead&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; (from his ring). His next spell application will be &lt;a href=\"Mantle\"&gt;Mantle&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter that the mage will recognize spell caster classes and could try to take out that target with a combined &lt;a href=\"Ruby%20Ray%20of%20Reversal\"&gt;Ruby Ray of Reversal&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Maze\"&gt;Maze&lt;/a&gt; a few game tics later.\nA &lt;a href=\"Finger%20of%20Death%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Finger of Death (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; is scripted for use at the third nearest enemy.\nThe second nearest enemy to Conster will be targeted with a combination &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Malison\"&gt;Greater Malison&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Flesh%20to%20Stone\"&gt;Flesh to Stone&lt;/a&gt;. If summoned creatures are spotted by Conster he'll attempt another combination cast with &lt;a href=\"Delayed%20Blast%20Fireball\"&gt;Delayed Blast Fireball&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;.\nA &lt;a href=\"Finger%20of%20Death%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Finger of Death (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; is scripted for use at the third nearest enemy.\nA &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt; will be attempted for self protection, as well as another &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; if the previous is down to 1 skin.\nAnd further direct attack and disabling spells are potentially possible such as &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Lightning\"&gt;Chain Lightning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;Lightning Bolt&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missile\"&gt;Magic Missile&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Melf%27s%20Acid%20Arrow\"&gt;Melf's Acid Arrow&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf defeated, on his corpse you will find an item of &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure%23Well-off%20treasure\"&gt;well-off random treasure&lt;/a&gt;, 25 and the &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%20Prison%20Key\"&gt;key&lt;/a&gt; that unlocks the cell holding the captive child of &lt;a href=\"Garren%20Windspear\"&gt;Garren Windspear&lt;/a&gt; (either &lt;a href=\"Iltha\"&gt;Iltha&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Taar\"&gt;Taar&lt;/a&gt;).\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some changes to Conster, especially if the \"Smarter Mage\" component is installed. The mage is still a conjurer, but has a revised spell book with many different memorized spells, and more conjuration variety.\nIn battle, Conster will apply a series of buffs (previously cast) to include: &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity Invocation&lt;/a&gt; (or \"Dispelling Screen\" with &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;SR Mod&lt;/a&gt;), &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Normal%20Missiles\"&gt;Protection From Normal Missiles&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Cold\"&gt;Protection From Cold&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt;. Also added to the group will be a conjured &lt;a href=\"Invisible%20Stalker\"&gt;Invisible Stalker&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfterwards the SCS AI script will conduct threat recognition and opponent vulnerability assessments. This guides the offensive and other spells cast next. Conster can remove magical defenses with &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Khelben%27s%20Warding%20Whip\"&gt;Khelben's Warding Whip&lt;/a&gt;. If enemy summoned creatures are detected, a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; can be cast.\nA prepared &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trigger\"&gt;Spell Trigger&lt;/a&gt; are ready to deploy during the battle, near instantly.\nAs a conjurer, Conster has a good number of summoning spells to add allies to attack the party, including a &lt;a href=\"Djinni\"&gt;Djinni&lt;/a&gt;, Fire and Air Elementals, and some high-level creatures. The mage has some random SCS potions for consumption during battle to heal or boost abilities and is scripted to quaff them.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; all the mages spell will be the SR versions. Summoned/conjured creatures will have the SR stats and abilities, but combined with SCS will also have improved AI scripts (like the spell casting Djinni)"}
{"id": "6263", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6263", "title": "Constitution", "text": "Constitution is one of the six &lt;a href=\"Ability%20Scores\"&gt;ability scores&lt;/a&gt;.\nFor warrior and priest &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Class%20group\"&gt;class group&lt;/a&gt;, constitution modifies their &lt;a href=\"Hit%20Dice\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; for the first 9 levels, for wizard, rogue class group, the first 10 levels. For example, a &lt;a href=\"Ranger\"&gt;Ranger&lt;/a&gt; with 18 constitution gains 1d10+4 HP each level from 1 to 9 and a fixed +3 each level afterwards; a &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt; with 15 constitution gains 1d4+1 HP each level from 1 to 10 and a fixed +2 each level afterwards. The effects of constitution altering are retroactive, whenever the score changes, hit points are immediately added or subtracted. Having 20 or more constitution also grants HP regeneration.\n&lt;a href=\"Dwarf\"&gt;Dwarves&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Halfling\"&gt;Halfling&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Gnome\"&gt;Gnome&lt;/a&gt;s, get bonuses called \"shorty bonuses\" to &lt;a href=\"saving%20throw\"&gt;saving throw&lt;/a&gt;s based on their constitution, Dwarves and Halflings both have the bonus added to their death, wands and spells ST, while Gnomes receive this bonus to vs. wands and spells, these bonuses are re-calculated only on level-up.\nConstitution also affects how much time spent before a character gets &lt;a href=\"Fatigue\"&gt;fatigued&lt;/a&gt; and their capacity for liquor.\nThe classic Baldur's Gate manual describes a \"resurrection chance\" based on constitution, but this is not actually implemented in game. All &lt;a href=\"companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; can be resurrected regardless of their constitution score provided their body is salvageable, that is, the companion's hit points haven't been reduced below \"-10\", or been turned to stone and subsequently shattered. On normal difficulties and below, companions can be resurrected even if their body was destroyed.\nMod content.\nIf the \"Boareskyr Bridge Scene\" mod is installed, in a +1 constitution boost is gained by taking the third choice when crossing the Boareskyr Bridge (Evil Choice). The other answers increase wisdom or dexterity (answers 1 and 2 respectively)."}
{"id": "52956", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52956", "title": "Constitution (BG3)", "text": "Constitution (CON) is one of the six &lt;a href=\"Ability%20Scores%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;Ability Scores&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20III\"&gt;Baldur's Gate III&lt;/a&gt;\". It represents a creature's stamina and physical endurance, and affects their maximum &lt;a href=\"hit%20point%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;hit points&lt;/a&gt;. Although it is not a primary ability for any class, Constitution is important for any character."}
