{"id": "56087", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56087", "title": "Construct (card)", "text": "The Construct card, can be drawn from the deck of many things when agreeing to play a game with &lt;a href=\"Aesgareth\"&gt;Aesgareth&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis page is to document the potential spell effects of this card when it is drawn.\nGameplay.\nWhen Aesgareth takes a turn in the first draw contest, there is an even chance of drawing the Construct card, or the &lt;a href=\"Triumph%20%28card%29\"&gt;Triumph (card)&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf this card is drawn, the cambion is has a unique version of an &lt;a href=\"Adamantite%20Golem\"&gt;Adamantite Golem&lt;/a&gt; conjured adjacent to the fiend. The golem will attack Aesgareth.\nAesgareth and his servants will counterattack the golem, and eventually destroy it.\nHealing spells will be cast by the Tiefling cleric afterwards.\nNote that the golem is secretly gimped by a &lt;a href=\"Slow\"&gt;Slow&lt;/a&gt; effect, and only has 50 hit points, ensuring its rapid demise."}
