{"id": "49832", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49832", "title": "Contract (OHNNOTE1.itm)", "text": "The Contract is found in Lanneth's room in the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Wizard%20Enclave\"&gt;Red Wizard Enclave&lt;/a&gt;, opened by the &lt;a href=\"Laboratory%20Key\"&gt;Laboratory Key&lt;/a&gt;, during the quest &lt;a href=\"Neera%27s%20Hidden%20Refuge\"&gt;Neera's Hidden Refuge&lt;/a&gt;. It is signed by &lt;a href=\"Lanneth\"&gt;Lanneth&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hayes\"&gt;Hayes&lt;/a&gt;, and witnessed by &lt;a href=\"Gul%20Dukeem\"&gt;Gul Dukeem&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "52108", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52108", "title": "Control Circlet", "text": "The\u00a0Control Circlet\u00a0can be produced by an unusual illithid machine apparatus in a specific chamber within the &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayers%20in%20Underdark\"&gt;Mind Flayers in Underdark&lt;/a&gt; complex reached from the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt; area map and the Eastern Tunnels transition. \nGameplay.\nThe circlet is \"manufactured\" by adding the &lt;a href=\"Illithid%20Serum\"&gt;Illithid Serum&lt;/a&gt; to the machine and interacting with it using the cursor. Up to four circlets can be made before the machine's ability is exhausted. \nAdditional background, some explanation of the machine and other pertinent dialogue can be obtained from the &lt;a href=\"Slave%20Leader%20%28Illithids%29\"&gt;Slave Leader (Illithids)&lt;/a&gt;.\nEach circlet has one charge available that can launch a projectile with a 4 feet range at any targetable creature in the game. The creature will be exposed to a Dire Charm effect that bypasses all protections and magic resistance. There is no saving throw against the effect. The creature will be Dire Charmed for an 1800 duration. During this period, it can be commanded to do some activities, such as attack another creature in melee combat, move where directed, and other very limited actions.\nAs this charmed creature relates to the &lt;a href=\"Captured%20by%20Mind%20Flayers\"&gt;Captured by Mind Flayers&lt;/a&gt; quest, the circlet can be employed to take control of an illithid, and force it to open doors that are psionically sealed by &lt;a href=\"The%20Master%20Brain\"&gt;The Master Brain&lt;/a&gt;. Those specially locked doors can only be opened doing this action, or by the protagonist turning into the &lt;a href=\"Slayer%20Form\"&gt;Slayer Form&lt;/a&gt;. No other methods can open these specific doors, including using a door bash or a &lt;a href=\"Knock\"&gt;Knock&lt;/a&gt; spell effect (and there are no keys to be found).\nAny illithids that are dire charmed will revert to hostile status as soon as they are used to open one of these doors, so in reality, the charm duration isn't actually adhered to.\nThe only way to resist the Dire Charm effect of this circlet is to be immune to the &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Creature\"&gt;Charm Creature&lt;/a&gt; effect itself. Any creature that is protected against charm will therefore not be affected by the Control Circlet.\nOnce a circlet's charges are expended the item is destroyed."}
{"id": "5849", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5849", "title": "Control Undead", "text": "Control Undead allows a wizard to take control of up to 4 undead creatures.\nGameplay.\nThe caster directs this spell at a single &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; creature in range.\nThe spell only affects creatures with a General Identifier file coded as Undead.\nOnce casting is finished the spell launches a projectile that travels rapidly to the undead creature.\nThe projectile has a relatively small area of effect (similar to a &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Hold Person&lt;/a&gt; spell) reaching out to 5 feet radius from the initial targeted creature - if there are other undead in that AoE, then the spell can affect them too.\nThe spell implements a modified &lt;a href=\"Charmed\"&gt;Charmed&lt;/a&gt; effect on the undead - equivalent to a hostile domination type charm, forcing the creature to obey commands for the spell's duration.\nUndead with 3 or less &lt;a href=\"Hit%20Dice\"&gt;Hit Dice&lt;/a&gt; get no saving throw, while others are allowed a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus spells to negate.\nThis spell bypasses &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; but can otherwise be blocked with a spell protection that can stop a &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; 7 effect, or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Necromancy&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe charm effect lasts until expiry or if removed by a &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nAs this spell uses a modified charm &lt;a href=\"Opcode\"&gt;effect code&lt;/a&gt;, undead creatures that are normally immune to charm effects are not immune to this one.\nA controlled undead creature(s) is still subjected to the party's &lt;a href=\"Turn%20Undead\"&gt;Turn Undead&lt;/a&gt; ability, so keep that in mind when deciding to use this spell, less the newly controlled undead are turned/destroyed by the party's cleric/paladin shortly thereafter, making the spell cast somewhat unnecessary.\nMod Content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; Mod changes this spell - including duration, saving throw, effects and description. See below:\nControl Undead&lt;br&gt;\nLevel: 7&lt;br&gt;\nSchool: Necromancy&lt;br&gt;\nRange: Long&lt;br&gt;\nDuration: 5 turns&lt;br&gt;\nCasting Time: 7&lt;br&gt;\nArea of Effect: Target, and enemies within 5\u2019&lt;br&gt;\nSaving Throw: Special&lt;br&gt;\nThe Control Undead spell allows the caster to take control of undead creatures within the area of effect. This creates a telepathic link between the caster and the undead, allowing complete control. If the undead have 5 or more Hit Dice/levels less than the caster then there is no saving throw allowed, else a save vs. spell at -6 is allowed to negate the effect. The undead remain under control of the caster for the duration of the spell or until they are affected by a dispel magic."}
{"id": "34335", "revid": "35642161", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34335", "title": "Convenient Enhanced Edition NPCs", "text": "Convenient Enhanced Edition NPCs is a &lt;a href=\"companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt;-related mod for the \"\" and \" Enhanced Edition\"s. It aims to tone down or completely remove content added by the these, bringing them closer to the original . It also allows you to change the class of the EE NPCs.\nAffected companions are:\nFeatures.\nThis mod is highly modular and can affect either all or a selection of the mentioned companions in two ways:\nThe second component of the mod then offers to make the selected companions' personal and quest items available for sale in .\nThe third component modifies the EE NPCs class, for example, changing Hexxat to be a Shadowdancer."}
