{"id": "2456", "revid": "224791", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2456", "title": "Coordinates", "text": "Coordinates are a good way to keep track of locations of characters, containers, and items in the game.\nThe key used to show the coordinates depends on and edition: while it is \"L\"1 in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" and its expansion \"\", it is \"X\"1 in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\" and the \"Enhanced Editions\". The assigned key can be changed through the games' configuration tools or settings.\n1 The lower case variant of the keys works, codice_1 does not have to be pressed.\nThe co-ordinates of your cursor along with the code for the &lt;a href=\"Areas\"&gt;area&lt;/a&gt; you are in will appear in your &lt;a href=\"Dialogue%20Window\"&gt;dialogue window&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is not possible to view coordinates or assign a key to do so in the PlayStation 4, Xbox One, or Nintendo Switch releases of the Enhanced Editions. On Ps4, keep X pressed and move L3 to highlight interactive element, including hidden storage. \nWhen containers, characters, or other items in the game may be hard to locate for players, coordinates may be provided to help pinpoint the location. Coordinates should be provided in the following format: parenthetical notation, X coordinate followed by Y coordinate separated by a period, e.g. (&lt;a href=\"Coordinates\"&gt;xxxx.xxxx&lt;/a&gt;). On the first occurrence of coordinates on a page, please include a link to the coordinates page as shown. When adding coordinates as a \"tag\" to an object or area, it is preferable to use the location templates, by typing codice_2 (area can be omitted when not necessary, such as coordinates on an area's own page). As an example of this template in action, coordinates will appear like this: To distinguish between games, and should be used, rather than the base template. For more information, see ."}
{"id": "53404", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53404", "title": "Coordinator", "text": "Coordinator is a male figure that has the appearance of a monk with a staff. He can be encountered in &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Main%20Floor\"&gt;Spellhold Main Floor&lt;/a&gt; area in .\nGameplay.\nThe unnamed Coordinator is ostensibly a Cowled Wizard official working in some capacity within the Spellhold facility. He contacts the party as soon as entry is made into the building when the party is in possession of the &lt;a href=\"Wardstone%20for%20Asylum\"&gt;Wardstone for Asylum&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe coordinator calmly and politely responds to questions and eventually leads the party on a tour to show the treatment of some of the inmates, and also promises to lead the PC to Imoen. He says:\nThe coordinator leads the party on a tour of the cellblock, stopping at each occupied cell and giving a short description of the diagnosis and history of the inmate within. Each inmate will have dialogue of some degree, and this can trigger interjections by certain core party members. \nAt the end of the tour, the party can find Imoen in the \"Inmate Commons\" room. The coordinator will then explain her state of mental health, paraphrased below:\nThe PC can provide statements, some angry and terse, but in the end, the Coordinator takes the initiative and can't be prevented from exposing all party members to a special sleep cloud that renders them all helpless.\nThe coordinator has tricked the party into a trap. The next event that will occur is a scene where the party is split up, all members but the PC are caged and (not controllable), and the bhaalspawn is trapped in a glass enclosure in some kind of laboratory. &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;Jon Irenicus&lt;/a&gt; will address the PC. This is covered in the &lt;a href=\"Escaping%20the%20asylum\"&gt;Escaping the asylum&lt;/a&gt; article."}
{"id": "5655", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5655", "title": "Copper Coronet", "text": "The Copper Coronet is a large tavern and inn in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;Slums&lt;/a&gt;. It can be used as an access point to the slum district &lt;a href=\"Sewers%20%28Slums%20District%29\"&gt;sewers&lt;/a&gt;.\nContainers.\nThere a various barrels, chests, tabletops, shelves and other nooks with potential treasures in them. Some have nothing, others have random treasures. It's yours for the taking if you can find them and are inclined to help yourself. Some may be locked. Some might be trapped too. \nCreatures.\nCompanions.\n&lt;a href=\"Nalia%20de%27Arnise\"&gt;Nalia de'Arnise&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Anomen%20Delryn\"&gt;Anomen Delryn&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Korgan%20Bloodaxe\"&gt;Korgan Bloodaxe&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Hexxat\"&gt;Hexxat&lt;/a&gt; can all be recruited here, though for Nalia, Korgan, and Hexxat you will have to go through a sub-quest first. Also, if you dismissed either &lt;a href=\"Minsc\"&gt;Minsc&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Imoen\"&gt;Imoen&lt;/a&gt; or Edwin, they can all be found in the tavern if you want to re-hire them. &lt;a href=\"Yoshimo\"&gt;Yoshimo&lt;/a&gt; can also be here if you dismissed him, but only before &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%204\"&gt;Chapter 4&lt;/a&gt; due to plot reasons.\nCopper Coronet patrons and gameplay.\nThere are several patrons including commoners, noblemen and various drunks in the tavern public bar and also in the rear/upstairs \"exclusive\" areas. All have dialogue if you engage. Some have specific lines and opinions depending on who is in your party. There are lines for &lt;a href=\"Viconia\"&gt;Viconia&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Anomen%20Delryn\"&gt;Anomen Delryn&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Jan%20Jansen\"&gt;Jan Jansen&lt;/a&gt; and others. One particular drunk (a \"fat man\" animation\") has quite a long and burp filled tale about his recent mugging assault and heroic defense. Don't miss it! Try speaking with everyone you can. There are clues, nonsense, folly, and insight available.\nFor first time players, speaking with everyone you can in here is the best way to go. Enough clues are provided for you to figure out how to get into the back rooms of the Copper Coronet. So, no spoilers here about that. The wiki is sure that you can crack that nut and solve this by playing the game.\nUpon first visit to the Copper Coronet, a local bully named &lt;a href=\"Amalas\"&gt;Amalas&lt;/a&gt; accompanied by two other toughs (or \"Ruffians\"), will address the protagonist. If the PC is a female the volley of antagonistic insults will be different and quite annoying. Amalas is trying to goad the PC into the \"fighting pit\" for a fight to the finish, most likely to prove his prowess and also for some side bet wagering opportunity. The PC can agree and have a one on one fight or try and deescalate the situation with various dialogue choices. However, if Minsc is in the party and with a female PC, this is not going to end peacefully, as the Ranger won't stand for the bullying and attacks the ruffians. \n&lt;a href=\"Anomen\"&gt;Anomen&lt;/a&gt; will speak to the party if you get close enough to him. He can join the party if desired. Anomen has his own quests if in the party.\n&lt;a href=\"Hexxat\"&gt;Hexxat&lt;/a&gt; can be found near the staircase to the second floor. She'll initiate a call for help, trying to get the party to assist with visiting a tomb and promise of great treasure. She's behaving strangely, and her speaking ability seems unnatural. You may take her into the party as a companion if desired, or leave it alone until later, or never. This is BG2EE Content only, for those who are still playing the original game.\n&lt;a href=\"Korgan%20Bloodaxe\"&gt;Korgan Bloodaxe&lt;/a&gt; is also in the tavern. The party must initiate conversation with him. He can also join the party as a companion. Korgan has his own quest if in the party.\n&lt;a href=\"Nalia%20de%27Arnise\"&gt;Nalia de'Arnise&lt;/a&gt; will approach the party when she sees the group. She'll ask for assistance with a problem. If desired, she can join the party as a companion, or be sent ahead and met later, or the party can temporarily decline speaking with her until later (or never). She is the only way to get the &lt;a href=\"The%20de%27Arnise%20Keep%20has%20been%20Invaded\"&gt;The de'Arnise Keep has been Invaded&lt;/a&gt; quest, and that quest is also the only way to obtain the &lt;a href=\"Ruling%20the%20de%27Arnise%20Keep%20and%20Lands\"&gt;Ruling the de'Arnise Keep and Lands&lt;/a&gt; stronghold quests.\n&lt;a href=\"Lord%20Jierdan\"&gt;Lord Jierdan&lt;/a&gt; does not initiate conversation, but he does announce out loud to anyone within a certain range that he has an offer if the party wishes to hear it. If so, initiate dialogue with him.\n&lt;a href=\"Yarin\"&gt;Yarin&lt;/a&gt; located in a room upstairs has special dialogue if Yoshimo is in the party and he speaks with him. Give it a try.\n&lt;a href=\"Tiana\"&gt;Tiana&lt;/a&gt; is on the tavern floor. She's angry and looking for her husband &lt;a href=\"Rumar\"&gt;Rumar&lt;/a&gt;. If you find Rumar and his clandestine fling &lt;a href=\"Priss\"&gt;Priss&lt;/a&gt;, you can then let Tiana know that you spotted her husband upstairs. Tiana will then march upstairs and straight over to Rumar and Priss. A fight will break out between the two women. If the party intervenes and helps kill Tiana there is a XP reward, and some rich &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure\"&gt;Random treasure&lt;/a&gt;. If the party helps slay Priss, that results in a reputation loss for an innocent. Or the party can just watch the encounter and hear all the delicious dialogue.\n&lt;a href=\"Salvanas%20di%20Riyos\"&gt;Salvanas&lt;/a&gt; is smooth talking character. Special dialogue is available for any female party members that speak to him individually, such as the PC, Jaheria, Aerie etc. It is unique for each person, and humorous as well. \n&lt;a href=\"Madame%20Nin\"&gt;Madame Nin&lt;/a&gt; is located upstairs. Speak with her to hire some temporary love. If someone in the party does, then speak with the companion to get insight into their status, and it will add more to the impressions that the Copper Coronet is engaging in some morally questionable activities. There are also additional girls upstairs, already with clients. Speaking with them add even more information to consider. If any of the companions complain that you are asking too many questions, Madame Nin may ban you from further paid companionship. If Yoshimo is in the party, there is special dialogue with the girls, and some humorous lines if he speaks with one of the other patrons with his hired companion. After the &lt;a href=\"Free%20Hendak%20and%20the%20slaves\"&gt;Free Hendak and the slaves&lt;/a&gt; quest is complete, Madame Nin will abscond from the Copper Coronet.\nBugs.\nAs of BG2EE 2.6, several doors in various areas, including this one, would disappear when opened, leaving no way to close them. This is identified for correction in the pending Enhanced Edition Fix Pack (EEFP).\nReference: (ar0406.are, ar0711.are, ar1302.are, ar1307.are, ar1307.are, ar5007.are)"}
{"id": "48455", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48455", "title": "Copper Coronet Guard", "text": "When the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; enters the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt; and receives permission from &lt;a href=\"Lehtinan\"&gt;Lehtinan&lt;/a&gt; to access the \"back rooms\" of his inn, two Copper Coronet Guards will be encountered when the party enters this area. The guard near the first door will approach the party and give the ok to look around. \nTraveling down the long hallway leads to another door that opens to the area where some jail cells are located. The second guard in this area will inform the party that they have entered a restricted area. Any reply given, except offering to leave, will result in the guard becoming hostile and summoning five more guards; three of these summoned guards are straight &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt;s and the other two are fighter/mages. Two of the fighters and both mages will appear in the jail cell area while the third fighter appears in the short hallway that leads to the &lt;a href=\"Sewers%20%28Slums%20District%29\"&gt;sewers&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce these guards have been defeated and the &lt;a href=\"Beastmaster%20Key\"&gt;key&lt;/a&gt; to the jail cells has been recovered from the &lt;a href=\"Beastmaster\"&gt;Beastmaster&lt;/a&gt;, freeing &lt;a href=\"Hendak\"&gt;Hendak&lt;/a&gt; from his imprisonment will result in two more guards appearing in the long hallway and near the entrance to the back rooms, respectively.\nKilling all of nine of these guards will not lead to a loss of &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis Copper Coronet Guard is the straight fighter summoned by the jail cell guard. These guards have 20 &lt;a href=\"Hit%20point\"&gt;hit points&lt;/a&gt; and give 1000 &lt;a href=\"XP\"&gt;XP&lt;/a&gt; when killed.\nThis Copper Coronet Guard is the fighter/mage summoned by the jail cell guard. These guards have no armor and 40 &lt;a href=\"Hit%20point\"&gt;hit points&lt;/a&gt;, but give 2000 &lt;a href=\"XP\"&gt;XP&lt;/a&gt; when killed. Their \"mage\" script allows them to utilize every spell in their spell book before they revert to melee attack with thier &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaff\"&gt;Quarterstaff&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "48913", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48913", "title": "Cor Delryn", "text": "Cor Delryn is the father of &lt;a href=\"Anomen%20Delryn\"&gt;Anomen Delryn&lt;/a&gt; and resides at &lt;a href=\"Delryn%20Estate\"&gt;Delryn Estate&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Government\"&gt;Government District&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign."}
{"id": "3418", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3418", "title": "Coran", "text": "Coran is a &lt;a href=\"male\"&gt;male&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"elf\"&gt;elf&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"chaotic%20good\"&gt;chaotic good&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"multi-class\"&gt;multi-class&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Fighter%20/%20Thief\"&gt;fighter/thief&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\", where &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; may choose him as a &lt;a href=\"companion\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe has also short appearances in ' and '.\n&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; &amp;.\nRecruitment.\nCoran is available from &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Four\"&gt;Chapter Four&lt;/a&gt;. He can be found standing at the middle of a bridge in NW of first part of &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood\"&gt;Cloakwood&lt;/a&gt;. He will ask you to join his &lt;a href=\"Coran%20the%20Wyvern%20Hunter\"&gt;plan&lt;/a&gt; in bringing the governor of &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt; a 'dragon's head', if it is accepted, he will join the party.\nGameplay.\nHis starting equipment is: leather armor, a long bow, 20 arrows and a long sword. He is an &lt;a href=\"elf\"&gt;elf&lt;/a&gt; (+1 &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;to-hit&lt;/a&gt; with bows and swords), and he has 20 &lt;a href=\"dexterity\"&gt;dexterity&lt;/a&gt; (1 point over the elf max, a minor bonus to his thief skills, +3 to-hit with ranged weapons) and 3 &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20proficiency\"&gt;proficiency points&lt;/a&gt; in longbow (Mastery: +3 to-hit/damage, +1/2 attack) which player-made multi-class fighters cannot do, making him the best archer companion in BG1. If he's given the &lt;a href=\"Gauntlets%20of%20Ogre%20Power\"&gt;Gauntlets of Ogre Power&lt;/a&gt;, he can use composite bows as well.\n\" note\": &lt;a href=\"companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; who are under-leveled at the time of joining will be given a certain amount of &lt;a href=\"Experience%20tables\"&gt;experience points&lt;/a&gt; (XP) for you to manually level them up to gain more control of their proficiencies and skill point allocation.\n\nCoran's appearance in Siege of Dragonspear is rather short as his \"maiden\" affair was discovered by &lt;a href=\"Safana\"&gt;Safana&lt;/a&gt;, who he apparently had developed a relationship with. He'll greet the player on the second floor of &lt;a href=\"Elfsong%20Tavern\"&gt;Elfsong Tavern&lt;/a&gt; but quickly run away before Safana's fury devours him.\nCoran makes a cameo in\u00a0Baldur's Gate II: Shadows of Amn, found in the northwest portion of the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Tethir%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;Forest of Tethir&lt;/a&gt;. He cannot be recruited into the party, but does ask for your help in &lt;a href=\"Coran%20and%20the%20Wolfweres\"&gt;freeing\u00a0Safana&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0from a group of wolfweres."}
{"id": "55001", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55001", "title": "Coran's Cabin", "text": "Coran's Cabin is a location found in the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Tethir%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;Forest of Tethir (Shadows of Amn)&lt;/a&gt; map reachable in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; as part of the and game versions.\nBackground.\nThe structure can be explored after initial dialogue with &lt;a href=\"Coran\"&gt;Coran&lt;/a&gt;, who stands adjacent to the home. After dialogue, Coran departs and the subsequent registry of the &lt;a href=\"Coran%20and%20the%20Wolfweres\"&gt;Coran and the Wolfweres&lt;/a&gt; side quest takes place. The Automap Marker for the Forest of Tethir area simply labels this structure as \"Cabin\", but the game files title it as \"Coran's Cabin\".\nBased on the unhealthy infestation found within, it isn't hard to see why Coran wasn't encountered inside. It's too bad he had no commentary about what lurks within the cabin, as entry will provide a nasty surprise for the party.\nGameplay walkthrough.\nThe party can ignore this cabin if they wish. There is no required quest completion requirement to explore it.\nBut, exploring is what adventurers do, so let's assume the player directs the party to enter the cabin.\nThe party transitions through the doorway from the front cabin porch and is immediately beset upon by a mixed group of unfriendly mist creatures, as shown in the InfoBox.\nSeveral of the mists have special innate ability attacks that will likely require making a few saving throws. Be aware of potential &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt; touch attacks here as well.\nShould the party manage to dispose of the creatures, there are a total of six \"containers\" within the two-room structure that can be examined. Recommended practice is to assume something could be trapped, as well as locked - so take precautions before opening these containers."}
{"id": "5966", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5966", "title": "Coran and the Wolfweres", "text": "Coran and the Wolfweres is a &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt; side quest which can be started either in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%207\"&gt;Chapter 7&lt;/a&gt;.\nAquisition.\nWhen a party member is within a certain distance of Coran, he'll initiate dialog. Coran is adjacent to a Cabin structure in the forest. The quest is added to the player's journal after dialogue with Coran is concluded.\nWalk through (abbreviated).\nIn the northwest part of the Forest of Tethir, near the cabin, you find &lt;a href=\"Coran\"&gt;Coran&lt;/a&gt;, a potential companion from Baldur's Gate. \nHe asks you to help him rescue &lt;a href=\"Safana\"&gt;Safana&lt;/a&gt;, another potential companion from Baldur's Gate, who has been captured by &lt;a href=\"wolfwere\"&gt;wolfwere&lt;/a&gt;s. The Wolfwere camp is marked on your map. It's located to the East, near the point where you entered the area. \nOnce the party arrives at the camp, they learn that Safana is in league with &lt;a href=\"Lanfear\"&gt;Lanfear&lt;/a&gt;, a female lycanthrope, to kill the bhaalspawn because of the bounty on &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;. \nHowever, Lanfear has only done this to meet Coran again.\u00a0 They spent a night together when she was in human form. Coran, disgusted by this, is unwilling to cooperate. \nLanfear spitefully kills Safana when Coran refutes her advances and then she and her pack attack Coran and the party. The wolferes must be defeated. \nOnce the wolfweres have been downed, Coran address the party (assuming he lived) again. An invitation to join the party is politely declined, although he admits the offer is tempting. He thanks you for your help and leaves the area - no doubt seeking an Alehouse where he can soak his sorrows."}
{"id": "13265", "revid": "78773", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13265", "title": "Coran the Wyvern Hunter", "text": "This is the companion quest for &lt;a href=\"Coran\"&gt;Coran&lt;/a&gt;, the rather seedy (although Chaotic Good in &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;alignment&lt;/a&gt;) Fighter / Thief from the &lt;a href=\"First%20Cloakwood\"&gt;First Cloakwood&lt;/a&gt; area.\nCoran has been tasked with obtaining a &lt;a href=\"Wyvern\"&gt;Wyvern&lt;/a&gt; head by &lt;a href=\"Kelddath%20Ormlyr\"&gt;Kelddath Ormlyr&lt;/a&gt;, governor of &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt; and priest of the &lt;a href=\"Song%20of%20the%20Morning%20Temple\"&gt;Song of the Morning Temple&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Temple\"&gt;Temple&lt;/a&gt; area east of Beregost. Kelddath has offered a substantial reward \u2014 for a single head \u2014 and Coran wants your assistance in obtaining one.\nThe head must come from an adult (as opposed to &lt;a href=\"Baby%20Wyvern\"&gt;Baby Wyvern&lt;/a&gt;) Wyvern, of which there are two in the &lt;a href=\"Wyvern%27s%20Cave\"&gt;Wyvern's Cave&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Fourth%20Cloakwood\"&gt;Fourth Cloakwood&lt;/a&gt; area.\nReturn the head of one to &lt;a href=\"Kelddath%20Ormlyr\"&gt;Kelddath&lt;/a&gt; at the Temple. In the original game the other can be sold to &lt;a href=\"Officer%20Vai\"&gt;Officer Vai&lt;/a&gt; for . In the enhanced edition she's strictly interested in &lt;a href=\"Bandit%20Scalp\"&gt;Bandit Scalp&lt;/a&gt;s. Selected merchants (like &lt;a href=\"Thalantyr%20the%20Conjurer\"&gt;Thalantyr&lt;/a&gt;) pay for each one of them (starting price, subject to &lt;a href=\"Game%20Terminology%23D\"&gt;depreciation&lt;/a&gt;).\nCompletion Timer.\nAfter seven in-game days, Coran will complain of his impatience if a Wyvern Head has not yet been acquired. Coran: \"I could while away days on end in the company of friends, but there is business to attend to as well. We must set out after our wyvern quarry soon lest we lose the chance at all.\"\nRumours to the contrary notwithstanding, after another seven days, he will leave the party, and the game, if a Wyvern Head has still not been acquired."}
{"id": "8147", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8147", "title": "Cordyr", "text": "Cordyr is a fisherman who was put out of work and now resides in his &lt;a href=\"Cordyr%27s%20Home\"&gt;house&lt;/a&gt; which is located between &lt;a href=\"Jopalin%27s%20Tavern\"&gt;Jopalin's Tavern&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Warehouses%20%28south%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;warehouse&lt;/a&gt; in the district of &lt;a href=\"South%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;South Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nCordyr's fishing grounds were located a fair way off to the south of the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;city&lt;/a&gt;, down the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt;, just north of an abandoned &lt;a href=\"lighthouse\"&gt;lighthouse&lt;/a&gt;. However, &lt;a href=\"sirine\"&gt;sirine&lt;/a&gt;s tried to move into that area and sank Cordyr's fishing boat. Now he's quite doubtful of how to deal with the situation.\nInvolvement.\nBeing conflicted between the beauty of those creatures and \"how much of a nuisance\" sirines can be, Cordyr tries to find people adequate to deal with such issues. \"Heroes\" or too \"popular\" &lt;a href=\"Party\"&gt;parties&lt;/a&gt; will not learn about his problem, but a less &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;reputable&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; may hear Cordyr's story \u2013 still, without any gruesome task, but expectations unspoken.\nHe even understands if the party decides not to kill &lt;a href=\"Sil\"&gt;Sil&lt;/a&gt;, head woman of that small tribe of sirines:\nIf the deed was done, Cordyr's reaction again focuses on the background and intentions of Gorion's Ward and his own objections, rewarding parties with an average or above reputation differently than disliked or despised ones, while speaking of \"steely hearts\", \"dirty deeds\" and the \"cost of civilization\". He even admits that he didn't believe, the party would survive the sirines.\nSee the Cordyr and the Sirines quest article for details about reputation requirements and possible rewards."}
{"id": "46572", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46572", "title": "Cordyr's Home", "text": "Cordyr's Home is the home of the fisherman &lt;a href=\"Cordyr\"&gt;Cordyr&lt;/a&gt; and is located between &lt;a href=\"Jopalin%27s%20Tavern\"&gt;Jopalin's Tavern&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Warehouses%20%28south%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;warehouse&lt;/a&gt; in the district of &lt;a href=\"South%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;South Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. The front door is locked with a DC of 30.\nCordyr can be found on the ground floor standing in the foyer and will immediately begin wandering the premises when you enter the house. The barrel in the kitchen contains 1 and the shelf contains a &lt;a href=\"Club\"&gt;Club&lt;/a&gt;.\nOn the second floor, a sleeping man and woman are present at night. All four of the beds have lootable nightstands next to them that are empty. The unlocked chest of drawers contains a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Healing&lt;/a&gt; and the bookshelf contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20I\"&gt;History of Shadowdale I&lt;/a&gt;."}
