{"id": "48373", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48373", "title": "Crazy Celvan", "text": "Crazy Celvan is an odd little Gnome encountered on the stairs above &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var%27s%20Guildhall\"&gt;Mae'Var's Guildhall&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Docks District&lt;/a&gt;. Try speaking to him with each individual party member. Celvan may have individualized limericks for that specific companion. It may take several attempts to get anything out of him except for his bizarre laugh. After dialogue, he will may run around the block, only to return, nearly, to his starting point or just wander around, as if he can't keep focused, and even disappear through a door to the guildhall or some other building, possibly never to be seen again.\nSince Crazy Celvan has no specified &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;Alignment&lt;/a&gt; perhaps this explains why he's so crazy? Can't make up his mind what he is or how he thinks? It's Crazy!\nCompanion Limericks.\nAerie.\n\"There once was an elf who could fly,&lt;br&gt;without wings she was sure she would die.&lt;br&gt;But soon she'll have found&lt;br&gt;that it is on the ground&lt;br&gt;that her true destiny does lie.\"\nAnomen.\n\"There once was a man full of woes,&lt;br&gt;strong and mighty he smote all his foes.&lt;br&gt;Soon he'll take his Test,&lt;br&gt;to him it's no jest,&lt;br&gt;if he'll pass not even he knows.\"\nJaheira.\n\"\"There once was an elf proud and fair,&lt;br&gt;men withered once under her stare.&lt;br&gt;But she loved one man true,&lt;br&gt;and he died...as men do,&lt;br&gt;and now there is naught but grief there.\"\"\nKeldorn.\n\"There once was a knight pure of heart,&lt;br&gt;from his wife he is always apart.&lt;br&gt;Has his heart grown colder&lt;br&gt;as his deeds grew bolder?&lt;br&gt;What is finished can never restart.\"\nMazzy.\n\"There once was a halfling so pure,&lt;br&gt;she's a paladin, as sure as she's sure.&lt;br&gt;If she's lucky one day&lt;br&gt;her goddess will smile and say&lt;br&gt;that the lack of one she'll no longer endure.\"\nMinsc.\n\"There once was a warrior true,&lt;br&gt;with the sense knocked out of him, too.&lt;br&gt;but in a hamster he found,&lt;br&gt;some wisdom profound,&lt;br&gt;and now where goes he goes his Boo!\"\nNeera.\n\"With no warning, a magical surging, &lt;br&gt;It comes regardless of urging.&lt;br&gt;Friends are burnt,&lt;br&gt;Yet lessons go unlearnt;&lt;br&gt;A new Neera will soon be emerging.\"\nValygar.\n\"There once was a man so afraid&lt;br&gt;that his soul was to be soon waylaid,&lt;br&gt;see, the wizard's returned&lt;br&gt;in his sphere, he has learned,&lt;br&gt;but has he learned if a soul can be weighed?\"\nGorion's Ward.\nWhen it comes to the protagonist, at random he might just giggle again \"Tee-hee hee!\" . . . OR, he clams up quick!\n\"\"There once was a child of...of...&lt;br&gt;Oh my...\"\nIf asked, \"What is it? How do you know so much about us?\"\n\"I..I.. (giggle!) ..the gods speak! The speak and speak and speak and speak! To ME!! Hee hee...\"\nYou can also threaten him, \"Tell me what you know about us or I'll knock you from one end of this city to the other!!\"\n\"AAAAAHHHHH!! DON'T MURDER ME!! AAAAAHHHHH!!\"\nIn either case, he will try to escape the area after this."}
{"id": "13570", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13570", "title": "Crazyface", "text": "Crazyface is a character in \"\". He appears on the roof of the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt; with Korgan's former friends during the &lt;a href=\"Help%20Korgan%20Recover%20the%20Book%20of%20Kaza\"&gt;companion quest&lt;/a&gt;. Crazyface has memorized various Cleric spells including &lt;a href=\"Barkskin\"&gt;Barkskin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Person%20or%20Mammal\"&gt;Charm Person or Mammal&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might\"&gt;Draw Upon Holy Might&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Hold Person (priest)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Animate%20Dead\"&gt;Animate Dead&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Animal%20Summoning%20II\"&gt;Animal Summoning II&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mental%20Domination\"&gt;Mental Domination&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Righteous%20Magic\"&gt;Righteous Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Slay%20Living\"&gt;Slay Living&lt;/a&gt;."}
