{"id": "47772", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47772", "title": "Dusk Ritual", "text": "The Dusk Ritual scroll is the third of three scrolls located within the &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple\"&gt;Ruined Temple&lt;/a&gt; that provide clues to the three-part Holy Ritual test.\nBackground.\nThe Holy Ritual test is a ritual that, when performed correctly, will allow the party to acquire one of three symbol pieces that make up the &lt;a href=\"Symbol%20of%20Amaunator\"&gt;Symbol of Amaunator&lt;/a&gt;. The symbol is needed to unlock the magically-warded door to the Lair of the &lt;a href=\"Shade%20Lord\"&gt;Dark One&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocation.\nThe scroll is found in a small statute of Amaunator in the room with the &lt;a href=\"Bone%20Golem\"&gt;Bone Golem&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "6188", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6188", "title": "Duskblade", "text": "Duskblade is an which appears in ' and\u00a0'.\nGameplay.\nThis two-handed weapon is an enchanted polearm. It has similar properties as a &lt;a href=\"Halberd%20%2B2\"&gt;Halberd +2&lt;/a&gt; and strikes for 1d10 +2 damage, 7 weapon &lt;a href=\"Speed%20Factor\"&gt;Speed Factor&lt;/a&gt;, -2 &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0bonus and a weight of 12 lbs.\nAdditionally, it also inflicts +2 points of &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;Cold damage&lt;/a&gt; when hitting a target creature. The cold is of the elemental type and bypasses magic resistance and spell protections.\nAcquisition.\nDuskblade is wielded in melee combat and eventually recovered as loot from &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Patrick\"&gt;Shadow Patrick&lt;/a&gt; during the battle between the &lt;a href=\"Shade%20Lord\"&gt;Shade Lord&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple\"&gt;Ruined Temple&lt;/a&gt; area during the side quest &lt;a href=\"Investigate%20the%20Deaths%20in%20the%20Umar%20Hills\"&gt;to stop the murders in Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt;."}
