{"id": "16587", "revid": "282391", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16587", "title": "Dwarven Doom Guard", "text": "There are four Dwarven Doom Guards guarding the tomb of &lt;a href=\"Durlag%20Trollkiller\"&gt;Durlag's&lt;/a&gt; son &lt;a href=\"Kiel%20the%20Legion%20Killer\"&gt;Kiel the Legion Killer&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey will not attack until one of them is provoked or when Kiel's &lt;a href=\"Kiel%27s%20Buckler\"&gt;buckler&lt;/a&gt; or his &lt;a href=\"Kiel%27s%20Morning%20Star\"&gt;morning star&lt;/a&gt; are removed from the chest at the foot of his final resting place.\nPhysical Description.\nLike the name suggests, these creatures are &lt;a href=\"Doom%20Guard\"&gt;Doom Guard&lt;/a&gt;s created from &lt;a href=\"Dwarf\"&gt;dwarven&lt;/a&gt;-sized armor, hence their smaller stature.\nGameplay.\nThe guards have a good THAC0, attack 4 times per round and have 18/00 strength, so they can deal a formidable amount of damage in one single round. They are also immune to many &lt;a href=\"status%20effects\"&gt;Status effects&lt;/a&gt; like fear or stun. However, their saving throws are modest enough so that are likely to be disabled by simple spells like &lt;a href=\"Blindness\"&gt;Blindness&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Web\"&gt;Web&lt;/a&gt;. There are four guards bunched together and normally if you upset one, you upset all, which makes for a formidable fight. If you cast blindness on one of the guards, the guard who is blinded will become aggro\u2019d, while the others remain neutral, allowing you to fight one at a time."}
