{"id": "51738", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51738", "title": "ELEMIMIX.ITM", "text": "ELEMIMIX.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by &lt;a href=\"Imix\"&gt;Imix&lt;/a&gt;, an evil elemental prince of fire. It is ostensibly a fist attack or melee attack by the fiery creature.\nGameplay.\nIt is considered a magical and +3 enchanted item and deals 1d6 damage (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a range of one foot, and speed factor of 0.\nThe item also applies a 6d6 &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt; on each successful strike. This damage is not magical, just elemental in nature, and can't be blocked by Spell level protections or magic resistance.\nEach hit on a target applies a &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; 10 &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect on the target. Whether it works or not, the combat record screen will display a \"Dispel effects\" text. The effect also destroys illusionary creatures that are struck, like a &lt;a href=\"Mislead\"&gt;Mislead&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Project%20Image\"&gt;Project Image&lt;/a&gt; phantasm. It will also cure &lt;a href=\"Feeblemindedness\"&gt;Feeblemindedness&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Deafness\"&gt;Deafness&lt;/a&gt; on the target.\nThe item bestows a special &lt;a href=\"Fireshield%20%28Red%29\"&gt;Fireshield (Red)&lt;/a&gt; spell effect that retaliates against the last attacker that strikes the item holder within about 6' range with weapon, spell or missile. The actual spell is SPIMIXD.spl, and the attacker will be exposed to a 1d12+8 &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt; attack that bypasses magic resistance. The fire damage is however assigned a level 4 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; and is subject to spell protections that can block that kind of effect, such as &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; as examples.\nThe final attribute this item bestows is a graphics application to the wielder of a &lt;a href=\"Fireshield%20%28Red%29\"&gt;Fireshield (Red)&lt;/a&gt; animation, that can't be removed or dispelled.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod alters this weapon and makes it a +5 enchanted item for the purposes of what it can strike."}
{"id": "51177", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51177", "title": "ELEMOGRE.ITM", "text": "ELEMOGRE.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by the elemental Prince of &lt;a href=\"Earth%20Elemental\"&gt;Earth Elemental&lt;/a&gt; creatures, &lt;a href=\"Ogremoch\"&gt;Ogremoch&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is considered a magical and +3 enchanted item and deals 5d10 damage (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), with a range of three feet, and speed factor of 0.\nAny hit on a target will induce a &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect, and the combat log will display a text \"Dispel Effects\". In addition, the dispel function will remove &lt;a href=\"Deafness\"&gt;Deafness&lt;/a&gt; on the target, destroy any creatures that are classified with a gender that is \"illusionary\", and remove and cure &lt;a href=\"Feeblemindedness\"&gt;Feeblemindedness&lt;/a&gt;. Due to the coding of this weapon, the Dispel magic effect is at the equivalent of a level 10 caster."}
