{"id": "2598", "revid": "285299", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2598", "title": "Edwin Odesseiron", "text": "Edwin Odesseiron is a &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;lawful evil&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Conjurer\"&gt;Conjurer&lt;/a&gt; and a potential &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt; in and .\n&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; &amp;.\nRecruitment.\nEdwin is available to recruit from &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Two\"&gt;Chapter Two&lt;/a&gt;. You can acquire him on a bridge at &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt; near the &lt;a href=\"Belching%20Dragon%20Tavern\"&gt;Belching Dragon Tavern&lt;/a&gt;. He asks you to help him find and kill the witch &lt;a href=\"Dynaheir\"&gt;Dynaheir&lt;/a&gt;, another potential companion. Normally it isn't possible to have both Edwin and Dynaheir in the same party because the player character has to choose a side between Edwin or Dynaheir &amp; &lt;a href=\"Minsc\"&gt;Minsc&lt;/a&gt;, if the party brought him as well. A workaround for this problem is that the party can acquire Edwin after saving Dynaheir from the &lt;a href=\"Gnoll%20Stronghold\"&gt;Gnoll Stronghold&lt;/a&gt;. At this point there'll be an option to take him along and Edwin says he will keep an eye on her.\nGameplay.\nIn BG1 &lt;a href=\"Edwin%27s%20Amulet\"&gt;his family amulet&lt;/a&gt; which can't be removed gives him an additional spell per spell level in addition to his &lt;a href=\"Specialist%20Mage\"&gt;conjurer&lt;/a&gt; specialization which gives him another spell per level with the penalty of not getting divination spells, the increased &lt;a href=\"Experience%20tables\"&gt;XP&lt;/a&gt; cap of lets him cast up to three level 5 spells. He has the second highest &lt;a href=\"intelligence\"&gt;intelligence&lt;/a&gt; among other companions. His &lt;a href=\"constitution\"&gt;constitution&lt;/a&gt; score of 16 grants him an additional adjustment of + 2\u00a0hp per level which is the maximum for non-warrior classes. He is one of the best wizard companions in game, rivaled only by &lt;a href=\"Baeloth%20Barrityl\"&gt;Baeloth.&lt;/a&gt;\nA &lt;a href=\"Exploits\"&gt;trick&lt;/a&gt; to use him is to equip him with two &lt;a href=\"Evermemory\"&gt;Rings of Wizardry&lt;/a&gt; so he's capable of casting 20 magic missiles per day at level 9. This however, is not possible in enhanced edition of the game because you can only wear one Ring of Wizardry.\nRecruitment.\nEdwin is available from Chapter 8. You'll see him storming east of the army camp at &lt;a href=\"Coast%20Way%20Crossing\"&gt;Coast Way Crossing&lt;/a&gt;, angrily mumbling about &lt;a href=\"Caelar%20Argent\"&gt;Caelar&lt;/a&gt;, you can convince him to join the party once he sees that you share the same goal.\nRelated quests.\nEdwin wants you to kill &lt;a href=\"Vichand\"&gt;Vichand&lt;/a&gt;, a fellow red wizard of &lt;a href=\"Thay\"&gt;Thay&lt;/a&gt; who joined the crusade. Vichand can be found in crusader camp at\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Boareskyr%20Bridge\"&gt;Boareskyr Bridge&lt;/a&gt;. In order for the quest to complete, Edwin needs to see his corpse in in the aforementioned area Boareskyr Bridge (BD2000). This means that if you resolve the siege situation without Edwin in your party, you will afterwards never be able to get him to acknowledge the kill (expressed without dialog but just the string \"Vichand is dead! Such is the fate of any enemy of Edwin!\"). 3 hours after that acknowledgement, Edwin will reward you with a &lt;a href=\"Robe%20of%20Red%20Flames\"&gt;Robe of Red Flames&lt;/a&gt;, which can be &lt;a href=\"Importing%20a%20Character%23Siege%20of%20Dragonspear%20Items\"&gt;imported&lt;/a&gt; into.\n&amp;.\nRecruitment.\nEdwin is available from &lt;a href=\"Chapter%202\"&gt;Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt;. He can be recruited in Mae'var's Guildhall during &lt;a href=\"Find%20proof%20of%20Mae%27var%27s%20Treachery\"&gt;Find proof of Mae'var's Treachery&lt;/a&gt;, which potentially leads to obtaining the thief &lt;a href=\"stronghold\"&gt;stronghold&lt;/a&gt;. If you \"underestimate his importance\", he offers the choice to be right where you left him or at the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn Enhanced Edition he will be level 9, Trained in Dagger and Quarterstaff.\nGameplay.\n&lt;a href=\"Edwin%27s%20Amulet\"&gt;His family amulet&lt;/a&gt; now gives him \"two\" additional spells per level instead of one in BG1, the total bonus for him would be three extra spells per spell level as he's also a &lt;a href=\"Specialist%20Mage\"&gt;conjurer&lt;/a&gt;. His &lt;a href=\"intelligence\"&gt;intelligence&lt;/a&gt; score of 18 allows him to scribe level 9 spells without an &lt;a href=\"intelligence\"&gt;intelligence&lt;/a&gt; modification. His main drawback is not accessing to which is a minor issue for the game offers plenty of other ways of casting &lt;a href=\"True%20Sight\"&gt;True Sight&lt;/a&gt;. Another drawback is that his amulet, while powerful, prevents him from wearing the &lt;a href=\"Amulet%20of%20Power\"&gt;Amulet of Power&lt;/a&gt;, making him unable to benefit from the maximum casting time reduction of 5 by stacking it with the &lt;a href=\"Robe%20of%20Vecna\"&gt;Robe of Vecna&lt;/a&gt;, although many players consider this to be worth the price.\nConsidering the overall power\u00a0of the &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; spell pool, especially some \"law-defining\" spells like &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Alacrity\"&gt;Improved Alacrity&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Contingency\"&gt;Chain Contingency&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Project%20Image\"&gt;Project Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Haste\"&gt;Improved Haste&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, his unique +3 spells/level pushes him to a much higher ground once high level spell slots are unlocked while others are inevitably restricted by the limited numbers of castings.\nOn top of all that, Edwin gets a -1 bonus to his saving throws after obtaining the Nether Scroll in his personal quest.\nAchievements.\nThe Nether Scroll.\nHelp Edwin &lt;a href=\"Find%20the%20Nether%20Scroll%20for%20Edwin\"&gt;track down the Nether Scroll&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "47013", "revid": "27501436", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47013", "title": "Edwin Odesseiron/Quotes", "text": "Edwin Odesseiron's quotes presents lines spoken by &lt;a href=\"Edwin\"&gt;Edwin&lt;/a&gt;, together with the associated sound files.\nTrue to the reputation of the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Wizards%20of%20Thay\"&gt;Red Wizards of Thay&lt;/a&gt;, Edwin thinks of himself as a being of great power surrounded by clueless simians. His behavior rarely fits his self-professed status, as he is prone to cowardice, paranoia and occasional bouts of lecherousness. He enjoys asking insidious questions about the supposed high moral ground of the organization good-aligned members of the party belong to, an activity he calls \"baiting hooks\", as he is convinced benevolent companions are either fools or hypocrites.\nReckless deciphering of the Nether Scroll as part of his &lt;a href=\"Find%20the%20Nether%20Scroll%20for%20Edwin\"&gt;personal quest&lt;/a&gt; will turn Edwin into Edwina and trigger additional dialogue from most companions. \nDialogues.\nWith &lt;a href=\"Aerie\"&gt;Aerie&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen Edwin has less than 25% HP remaining :\nIf Edwin has been turned into a woman as part of his quest, and stands less than 10 units away from Aerie :\nThrone of Bhaal only :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Anomen\"&gt;Anomen&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf Edwin has been turned into a woman as part of his quest :\nThrone of Bhaal only :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Cernd\"&gt;Cernd&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf Edwin has been turned into a woman as part of his quest :\nIf Edwin has been turned into a woman as part of his quest :\nThrone of Bhaal only :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Dorn\"&gt;Dorn&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf Dorn swore loyalty to a demon:\nIf Edwin has been turned into a woman as part of his quest :\nThrone of Bhaal only, if Dorn swore loyalty to a demon:\nThrone of Bhaal only, if Dorn didn't swear loyalty to a demon:\nWith &lt;a href=\"Haer%27Dalis\"&gt;Haer'Dalis&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf Edwin has been turned into a woman as part of his quest :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Hexxat\"&gt;Hexxat&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf Hexxat is wearing the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Dragomir\"&gt;Cloak of Dragomir&lt;/a&gt; :\nThrone of Bhaal only, if Hexxat is wearing the Cloak of Dragomir :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Imoen\"&gt;Imoen&lt;/a&gt;.\nThrone of Bhaal only :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen in a forest :\nIf Edwin has been turned into a woman as part of his quest :\nIf Edwin has been turned into a woman as part of his quest :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Jan%20Jansen\"&gt;Jan Jansen&lt;/a&gt;.\nThrone of Bhaal only :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Keldorn\"&gt;Keldorn&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf Keldorn stands less than 3 units away from Edwin :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Korgan\"&gt;Korgan&lt;/a&gt;.\nThrone of Bhaal only : \nWith &lt;a href=\"Minsc\"&gt;Minsc&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf Edwin has been turned into a woman as part of his quest :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Nalia\"&gt;Nalia&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf Edwin has been turned into a woman as part of his quest :\nIf Edwin has been turned into a woman as part of his quest :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Neera\"&gt;Neera&lt;/a&gt;.\nThrone of Bhaal only :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Rasaad\"&gt;Rasaad&lt;/a&gt;.\nThrone of Bhaal only :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Valygar\"&gt;Valygar&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter &lt;a href=\"Lavok%20Corthala\"&gt;Lavok&lt;/a&gt;'s death :\nThrone of Bhaal only :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Viconia\"&gt;Viconia&lt;/a&gt;.\nThrone of Bhaal only :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Yoshimo\"&gt;Yoshimo&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf Edwin has been turned into a woman as part of his quest :"}
{"id": "42592", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42592", "title": "Edwin Romance Mod", "text": "It is a Weidu mod for , that allows the player to carry out a romantic relationship with &lt;a href=\"Edwin%20Odesseiron\"&gt;Edwin Odesseiron&lt;/a&gt;, that insulting &lt;a href=\"Red%20Wizards%20of%20Thay\"&gt;Thayvian&lt;/a&gt; wizard wearing red.\nMod author's notes and excerpts.\nIt is also the culmination of a very long project for me (Laufey), and one that would never have been finished without the help of many different people. For more information on that, see the Links below. I had a lot of fun writing this mod - if it gives you, the player, even a fraction of that pleasure, I will be content.\nAn additional optional component for the romance is a new epilogue for romanced and redeemed Viconia, of a less tragic kind than the original one. Note that this will in no way affect the Edwin romance in itself, so if you prefer Viconia's original epilogue, simply bypass this component upon installation.\nViconia.\nViconia's romance epilogue is quite controversial amongst the fandom, who argue there are multiple reasons why it breaks suspension of disbelief (such as the sheer power and mystical options available to two such high-level adventurers).\nIn this unofficial, fan-made epilogue, which only triggers if Viconia's romance is completed, Gorion's Ward convinces her to change her alignment to True Neutral, and Gorion's Ward forsakes godhood; the couple come to a happier ending. Lolth's agents begin trying to assassinate Viconia after the two are wed, and this leads to the two embarking upon an epic quest through the Underdark and the Planes to confront the Demon Queen of Spiders. While what happens remains a secret to the two of them and their friends &amp; family, Lolth's assassination attempts cease. Viconia goes on to bear at least one child to Gorion's Ward, their firstborn being a half-drow daughter who goes on to become a mighty adventurer in her own right.\nMod Links.\n&lt;a href=\"https%3A//github.com/SpellholdStudios/Edwin_Romance\"&gt;Mod readme on the Spellhold Studios Github&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"https%3A//github.com/SpellholdStudios/Edwin_Romance/releases\"&gt;Latest Mod Version Download at Github&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "19985", "revid": "55770344", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19985", "title": "Edwin and Dynaheir", "text": "Edwin and Dynaheir is a companion quest given by &lt;a href=\"Edwin%20Odesseiron\"&gt;Edwin&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt;. Upon speaking to him the first time, he will ask &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; for aid in killing &lt;a href=\"Dynaheir\"&gt;Dynaheir&lt;/a&gt; located in the &lt;a href=\"Gnoll%20Stronghold\"&gt;Gnoll Stronghold&lt;/a&gt;. If the Ward agrees to help him, Edwin will join the party. It is entirely possibly to recruit both Edwin and &lt;a href=\"Minsc\"&gt;Minsc&lt;/a&gt;, and thus have this quest and &lt;a href=\"Rescuing%20Dynaheir\"&gt;Rescuing Dynaheir&lt;/a&gt; active at the same time, but only one of the two can be completed successfully.\nIf Gorion's Ward turns down Edwin's offer, he will leave and cannot be spoken to again.\nThe stronghold itself is home to respawning groups of &lt;a href=\"Gnoll\"&gt;gnolls&lt;/a&gt;. The timer for their respawn is quite short, so you may have to both fight your way in and out. The gnolls have driven whole tree sections (&lt;a href=\"pilings\"&gt;pilings&lt;/a&gt;) of appropriate lengths into the ground to make crude but effective stair steps down into the prisoner pits. &lt;a href=\"Dynaheir\"&gt;Dynaheir&lt;/a&gt; is at 2470, 1400, at the bottom of one of the prison pits. Note that &lt;a href=\"Dynaheir\"&gt;Dynaheir&lt;/a&gt; can't actually be seen without fully descending into the pit, this can be confusing because standing with the party above the pits does give the false impression that the whole pit, including the very bottom, is seen but in fact it isn't. Not reviewing in depth the prison pit can give the impression that &lt;a href=\"Dynaheir\"&gt;Dynaheir&lt;/a&gt; is nowhere to be found. Since she was kept in harsh conditions during her imprisonment, she is below her maximum HP when found.\nEven if you have Edwin in your party when finding Dynaheir, you can still chose if you want to kill her, rescue her or let Edwin and Dynaheir fight each other on their own. If you chose to kill Dynaheir and you have Minsc in your party he too will turn hostile.\nAt the end of the quest you can chose Edwin as a permanent companion or 500 gold pieces.\nIf the party subsequently rescues Dynaheir, a while later Edwin will show up at a random place in the wilderness for a second time to attack the party. His dialogue is different depending on whether Dynaheir is still in the party at the time of the attack.\nWalkthrough.\nBy accepting the quest, a ten-days timer is initiated, after which Edwin will remind Gorion's Ward of the task. If another six days pass without results, Edwin will leave the party to find other \"lackeys\" for it.\nAchievements.\nIn \" there is one achievement that can be earned from this quest:\""}
