{"id": "50303", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50303", "title": "Eilistraee's Song", "text": "Eilistraee's Song is a mod for &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Shadows of Amn&lt;/a&gt; that adds a new &lt;a href=\"world%20map\"&gt;world map&lt;/a&gt; location revolving around Eilistraee \u2013 the good-aligned deity of the &lt;a href=\"drow\"&gt;drow&lt;/a&gt; that rebelled against &lt;a href=\"Lolth\"&gt;Lolth&lt;/a&gt; the Spider Queen. \nOverview.\nThis mod adds a secret encampment of peaceful &lt;a href=\"Drow\"&gt;Drow&lt;/a&gt; who follow the good-aligned goddess Eilistraee, that the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; can visit late in the game.&lt;br&gt;\nThe mod introduces several side quests as well.\nMod initiation and how to get there.\n&lt;a href=\"Solaufein\"&gt;Solaufein&lt;/a&gt; is in the final room of the &lt;a href=\"Cave%20Between%20Underdark%20and%20Exit%20from%20Underdark\"&gt;Cave Between Underdark and Exit from Underdark&lt;/a&gt;. The mod does not initiate dialogue from Solafein, and it is up to the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; to do so. \nIf the party doesn't notice him, they could potentially miss this key encounter to initiate the mod - see screenshot in gallery below for the location.\nUpon exiting the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt; at the start of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;chapter 6&lt;/a&gt;, you'll find that the &lt;a href=\"World%20Map\"&gt;World Map&lt;/a&gt; marks \"Eilistraee's Clearing\".&lt;br&gt;\n\"(Requires that you helped him fake his death and escape during the &lt;a href=\"Inside%20the%20Drow%20City\"&gt;Inside the Drow City&lt;/a&gt; questline in &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%205\"&gt;chapter 5&lt;/a&gt;.)\"\nGallery.\nMod-only provided portraits are smaller and lower resolution. \nExternal links.\n\"(For the mod's main website/forum/download page, see the infobox above.)\""}
{"id": "8253", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8253", "title": "Ekandor", "text": "Ekandor is a &lt;a href=\"Red%20Wizard%20of%20Thay\"&gt;Red Wizard of Thay&lt;/a&gt; from the \"\" whom you first encounter when you meet &lt;a href=\"Neera\"&gt;Neera&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt;. Just after she approaches you, asking for help against \"vicious magic bandits,\" he attacks along with a &lt;a href=\"Thayan%20Wizard\"&gt;Thayan Wizard&lt;/a&gt; and two &lt;a href=\"Thayan%20Bodyguard%20%28Beregost%29\"&gt;Thayan bodyguards&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf you invite &lt;a href=\"Neera\"&gt;Neera&lt;/a&gt; into your party, and keep her long enough to get &lt;a href=\"Neera%20%28quest%29\"&gt;her quest&lt;/a&gt;, you will have a second, and far more deadly, encounter with Ekandor in &lt;a href=\"Adoy%27s%20Enclave\"&gt;Adoy's Enclave&lt;/a&gt;. During the battle, Ekandor will consume his scroll of &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; if his normally cast stoneskin is removed and he has enough time to use the scroll."}
{"id": "9000", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9000", "title": "Elan Garaq", "text": "Elan Garaq is a &lt;a href=\"rakshasa\"&gt;rakshasa&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Black%20Pits\"&gt;The Black Pits&lt;/a&gt;\".\nHe seems to be &lt;a href=\"Baeloth%20Barrityl\"&gt;Baeloth's&lt;/a&gt; right-hand man and participates together with him in the final battle, alongside &lt;a href=\"Thardek\"&gt;Thardek&lt;/a&gt;, the light weapons vendor.\nElan Garaq (store).\nElan has specialized in protective of magical kind. His palette increases with the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt;'s progress throughout the various \"Tiers\" of the arena battles. &lt;a href=\"Item\"&gt;Item&lt;/a&gt;s from earlier Tiers will be still available later and previously purchased ones restocked, with one exception: the &lt;a href=\"Girdle%20of%20Hill%20Giant%20Strength\"&gt;Girdle of Hill Giant Strength&lt;/a&gt; on Tier 2 will be replaced by the &lt;a href=\"Girdle%20of%20Stone%20Giant%20Strength\"&gt;Girdle of Stone Giant Strength&lt;/a&gt; at Tier 3.\nHe sells at 145% of an item's base value and buys far more than only weapons for 30% item value, at a &lt;a href=\"depreciation%20rate\"&gt;depreciation rate&lt;/a&gt; of 5. Prices might be further modified through high &lt;a href=\"charisma\"&gt;charisma&lt;/a&gt; or an other-than-average &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is not possible to steal from his store."}
