{"id": "32871", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32871", "title": "Electrical damage", "text": ""}
{"id": "32688", "revid": "5653418", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32688", "title": "Electricity damage", "text": "Electricity damage is one of the 10 main &lt;a href=\"Damage\"&gt;damage types&lt;/a&gt; of the game, typically inflicted by spells or on-hit effects caused by weapons like the &lt;a href=\"Flail%20of%20Ages\"&gt;Flail of Ages&lt;/a&gt;. A weapon would cause &lt;a href=\"Physical%20damage\"&gt;Physical damage&lt;/a&gt; provided it goes through &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt;, and then an additional effect could add elemental damage.\nProtection from electricity.\nThrough the use of certain spells, items or abilities, it is possible to reduce the amount of damage, afflicted by electricity.\nSpells.\n&lt;a href=\"Spells\"&gt;Spells&lt;/a&gt; usually offer only temporary protection from electricity, in varying degrees.\n\u2026 incomplete!\nItems.\n&lt;a href=\"Item\"&gt;Item&lt;/a&gt;s, as long as equipped, offer a constant protection from electricity. By wearing more than one of these, 100% resistance or even more is quite possible. Consumable items only give temporary protection.\nShields.\n\u2026 incomplete!\nAbilities.\nThere are a few that can offer temporary or constant protection from electricity.\n\u2026 incomplete!\nDamage from electricity.\nMany spells are based on electricity, as well as some abilities, and items may deal bonus or even pure electricity damage.\nSpells.\n\u2026 incomplete!\nItems.\n\u2026 incomplete!\nAbilities.\n\u2026 incomplete!\nCreatures, protected from electricity.\nSome have a natural resistance against electricity damage, some have special &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt;s equipped that protect them.\nCreatures, dealing electricity damage.\nThere's is a number of that always or by will are able to deal electricity damage, either naturally, via spells or through special &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt;s in their &lt;a href=\"Inventory\"&gt;equipment&lt;/a&gt;.\n\u2026 incomplete!"}
