{"id": "23763", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23763", "title": "Elemental", "text": ""}
{"id": "49489", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49489", "title": "Elemental Lich (Bridge District)", "text": "The Elemental Lich is a powerful &lt;a href=\"Lich\"&gt;Lich&lt;/a&gt; entombed in the cellar of his &lt;a href=\"House%20of%20the%20Elemental%20Lich\"&gt;house&lt;/a&gt; which is located in the Athkatla &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt;. This Lich may be encountered as part the &lt;a href=\"Restore%20Kangaxx%27s%20body\"&gt;Restore Kangaxx's body&lt;/a&gt; questline. The Elemental Lich guards body parts of &lt;a href=\"Kangaxx\"&gt;Kangaxx&lt;/a&gt;, which are stored within the sarcophagus. If a player interacts with the sarcophagus and attempts to open it, the Elemental Lich will rise from the Crypt Floor, and regardless of anything the party may say - eventually turn hostile. It will attempt to destroy you, the would-be Crypt robbers. The name \"Elemental Lich\" is derived by the fact that no name is mentioned directly as to this creature's actual name, however the game combat screen identifies it as the Elemental Lich. \nElemental Lich abilities.\nThis lich is equipped with three undroppable items which bestow the creature's immunities and protections, and its melee touch attack. These are:\n&lt;a href=\"RING95.ITM\"&gt;RING95.ITM&lt;/a&gt; for the general Undead protections. See the item link for specifics.\n&lt;a href=\"LICH.ITM\"&gt;LICH.ITM&lt;/a&gt; for lich specific protections. See the item link for specifics.\n&lt;a href=\"LICH02.ITM\"&gt;LICH02.ITM&lt;/a&gt; for the touch attack melee weapon. See the item link for specifics.\nMod content.\nInstallation of &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod will improve the Elemental Lich's AI noticeably over the basic and unmodified EE versions of the creature. If the SCS Smarter Mages component is also installed, this Lich will be even more formidable, in that it will utilize triggers, sequencers and contingency abilities. This component also works with the game difficulty settings, and this could mean that a Lich will also have access, and use, Mage &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt;. \nSCS makes the Elemental Lich a Level 30 Invoker (it could also be an enchanter, conjurer or necromancer - depends on the installation variable) - and uses a custom designed Lich Invoker AI script. It is immune to &lt;a href=\"Silence\"&gt;Silence&lt;/a&gt; effects, plus all the one's in the unmodified creature.\nAs soon as hostilities are initiated, an uninterruptable series of protective buffs will be deployed as \"previously cast\" and a spell trigger and or contingency that will basically make the lich invulnerable to most damage types including magical damage, and 75% protected from acid. It will also be protected from magical weapons. \nIn fact, the following spells will be implemented as buffs on the Lich: &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Blades%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Energy Blades (wizard)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt; (or \"Greater Spell Deflection\" with &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;SR&lt;/a&gt;), &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20The%20Elements\"&gt;Protection From The Elements&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity Divination&lt;/a&gt; (or \"Dispelling Screen\" with &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;SR&lt;/a&gt;), &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magic%20Energy\"&gt;Protection From Magic Energy&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt; and \"Mind Blank\" with &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;SR&lt;/a&gt;. \nA few seconds later while invisible, an instant application of &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt; takes place. At this moment the Lich will be protected being struck and nearly immune to elemental and magical damage - and can't be targeted at all. This will give it time to attempt a Remove Magic on the party or perhaps go directly to a Time Stop.\nWhen a Timestop is cast, during the pause will be cast other spells, and perhaps even a Spell Trigger during the interval. As the lich is an invoker, expect heavy use of damage dealing evocation spells. The party will have a -2 on saving throws against these (unless the party member is also an Invoker). The lich will attack with &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Blades%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Energy Blades (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; in between spell casts at point blank and missile range. All spells listed in the paragraph below are scripted for use and variably selected based on vulnerability assessments and available detected targets.\nMany different memorized spells are assigned, and all can be used by the AI. Examples include (not all are listed): &lt;a href=\"Shield\"&gt;Shield&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hands\"&gt;Burning Hands&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chromatic%20Orb\"&gt;Chromatic Orb&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missile\"&gt;Magic Missile&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Shocking%20Grasp\"&gt;Shocking Grasp&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Vocalize\"&gt;Vocalize&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;Lightning Bolt&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Thrust\"&gt;Spell Thrust&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Storm\"&gt;Ice Storm&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Invisibility\"&gt;Improved Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Malison\"&gt;Greater Malison&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Cloudkill\"&gt;Cloudkill&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cone%20of%20Cold\"&gt;Cone of Cold&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Shield\"&gt;Spell Shield&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Disintegrate\"&gt;Disintegrate&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Lightning\"&gt;Chain Lightning&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magic%20Energy\"&gt;Protection From Magic Energy&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"True%20Seeing\"&gt;True Seeing&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Delayed%20Blast%20Fireball\"&gt;Delayed Blast Fireball&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Khelben%27s%20Warding%20Whip\"&gt;Khelben's Warding Whip&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mordenkainen%27s%20Sword\"&gt;Mordenkainen's Sword&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20The%20Elements\"&gt;Protection From The Elements&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bigby%27s%20Crushing%20Hand\"&gt;Bigby's Crushing Hand&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Incendiary%20Cloud\"&gt;Incendiary Cloud&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Meteor%20Swarm\"&gt;Meteor Swarm&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spellstrike\"&gt;Spellstrike&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Wish\"&gt;Wish&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn addition, Mage HLA's are available, including &lt;a href=\"Comet\"&gt;Comet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Breath%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Dragon's Breath (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Blades%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Energy Blades (wizard)&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Alacrity\"&gt;Improved Alacrity&lt;/a&gt;. \nAll SCS liches can see invisible creatures, and this cannot be blocked or dispelled. \nThis creature will employ a \"Fear Aura\" ability, an innate power they may use with a fairly large area of effect. A saving throw negates, but it is unaffected by spell level protections and magic resistance. It causes a &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; effect and lasts a turn. The aura tics continuously every two rounds.\nIf the SCS \"More Consistent Breach\" component is installed, a level 5 &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; Spell can target a Lich, which it cannot in an unmodified game. However, SCS changes Breach to be blocked by all of the Spell Protection options such as Spell Shield, Spell Deflection, Spell Turning and Spell Trap.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod installation will change the creature's spells to the SR versions."}
{"id": "46530", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46530", "title": "Elemental Lich (Watcher's Keep)", "text": "This Elemental Lich can be encountered in and games on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Final%20Seal\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Final Seal&lt;/a&gt; dungeon, when operating the &lt;a href=\"Globe%20Machine\"&gt;Globe Machine&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nAfter the party presses the purple button on the Globe Machine and receives the fourth &lt;a href=\"Purple%20Globe\"&gt;Purple Globe&lt;/a&gt; - this lich spawns (along with a &lt;a href=\"Lich%20%28Purple%20Globe%204%29\"&gt;second lich&lt;/a&gt;) over at the eastern side of the chamber.\nThis undead mage will appear and initially deploy protection buffs, and if damaged in some manner will further protect himself with a contingency.\nAfterwards, if able, he will cast spells as noted under the conditions listed in the InfoBox.\nThis lich is unable to remove buffs or spell protections from the party - use that to advantage.\nThis lich is immune to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt;, can &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;, and will be ignored by summoned/gated fiends. \nIt is curious how the base game's script for this lich applies fire resistance and protection from evil on the creature, who is already immune to fire damage, and cannot be targeted by demons/devils innately.\nThe lich has a unique touch attack, that can induce a &lt;a href=\"Slay\"&gt;Slay&lt;/a&gt; effect - if the saving throw is missed, there is a 6 second delay before death takes hold, during that time the character will render a portrait icon displaying \"Dying\".\nWhen he is defeated, the lich's corpse remains on the ground, but no loot is discovered.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some revisions to this creature.\nFirst, SCS raises the lich's Experience level to 30, and will randomly assign a specialty kit at installation, either Conjurer, Enchanter, Invoker or Necromancer.\nThe creature's &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; scores are adjusted to reflect the higher experience level.\nThe assigned kit will determine which AI script is used by the lich, and influence available spell choices, prepared &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trigger\"&gt;Spell Trigger&lt;/a&gt;.\nExpect a more robust and rapid initial protective buff chain at the start of the encounter, making the lich more difficult to destroy or disrupt at the battle's start.\nNumerous AI recognition scripts are used to determine when and how to try and dispel/remove protections from the party using &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Thrust\"&gt;Spell Thrust&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Khelben%27s%20Warding%20Whip\"&gt;Khelben's Warding Whip&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ruby%20Ray%20of%20Reversal\"&gt;Ruby Ray of Reversal&lt;/a&gt;.\nA wide variety of spells are retained by the lich, perhaps including &lt;a href=\"Bigby%27s%20Clenched%20Fist\"&gt;Bigby's Clenched Fist&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bigby%27s%20Crushing%20Hand\"&gt;Bigby's Crushing Hand&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Wish\"&gt;Wish&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe player's selected game difficulty setting and install options may mean this lich will have use of several &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class abilities&lt;/a&gt;, such as &lt;a href=\"Comet\"&gt;Comet&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Breath%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Dragon's Breath (spell)&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Blades%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Energy Blades (wizard)&lt;/a&gt;, depending on which kit the mage has.\nIf the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod or the &lt;a href=\"IWDification\"&gt;IWDification&lt;/a&gt; mods are installed with SCS, the lich will have some of those mod's spell choices included in lich's spell casting scripts."}
{"id": "40651", "revid": "26939652", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40651", "title": "Elemental Plane of Earth", "text": "The Elemental Plane of Earth is a vast collection of solid matter, constantly in motion marked by tremors and violent earth quakes. It's original inhabitants are the &lt;a href=\"Earth%20Elemental\"&gt;Earth Elemental&lt;/a&gt;s and over time more creatures sought their home there, including &lt;a href=\"Dwarf\"&gt;Dwarf&lt;/a&gt;s (attracted by the rich deposits of metals and minerals), salt and stone and the lead by Great Kahn &lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Aforgottenrealms%3AKabril%20Ali%20al-Sara%20al-Zalazil\"&gt;Kabril Ali al-Sara al-Zalazil&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "11907", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11907", "title": "Elemental Plane of Fire", "text": "The Elemental Plane of Fire is an endless landscape of volcanoes, vast oceans of lava, impassable fields of magma and wastelands of super-heated obsidian. It is the home of &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Elemental\"&gt;fire elementals&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"salamander\"&gt;salamander&lt;/a&gt;s, and is ruled by the Grand Sultan of All the &lt;a href=\"Efreet\"&gt;Efreet&lt;/a&gt;, Marrake al-Sidan al-Hariq ben Lazan, from his palace in the City of Brass."}
{"id": "4770", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4770", "title": "Elemental Summoning", "text": "Elemental Summoning is a &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; usable by &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"druid\"&gt;druid&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"shaman\"&gt;shaman&lt;/a&gt;.\nRequired for: &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Elemental%20Summoning\"&gt;Greater Elemental Summoning&lt;/a&gt; (Druid only)\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has replaced \"Elemental Summoning\" with \"Elemental Swarm\". See below for description:\nElemental Swarm\nLevel: Quest\nSchool: Conjuration\nSphere: Elemental, Summoning\nRange: Long\nDuration: 2 turns\nCasting Time: 1 round\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nDrawing power from the environment, this spell summons a 12HD elemental from each of the three Planes of Earth, Air, and Fire. The elementals will do the bidding of the caster until they are slain or the duration of the spell runs out."}
{"id": "16718", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16718", "title": "Elemental Transformation (Earth)", "text": "Elemental Transformation (Earth) is a &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; available to &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druids&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffects.\nUnlimited duration\nSets base AC to -5 (can be enhanced by regular AC-enhancing equipment like helmets, shields, cloaks, rings, including specific slashing/crushing/piercing/missile modifiers of equipped armor, eg -3 slash AC from the Red Dragon Scale, and those of belts)\nSets base thac0 to 2 (base, so before strength and other bonuses apply)\nSets strength to 20 and dex to 14 (can be modified by buffs or equipping a girdle after transforming)\nSets base attacks per round to 2 (can be enhanced further by being a fighter dual/multi and also by equipping the Gauntlets of Extraordinary Specialization, also by being hasted or improved hasted)\nDamage: 2d10 crushing + strength bonuses.\nNo additional physical or elemental resistances\nImmunity against normal weapons\nAttacks count as +4 enchantment for the purpose of what creatures you can hit.\nIn the Enhanced Edition, shield work as normal (if equipped before transforming) and weapons provide both bonuses (eg +1 APR from Belm) and charge abilities (eg 1x/day Summon Spectral Blade from the Spectral Brand), but the offhand weapon bonuses will only apply after saving the game and then reloading. While in this form, the character will benefit from Sword and Shield Style while equipped with a shield, Single Weapon Style while the offhand is empty and no weapon style at all while equipped with an offhand weapon. \nIn the original games, they'll work as if you're dual wielding the elemental's fist and the weapon and, as such, dual wielding style bonuses (and penalties) will apply."}
{"id": "16719", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16719", "title": "Elemental Transformation (Fire)", "text": "Fire Elemental Transformation is a &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; available to &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druids&lt;/a&gt;.\nUnlimited duration\nSets base AC to -5 (can be enhanced by regular AC-enhancing equipment like helmets, shields, cloaks, rings, including specific slashing/crushing/piercing/missile modifiers of equipped armor, eg -3 slash AC from the Red Dragon Scale, and those of belts)\nSets base thac0 to 2 (base, so before strength and other bonuses apply)\nSets strength to 23 and dexterity to 14 (can be modified by buffs)\nUnlike Elemental Transformation (Earth), this form does not affect your attacks per round.\nDamage: 1d10 crushing + strength bonuses + 1d10 fire damage (bypasses magic resistance).\nSets fire resistance to 100% (which can be further enhanced by equipment or by simply levelling as a druid, reaching 127% at druid level 24, meaning that 27% of fire damage will heal you)\nImmunity against normal weapons\nAttacks count as +4 enchantment for the purpose of what creatures you can hit.\nIn the Enhanced Edition, shield work as normal (if equipped before transforming) and weapons provide both bonuses (eg +1 APR from Belm) and charge abilities (eg 1x/day Summon Spectral Blade from the Spectral Brand), but the offhand weapon bonuses will only apply after saving the game and then reloading. While in this form, the character will benefit from Sword and Shield Style while equipped with a shield, Single Weapon Style while the offhand is empty and no weapon style at all while equipped with an offhand weapon.\nIn the original games, they'll work as if you're dual wielding the elemental's fist and the weapon and, as such, dual wielding style bonuses (and penalties) will apply."}
{"id": "32659", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32659", "title": "Elemental damage", "text": "&lt;onlyinclude&gt;Elemental damage usually is caused by &lt;a href=\"spells\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt; or as bonus damage from &lt;a href=\"weapons\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt; on top of their &lt;a href=\"physical%20damage\"&gt;physical damage&lt;/a&gt;. The game implements damage types connected to the four major elemental planes plus one of the four para-elemental ones:\nA &lt;a href=\"creature\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt; may be &lt;a href=\"Resistances\"&gt;resistant&lt;/a&gt; or even to one or more of these. It should be noted that &lt;a href=\"Magical%20damage\"&gt;Magical damage&lt;/a&gt; behaves the same, but is not listed here since it is not elemental. It should also be noted that Poison damage is really not treated as an elemental damage by the game engine in any consistent way. For instance, the 7th Level arcane spell &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20The%20Elements\"&gt;Protection From The Elements&lt;/a&gt; excludes poison damage, and the 8th level arcane spell &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Energy\"&gt;Protection From Energy&lt;/a&gt; also does not add poison damage as an \"energy type\". For most intents and purposes, Poison Damage is a stand-alone damage type in the game. Disease effects that deal damage, use Poison Damage as the type.\nIn the original game, elemental hits could interrupt spellcasting even with 100% or more resistance (immunity). This has been changed in the Enhanced Editions."}
