{"id": "8080", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8080", "title": "Eler Had", "text": "Eler Had is a human thief, with a berserker kit. He supports &lt;a href=\"Gromnir%20Il-Khan\"&gt;Gromnir Il-Khan&lt;/a&gt; as an ally, turning up at the outset of battle in &lt;a href=\"Gromnir%27s%20Hideout\"&gt;Gromnir's Hideout&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe thief uses potions of invisibility to achieve &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt; opportunities. This can be attempted at least three times. The AI script prioritizes Mage class as targets before other classes.\nAt a predetermined threshold the rogue will quaff healing potions to self-heal damage incurred.\nThe backstabber moves quickly with the rare leather &lt;a href=\"Grandmaster%27s%20Armor\"&gt;Grandmaster's Armor&lt;/a&gt; worn.\nMod content.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Ascension\"&gt;Ascension&lt;/a&gt; mod some revisions are made to this rogue, mostly to enhance its powers and abilities.\nCombined with the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod, an excellent overhaul to the AI and Ascension scripts is made. Using both mods together will improve the challenge and ensure scripts and compatibility with the EE game are realized. \nThe thief is now a half-elf. The rogue receives some new weaponry and equipment. The thief also gets a boosted dexterity to 19 and intelligence to 14. Eler also has it's 'illegal' 18/50 strength changed to 17, and hit points are adjusted to 125 for a thief class. This rogue also has 100% &lt;a href=\"Magical%20damage\"&gt;Magical damage&lt;/a&gt; resistance, and in addition to the 200% movement rate provided by the Grandmaster's Armor, is given an extra +3 movement modifier on top of that. Eler begins combat with a use of &lt;a href=\"Enrage\"&gt;Enrage&lt;/a&gt;, and later can attempt two &lt;a href=\"Assassination\"&gt;Assassination&lt;/a&gt; innate abilities for use.\nThree pips in Dagger proficiency are provided. The thief also uses a &lt;a href=\"Buckler%20%2B1\"&gt;Buckler +1&lt;/a&gt; in the shield hand, and a mod-only undroppable weapon known as \"Soultaker\" Dagger. Eler will also flick &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20Throwing%20Dagger\"&gt;Poisoned Throwing Dagger&lt;/a&gt; attacks for ranged combat.\nThe Soultaker dagger is a unique weapon that is non-magical but is coated in a nasty alchemical compound that upon a hit requires a save vs death or be poisoned for 10 seconds and inflicting 2 damage per second. A strike also causes a no save slow effect lasting only a few seconds. However - it's amazing power is that a hit target will be suffer a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; effect and a &lt;a href=\"Spellstrike\"&gt;Spellstrike&lt;/a&gt; effect combination. Those effects bypass magic resistance.\nEler has an innate &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; spell that can be cast in 2 seconds on self and can be done four times. This may help to facilitate repeated backstabs."}
{"id": "6906", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6906", "title": "Elf", "text": "Elves are generally considered one of the most beautiful races. They are slightly shorter and more delicate than humans and are not as hardy. Elves are a rare sight on the sword coast perhaps because they prefer the wild to human cities. While they are well known as a cheerful and frolicsome race, many elves, especially drow, are as surly as &lt;a href=\"Dwarf\"&gt;dwarves&lt;/a&gt; or as prideful as &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;s.\nThere are many racial divisions of elves: Gold elves, drow (aka dark elves), moon elves, sea elves, wild elves, and winged elves (aka avariel). Elves are generally liked and even admired by &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;s and are easily accepted into their society. The same cannot be said for &lt;a href=\"Dwarf\"&gt;dwarves&lt;/a&gt; some of whom despise elves on principle.\nSubraces.\nDrow.\n&lt;a href=\"Drow\"&gt;Drow&lt;/a&gt; are a subterranean race of elves. They have dark grayish skin and are significantly different than surface elves in culture and attitude. Drow society is matriarchal, and drow women tend to view men of any race as inferior and weak to the point of misandry. Drow of either gender are stigmatized as evil by most non-Drow throughout Faer\u00fbn.\nAvariel.\nAvariel (or winged elves) have feathered wings and are capable of flight. They are more delicate than their earth-bound cousins, with hollow bones to aid their flight. They have pale skin and slightly larger than normal eyes.\nAvariel are said to have the most beautiful voices of all the elves. This makes them highly sought after by &lt;a href=\"bard\"&gt;bard&lt;/a&gt;s. \n&lt;a href=\"Aerie\"&gt;Aerie&lt;/a&gt; is the only known avariel in the .\nClasses.\nAccessible Classes.\n&lt;a href=\"Barbarian\"&gt;Barbarian&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cleric\"&gt;Cleric&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fighter\"&gt;Fighter&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href=\"Specialist%20Mage\"&gt;Diviner&lt;/a&gt;, Enchanter, &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Mage\"&gt;Wild Mage&lt;/a&gt; specializations), &lt;a href=\"Ranger\"&gt;Ranger&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer\"&gt;Sorcerer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;Thief&lt;/a&gt;\nAccessible Multi-Classes.\n&lt;a href=\"Fighter%20/%20Thief\"&gt;Fighter / Thief&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fighter%20/%20Mage\"&gt;Fighter / Mage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mage%20/%20Thief\"&gt;Mage / Thief&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fighter%20/%20Mage%20/%20Thief\"&gt;Fighter / Mage/ Thief&lt;/a&gt;\nElf is an excellent race to choose when playing a ranged character. Their ability to get 19 Dex allows them to get an extra +1 ranged THAC0 at character creation, which stacks with their Bow bonus. They also make great thieves for the same reasons, good rangers. They are initially disadvantaged as fighters due to their constitution penalty but it is possible to create an elf character who can hold their own in a melee.\nThe penalty can be compensated for and may not matter by game's end if you are willing to stack both the &lt;a href=\"Manual%20of%20Bodily%20Health\"&gt;Manual of Bodily Health&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate (game)&lt;/a&gt; and the +1 Constitution bonus from the &lt;a href=\"Machine%20of%20Lum%20the%20Mad\"&gt;Machine of Lum the Mad&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt; on the same elf. If you also use the &lt;a href=\"Manual%20of%20Quickness%20of%20Action\"&gt;Manual of Quickness of Action&lt;/a&gt; and use the Dexterity upgrade from the Machine, you'll have 21 Dexterity. This provides -1 bonus &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt; and better ranged THAC0 than any other race (save for &lt;a href=\"Halfling\"&gt;Halfling&lt;/a&gt;s). The extra THAC0 bonus with Bows and Swords helps should you choose to use those weapons. The manual suggests these bonuses are only obtained with &lt;a href=\"longbows\"&gt;longbows&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"long%20swords\"&gt;long swords&lt;/a&gt;, but in fact, they apply to all bows and all swords.\nElves also make great thieves, unkitted mages, sorcerers and wild mages, as those classes stop gaining any bonuses from constitution after 16 points (so elves are not disadvantaged in terms of HPs).\nThe mage specializations available to elves however are not that good. Diviners are barred from casting , while Enchanters are barred from which contains 90% of all direct damage incantations.\nRelated items.\nItem better for Elves:\n&lt;a href=\"Savage%20Shortbow\"&gt;Savage Shortbow&lt;/a&gt; "}
{"id": "5638", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5638", "title": "Elfsong Tavern", "text": "The Elfsong Tavern is an inn in &lt;a href=\"East%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;East Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe inn provides rooms and drinks but no other services.\nReputation trap.\nIf you have a reputation lower than 3 you will be ambushed by a group of three &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Enforcer%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23FLAMPUN\"&gt;Flaming Fist Enforcers&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Scout\"&gt;Flaming Fist Scout&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Battle%20Wizard\"&gt;Flaming Fist Battle Wizard&lt;/a&gt; once you enter.\nTrivia.\nAccording the proprietor, the Elfsong Inn used to be haunted by a ghost mourning her lost love, but the ghost, sometimes called \"The Lady\", has stopped appearing since the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Crisis\"&gt;Iron Crisis&lt;/a&gt; began."}
{"id": "52151", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52151", "title": "Elfsong Tavern (SoD)", "text": "The Elfsong Tavern is an in \"\".\nExterior.\nThe street in between this establishment and &lt;a href=\"Sorcerous%20Sundries%20%28SoD%29\"&gt;Sorcerous Sundries (SoD)&lt;/a&gt; is thronged with refugees as well as residents. An unwary person might be surprised by &lt;a href=\"Zelma\"&gt;pickpockets&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Rabble-Rousers\"&gt;be part of an altercation between guards and newcomers&lt;/a&gt;, or stop to use the financial services of &lt;a href=\"Senna\"&gt;Senna&lt;/a&gt;.\nGround floor.\nThe inn's bartender provides drinks but no other services and the bard &lt;a href=\"Garrick\"&gt;Garrick&lt;/a&gt; alternates between attempts to sing and woo the tavern's uninterested owner, \"Lady\" &lt;a href=\"Alyth%20Elendara\"&gt;Alyth Elendara&lt;/a&gt;.\nThose with the right enhanced vision may see the outline of &lt;a href=\"Al-Alai\"&gt;Al-Alai&lt;/a&gt; the elemental, who will not be pleased to be disturbed.\nIn the back room, &lt;a href=\"Irina\"&gt;Irina&lt;/a&gt; worries over the depletion of their ruby wine stock and awaits a hero to save them.\nSecond Floor.\nPassing up the steps, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; will be just in time to watch the end of a lover's spat between &lt;a href=\"Coran\"&gt;Coran&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Safana\"&gt;Safana&lt;/a&gt;, of which he will beg off any offer of companionship and she gladly accept.\nIn a dark storeroom lies a locked chest full of recently arrived &lt;a href=\"supplies\"&gt;supplies&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "6313", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6313", "title": "Elhan", "text": "Elhan is the commander of the elven forces defending the Underdark exit area, and what's left of the forces outside of &lt;a href=\"Suldanessellar\"&gt;Suldanessellar&lt;/a&gt; since its \"disappearance\".\nGameplay.\nAfter escaping the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt;, several elves will take &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and the party to see an elven general - and finally Elhan. \nA series of probing questions will be asked, and answers given by the party will be assessed for veracity by elven sages who are skilled at analyzing truthful responses and identifying deceit.\nMost likely, even if the party is giving sarcastic or begrudging responses, Elhan will have decided that the party is not an enemy of the elves, but rather seeking &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;Jon Irenicus&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Viconia%20DeVir\"&gt;Viconia DeVir&lt;/a&gt; is a party companion, there will be special dialogue presented and possibly a geas spell cast upon her in order to permit her to stay in the party. After all, the surface elves really do not trust the drow.\nAfter much back and forth - Elhan will make it understood that to find Jon Irenicus, the city of Suldaessalar must be exposed from its magical hiding. This can only be accomplished by using the &lt;a href=\"Rhynn%20Lanthorn\"&gt;Rhynn Lanthorn&lt;/a&gt; device. Elhan has a pretty good idea that &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; has made off with it and fled the area.\nThe party is to continue tracking down and destroy Bodhi, and wrest the Lanthorn from her, and return it to Elhan. This is not optional and is required to continue the saga, although there is no timer limit placed on this task.\nHe will also furnish the party with &lt;a href=\"Elven%20Holy%20Water\"&gt;elven holy water&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Wooden%20Stake\"&gt;wooden stakes&lt;/a&gt; to help with the task.\nElhan can spare no warriors to help the party and explains that the elves will not invade any areas outside of their territory. He advises that previous contacts of the party should be able to assist if needed.\nThe party's journal updates and records &lt;a href=\"The%20Elven%20City%20Requires%20My%20Aid\"&gt;The Elven City Requires My Aid&lt;/a&gt; questline.\nNote that for plot purposes, Elhan can't be killed (as evidenced by his &lt;a href=\"MINHP1.ITM\"&gt;MINHP1.ITM&lt;/a&gt;). It is pointless to attack the elves in this scenario, and frankly will gum up your ultimate game saga, so don't try it. There's plenty of opportunity for violent release ahead in the rest of the game.\nNote about the geas.\nThis geas accepted by Viconia seems not to actually implement anything specific in the game. It is more of a theatrical plot convention. However, if the party attacks any of the elves in this area, including Elhan, the PC will be killed by a scripted plot function, and it will be game over.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"https%3A//github.com/RoxanneSHS/LensHunt\"&gt;Broken Lanthorn&lt;/a&gt; mod will initiate when the party returns to speak with Elhan after the party has recovered the Rhynn Lanthorn."}
{"id": "55093", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55093", "title": "Elhan - Suldanessellar", "text": "Elhan is the commander of the elven defenders inside the invaded city of &lt;a href=\"Suldanessellar\"&gt;Suldanessellar&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThis page is for the new creature file for Elhan as he appears in the elven city at the start of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%207\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 7&lt;/a&gt;.\nElhan has already used the &lt;a href=\"Rhynn%20Lanthorn\"&gt;Rhynn Lanthorn&lt;/a&gt; to reveal the entrance to the city from Irenicus powerful illusionary magic. Elhan entered the gate, and before doing so bade the party to follow when ready.\nWhen the party transition from the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Tethir%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;Forest of Tethir (Shadows of Amn)&lt;/a&gt; to the elven city a cut scene animation plays about the invaded city - and then Elhan addresses the party with a status report and objectives.\nElhan gives orders to his \"Elite War Guards\" to go forth and take up positions in the city. He and remains stationed in this area to receive any elves in the city who are shepherded here for safety, protection and healing.\nIt is the party's job to venture within and help the various elves still fighting in the city to defeat Irenicus's invaders. Elhan says it is a priority to ensure any remaining civilian elves are not killed during the carnage.\nHe also makes it clear that finding queen &lt;a href=\"Ellesime\"&gt;Ellesime&lt;/a&gt; is necessary in order to plan a way to defeat Irenicus. She'll know what to do.\nDuring various stages of the player's progress, the party can visit Elhan and get his reaction, commentary and maybe even advice or words of encouragement."}
{"id": "50237", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50237", "title": "Elite Fire Giant", "text": "Elite Fire Giant is found in &lt;a href=\"Yaga-Shura%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Yaga-Shura's Keep&lt;/a&gt;. Several of these Giants will attempt to crush you if you enter the Keep. \nDescription.\nThese hard-hitting creatures wield an undroppable Battle Axe (GIAFIR.ITM), which is a +3 enchanted weapon with a speed factor of 5 and a reach of 2 (same as a halberd). It gives the giant a +3 THAC0 bonus, deals 2d12 slashing damage and 1d12 fire damage on any successful strike. With the creature's axe proficiency and strength bonus it will deal an extra +13 damage and an extra +4 to hit. Note that these Giants have a penalty of -4 to hit Dwarves, Gnomes and Halflings (the \"shorty\" races\"). The adjusted Attacks per Round (APR) for the giant is 2.5.\nThe Elite Fire Giant is healed by fire damage. The AI script will utilize carried potions depending on script timers and availability in the inventory. Typically, one will be consumed within 1 round of hostilities, such as the oil of speed. Healing potions are used based on incurred damage percent and situational triggers.\nGameplay.\nThe Elite Fire Giant will move toward a detected enemy and quickly consume one potion from its inventory (might be the Oil of Speed, or the Potion of Invulnerability). Once in weapon range it will engage in melee combat with its special Battle Axe. Expect it to hit frequently if your only protection is Armor Class rating. Although the creature is a Berserker class, in the unmodified game it does not use the &lt;a href=\"Enrage\"&gt;Enrage&lt;/a&gt; ability, as it wasn't added to the script. See Mod content below for how the creature can use its innate abilities and HLA's.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod Improves Yaga Shura's Keep and all creature's within and without as a whole. Along with the changes, Elite Fire Giants are also improved and enhanced. The creature will use potions as with the original giant. Some mod changes are:"}
