{"id": "23698", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23698", "title": "Elminster Aumar", "text": "Elminster Aumar, also known as the Sage of Shadowdale, is one of the most famous and powerful wizards in all of &lt;a href=\"Faer%C3%BBn\"&gt;Faer\u00fbn&lt;/a&gt;, a fair fighter and thief, and a founding member of the &lt;a href=\"Harpers\"&gt;Harpers&lt;/a&gt;. He is also the &lt;a href=\"chosen\"&gt;chosen&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Mystra\"&gt;Mystra&lt;/a&gt;, goddess of magic, which grants him extended longevity and magic prowess.\n\"Baldur's Gate\".\nQuotes.\n\"Ho there wanderer, stay thy course a while and indulge an old man\"\n\"Baldur's Gate II\".\nSpell books.\nElminster has a lot of spells memorized when appearing during \"Baldur's Gate II\". Really \u2013 a lot. And each of them three times, if not stated otherwise."}
{"id": "27438", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27438", "title": "Elven", "text": ""}
{"id": "55090", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55090", "title": "Elven Archer", "text": "Elven Archer is an elven male fighter class encountered in the battle for &lt;a href=\"Suldanessellar\"&gt;Suldanessellar&lt;/a&gt;, usually on the pathways and outside buildings.\nGameplay.\nThere are several of these \"Elven Archer\" creatures that will be spawned on the map. They are created along with a few &lt;a href=\"Elven%20Warrior%20%28Suldanessellar%29\"&gt;Elven Warriors&lt;/a&gt; when a party member crosses a hidden proximity trigger on the area map.\nThe player can't control these elves, nor give them orders.\nOccasionally some of the elves will show shouts and battle cries displayed on the player's text screen.\nThe archers have no dialogue and can't be spoken to.\nThe purpose of these elves is to add some realism for the story that the elves are in battle with Irenicus's forces, as they defend the city and try and stave off the various intruders.\nIn reality, they aren't meant to actually defeat anything in the city on their own, or somehow come to the rescue of the party. If the player wants to kill a troll, or a rakshasa, or a golem, these elves can't do it on their own. They can't even hit a golem or rakshasa with their normal arrows, nor kill a troll since they have no fire or acid attack.\nThey will actually fire a few arrows if they see an enemy creature.\nIf any of the warriors/archers are killed, they drop a bit of equipment. Accidentally, or even on purpose, the player can kill any of these elves. There are no repercussions other than for role play reasons."}
{"id": "55091", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55091", "title": "Elven Battle Mage", "text": "Elven Battle Mage is an elven male mage class encountered in the battle for &lt;a href=\"Suldanessellar\"&gt;Suldanessellar&lt;/a&gt;, usually on the pathways and outside buildings.\nGameplay.\nThere are several of these \"Elven Battle Mage\" creatures that will be spawned on the map. They are created when a party member crosses a hidden proximity trigger on the area map. A few of these mages are also prepositioned on the map with &lt;a href=\"Elhan\"&gt;Elhan&lt;/a&gt; at the beginning of the Chapter 7 introduction to basically act out a little scene where they are sent ahead to hunt for the enemy and cast a few buffs on themselves (they eventually disappear off the map) - just a little bit of plot animation.\nThe player can't control these elves, nor give them orders.\nOccasionally some of the elves will show shouts and battle cries displayed on the player's text screen.\nThe mages have no dialogue and can't be spoken to.\nThe purpose of these elves is to add some realism for the story that the elves are in battle with Irenicus's forces, as they defend the city and try and stave off the various intruders.\nIn reality, they aren't meant to actually defeat anything in the city on their own, or somehow come to the rescue of the party. In some cases the mages will cast both real spells as well as \"phony spells\" to simulate magic preparations or attacks. As this theatrical animation occurs mostly versus the rakshasa enemies in the city, none of their actual attack spells can affect these creatures at all due to their immunities to spells between level 1-7.\nThe exception to this is that the battle mage can actually kill a troll if thy use &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Arrow\"&gt;Flame Arrow&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hands\"&gt;Burning Hands&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Agannazar%27s%20Scorcher\"&gt;Agannazar's Scorcher&lt;/a&gt; - which they can do by script.\nIf any of the battle mages are killed, they drop no of equipment. Accidentally, or even on purpose, the player can kill any of these mages. There are no repercussions other than for role play reasons."}
{"id": "5308", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5308", "title": "Elven Chain +1", "text": "Elven Chain +1 is a set of light magical armor, very similar in appearance to &lt;a href=\"Elven%20Chain%20Mail\"&gt;Elven Chain Mail&lt;/a&gt;, but it has more weight than normally expected as the enchantment level on it increases, unlike all other magical armor, which exhibit a decrease in weight as the enchantment level increases. \nThe armor has the same protection modifiers as elven chain mail, +2 against slashing and -2 against piercing attacks, as well as the same penalties to thieving skills. It has a weight of 8 lbs and it provides an &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; of 4."}
{"id": "5281", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5281", "title": "Elven Chain Mail", "text": "Elven Chain Mail is a very light magical armor found in the , &lt;a href=\"Siege%20of%20Dragonspear\"&gt;Siege of Dragonspear&lt;/a&gt;, , , and .\nGameplay.\nIt has a weight of only 7 lbs and provides an armor class of 5. It has the same protection modifiers as regular &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Mail\"&gt;Chain Mail&lt;/a&gt;: a bonus of 2 against slashing, but also a penalty of 2 against crushing attacks.\nIts very low weight makes it ideal for low-strength characters.\nIts fine craftmasnship allows &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;Thieves&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bard\"&gt;Bard&lt;/a&gt;s to be wearing it while performing their &lt;a href=\"Thieving%20Abilities\"&gt;shadowy abilities&lt;/a&gt;, but they should be wary of the penalties: lockpicking and trap-finding/disarming are lowered by 5%, hide in shadows by 10% and pickpocketing by 20%.\nMoreover, its craftsmanship also makes it possible to be worn by arcane casters who will still be able to cast &lt;a href=\"wizard%20spells\"&gt;wizard spells&lt;/a&gt; without any spell failure, so it may be a good choice for Bards, &lt;a href=\"Fighter%20/%20Mage\"&gt;Fighter / Mage&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Cleric%20/%20Mage\"&gt;Cleric / Mage&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Fighter%20/%20Mage%20/%20Thief\"&gt;F/M/Ts&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Fighter%20/%20Mage%20/%20Cleric\"&gt;F/M/Cs&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Elven Chain Mail can't be worn by the specialized &lt;a href=\"Kensai\"&gt;Kensai&lt;/a&gt; fighters and &lt;a href=\"Archer\"&gt;Archer&lt;/a&gt; rangers, along with &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Monk\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt;s, and plain &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer\"&gt;Sorcerer&lt;/a&gt;s."}
