{"id": "54736", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54736", "title": "Elven Mage", "text": "Elven Mage is a somewhat generic title given to several creatures seen in the &lt;a href=\"Elven%20Temple%20at%20Underdark%20Exit\"&gt;Elven Temple at Underdark Exit&lt;/a&gt; area.\nThe creature represented in the InfoBox is an example of one of these five mages.\nPractically all of these various creatures are plot animation purposes rather than used as an opponent or interaction by the party. They are not meant to be attacked.\nMost of these creatures are removed by script (destroy-self) from the map when &lt;a href=\"Elhan\"&gt;Elhan&lt;/a&gt; finishes his main dialogue and assigns &lt;a href=\"The%20Elven%20City%20Requires%20My%20Aid\"&gt;The Elven City Requires My Aid&lt;/a&gt; questline. Some others just move off the map when triggered to do so.\nA similar one remains with &lt;a href=\"General%20Sovalidaas\"&gt;General Sovalidaas&lt;/a&gt;, though this one has limited dialogue and a different .CRE file (C6EXTR04)."}
{"id": "27970", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27970", "title": "Elven Priest Stone", "text": "The Elven Priest Stone can be found at the top of &lt;a href=\"The%20Priest%27s%20House\"&gt;The Priest's House&lt;/a&gt;, during ' and '. \nGameplay.\nThe item is flagged as \"critical\" and can't be sold. Its only purpose is to provide information/clues to assist with opening the puzzle box. The stone is removed from the game after the puzzle is solved.\nThe stone is inside the priest's desk and gives the solution to open the \"Elven Puzzle Box\". The puzzle box is located on the lower floor of this structure.\nSee &lt;a href=\"The%20House%20of%20the%20Talisman\"&gt;The House of the Talisman&lt;/a&gt; for details."}
{"id": "55235", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55235", "title": "Elven Spirit", "text": "Elven Spirit is an elven male with a blurry fighter appearance encountered in the battle for &lt;a href=\"Suldanessellar\"&gt;Suldanessellar&lt;/a&gt;, usually on the pathways and outside buildings.\nGameplay.\nThere are two \"Elven Spirit\" creatures that will be found on the map. The spirits are created after the &lt;a href=\"Avatar%20of%20Rillifane\"&gt;Avatar of Rillifane&lt;/a&gt; is awakened.\nThe spirits are generated at designated outdoor areas on the city map and are created as a plot device to illustrate that Rillifane has provided protective allied elven spirit warriors to purge the city of the invaders. \nAs the party travels on the city pathways, they are shown a scene where one elven warrior destroys a hostile &lt;a href=\"Lesser%20Air%20Elemental\"&gt;Lesser Air Elemental&lt;/a&gt;. Another is scripted to slay a golem.\nThe creatures are not meant to be destroyed by the player, but if they are attacked, they will be killed easily. A reputation penalty will be applied for killing an innocent."}
{"id": "51335", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51335", "title": "Elven Table while Spellhold Test", "text": "This area is technically part of &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe party appears in a rectangular room facing north. An impressive central table dominates the central area of the space. Upon it is seen various tableware, expensive cutlery and bowls laden with fruits, nuts, sweet cakes and other delicacies. To the left (west), center (north) and right (east) are seated four somber robed figures facing the party. They are silent and make no gestures at first meeting.\nGameplay.\nThis room is where the party is transported to by the &lt;a href=\"Apparition%20%28Spellhold%29\"&gt;Apparition&lt;/a&gt;. If the player has found themselves here, then this is a good sign, and the previous answers given to Apparition have been deemed to have mental clarity and are not considered problematic by the Arbiters.\nThe apparitions make no effort to initiate any conversation and curiously watch the party. \nAny of the four can be spoken to individually at first.\nThe design of this encounter, and the dialogue to come means that it doesn't matter which of these four apparitions are engaged first. For the sake of providing a description of this encounter the wiki will just begin with the apparition to the party's left, seated in the westernmost chair. Initiate dialogue by speaking to the creature.\nThe apparition (ELEPUZ01) will begin with:\nAfterwards another apparition (ELEPUZ02) interjects an answer with:\nAnd a third apportion (ELEPUZ03) interjects:\nThen the fourth (ELEPUZ04) says:\nThis discussion among the apparitions continues, with \"Then what is the proper fate?\" - and then another says \"Answer nonsense with nonsense. Let a backstep of logic move them forward.\"\nThe apparition now addresses the party and says:\nThe first riddle is then presented by the apparition (ELEPUZ01).\nFirst riddle.\nThe first apparition (ELEPUZ01) says:\nThe party must now make a selection from eight potential answer choices. If the correct answer is given, the apparition says - \"\"Giddy I am with the clarity of your perception, but free you are not. Have my fellows questions for this young mad&lt;MANWOMAN&gt;?\". Another apparition will then take over and ask the second riddle.\nIf an incorrect answer is given, the apparition will exclaim:\nThe party is then transported to the &lt;a href=\"Sahuagin%20Room%20%28Spellhold%20Test%29\"&gt;Sahuagin Room (Spellhold Test)&lt;/a&gt; area.\nSecond riddle.\nThe second apparition (ELEPUZ02) says:\nThe party must now make a selection from eight potential answer choices. If the correct answer is given, the apparition says - \"An answer that moves you forward, though only if you know where you began. Answer another from my kind to progress.\". Another apparition will then take over and ask the third riddle.\nIf an incorrect answer is given, the apparition will exclaim:\nThe party is then transported to the &lt;a href=\"Sahuagin%20Room%20%28Spellhold%20Test%29\"&gt;Sahuagin Room (Spellhold Test)&lt;/a&gt; area.\nThird riddle.\nThe third apparition (ELEPUZ03) says:\nThe party must now make a selection from eight potential answer choices. If the correct answer is given, the apparition says - \"\" A success that moves you towards goals you cannot know. Does it satisfy? Who can say? \". the fourth apparition will then take over and ask the fourth and final riddle.\nIf an incorrect answer is given, the apparition will exclaim:\nThe party is then transported to the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Room%20%28Spellhold%20Test%29\"&gt;Fire Room (Spellhold Test)&lt;/a&gt; area.\nFourth riddle.\nThe fourth apparition (ELEPUZ04) answers the third apparition and says:\nThe party must now make a selection from eight potential answer choices. If the correct answer is given, the apparition says:\nThis is followed by an exchange of commentary from the second apparition, \"This makes very little sense at all.\" - and the final statement from the first apparition summing it all up with \"Then it is more than I would have hoped from a room of the maddened dead.\"\"\nThe party is then transported to the &lt;a href=\"Troll%20Cave%20%28Spellhold%20Test%29\"&gt;Troll Cave (Spellhold Test)&lt;/a&gt; area.\nIf an incorrect answer is given, the apparition will exclaim:\nThe second apparition then interjects \"That makes no sense to the right-thinking person.\" - and the first apparition follows with \"What more would you ask of the maddened dead? It will suffice.\"\"\nThe party is then transported to the &lt;a href=\"Lever%20Room%20%28Spellhold%20Test%29\"&gt;Lever Room (Spellhold Test)&lt;/a&gt; area.\nContainers.\nTwo hidden containers. The central table, and a drawer in a small cabinet. You find a &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure\"&gt;Random treasure&lt;/a&gt; in one and the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Reflection\"&gt;Cloak of Reflection&lt;/a&gt; in the table.\nRiddle solution (spoiler).\nAttention: Reading the solutions is a \"spoiler\", don't expand the text if you want to try solving the riddles without being provided the answers.\nThe correct selections to solve Riddles 1 through 4 are:\nCongratulations! You have cheated successfully!"}
{"id": "53195", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53195", "title": "Elven Temple at Underdark Exit", "text": "Upon return to the surface, &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; begins, timers of pre-chapter 4 quests, if any, start to flow again, &lt;a href=\"romance\"&gt;romance&lt;/a&gt; will also be reactivated.\nDescription.\nThis outdoor area is a lightly forested setting with a few small ponds, some rocky outcroppings, and several ancient elf-tended trees. The area is an old cluster of elven temple activities, with some of the structures still standing from the recent drow assaults. Ritual circles and runes are still evident on the ground. \nThe elven forces have erected some semi-permanent tent structures here as well, with banners and heraldic flags fluttering atop.\nOn a small hillside is located the cave leading down into the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;. The cave is also connected to a ruined elven temple below, although damaged and no longer functional from the ravages of time and conflict. The elven forces seek to prevent the drow from pouring out into the surface to cause untold harm.\nThere are some areas that can be inspected on the map using the player's cursor, with text message display:\nPlot recap and entry into the Elven Temple at Underdark Exit.\nThe party has managed to extricate itself from the unfriendly Underdark and made its way past the &lt;a href=\"Drow%20gate%20guardians\"&gt;Drow gate guardians&lt;/a&gt;, then battling drow forces into the &lt;a href=\"Cave%20Between%20Underdark%20and%20Exit%20from%20Underdark\"&gt;Cave Between Underdark and Exit from Underdark&lt;/a&gt;, and finally to this elven occupied surface area. \nThe elven warriors above will immediately surround and take control of the party when they emerge from below. The party will have to speak with a &lt;a href=\"General%20Sovalidaas\"&gt;General Sovalidaas&lt;/a&gt;, and eventually the elven commander &lt;a href=\"Elhan\"&gt;Elhan&lt;/a&gt;.\nFrom this point on the saga continues and is described in the &lt;a href=\"The%20Elven%20City%20Requires%20My%20Aid\"&gt;The Elven City Requires My Aid&lt;/a&gt; quest pages and sub links on that article.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises all the elven creatures present on this map. This won't affect gameplay however, because the game plot script will terminate the player's PC if the elves here are attacked."}
{"id": "54735", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54735", "title": "Elven War Sage", "text": "Elven War Sage is a set of characters present during &lt;a href=\"Elhan\"&gt;Elhan's&lt;/a&gt; questioning of the party and their purpose after emerging from the &lt;a href=\"underdark\"&gt;underdark&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Elven%20Temple%20at%20Underdark%20Exit\"&gt;Elven Temple at Underdark Exit&lt;/a&gt; area.\nGameplay.\nWhile Elhan is questioning the party regarding what they were up to in the Underdark, as well as what they may know of &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;Jon Irenicus&lt;/a&gt; - these two sages are assisting in divining the answers and replies to the elven commander.\nThe sages have an uncanny perception to discern truth and falsehood. The sages typically interject short appraisal conclusions of any answer given by the party to Elhan's line of questioning.\nAfter the party has been assigned &lt;a href=\"The%20Elven%20City%20Requires%20My%20Aid\"&gt;The Elven City Requires My Aid&lt;/a&gt; journal entry, the two sages are now trimmed to one (WARSAGE.cre), remaining with Elhan.\nThis solitary sage has additional dialogue, and some of it is pertinent to the &lt;a href=\"Rhynn%20Lanthorn\"&gt;Rhynn Lanthorn&lt;/a&gt;, Vampirism and other Chapter 6 topics.\nA reminder that any attacks on the elves in this area will lead to a near immediate game scripted plot death for the PC - as warned by the General earlier."}
{"id": "54721", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54721", "title": "Elven Warrior", "text": "Elven Warrior is a somewhat generic title given to several creatures seen in the &lt;a href=\"Elven%20Temple%20at%20Underdark%20Exit\"&gt;Elven Temple at Underdark Exit&lt;/a&gt; area.\nThe creature represented in the InfoBox is an example of one of these elven warriors, although there may be slight sprite differences between several (for visual variety purposes).\nPractically all these various creatures are plot animation purposes rather than used as an opponent or interaction by the party. They are not meant to be attacked.\nMost of these creatures are removed by script (destroy-self) from the map when &lt;a href=\"Elhan\"&gt;Elhan&lt;/a&gt; finishes his main dialogue and assigns &lt;a href=\"The%20Elven%20City%20Requires%20My%20Aid\"&gt;The Elven City Requires My Aid&lt;/a&gt; questline. Some others just move off the map when triggered to do so.\nA few remain with &lt;a href=\"General%20Sovalidaas\"&gt;General Sovalidaas&lt;/a&gt;, though those have different .CRE files (C6EXTR03)."}
{"id": "55092", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55092", "title": "Elven Warrior (General)", "text": "Elven General is an experienced elven male fighter class encountered in the battle for &lt;a href=\"Suldanessellar\"&gt;Suldanessellar&lt;/a&gt;, positioned in front of the first of two gates leading to &lt;a href=\"The%20Palace\"&gt;The Palace&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe general addresses the first detected party member in his visual range. He isn't sure if the party is real. Those shifty Rakshasas have been fooling the elves with their illusions most likely.\nA discussion will begin as the player tries to convince the general that the party is here to help, and is assisting Elhan, and hunting Irenicus and things of that nature.\nThe party spokesperson will be able to get favorable dialogue reactions based on moderately high &lt;a href=\"Charisma\"&gt;Charisma&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Wisdom\"&gt;Wisdom&lt;/a&gt; attributes, depending on the dialogue selections.\nIt isn't very difficult to get the general to believe that you are friends of the elves, and he'll unlock the gate for you.\nEven if the party blunders and fails this task - the gate only has 70 difficulty to lockpick. If even that is too hard for the party to do, then try a &lt;a href=\"Knock\"&gt;Knock&lt;/a&gt; spell or try to force open the gate with strength. Failing that, you'll have to scout around and perhaps find a side path into the Palace grounds."}
{"id": "55089", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55089", "title": "Elven Warrior (Suldanessellar)", "text": "Elven Warrior is an elven male fighter class encountered in the battle for &lt;a href=\"Suldanessellar\"&gt;Suldanessellar&lt;/a&gt;, usually on the pathways and outside buildings.\nGameplay.\nThere are a number of \"Elven Warrior\" creatures that will be found on the map. Some are prepositioned on the city map. Others are spawned and created by the party crossing hidden proximity triggers. For instance, you will come across a group of these warriors in battle with some trolls or a rakshasa. The game is inviting the party to join in and defeat the enemy.\nThe player can't control these elves, nor give them orders.\nOccasionally some of the elves will show shouts and battle cries displayed on the player's text screen.\nSeveral of the creatures share the same dialogue scripts if spoken to by a party member - just embellishment dialogue for more immersive gameplay.\nThe purpose of these elves is to add some realism for the story that the elves are in battle with Irenicus's forces, as they defend the city and try and stave off the various intruders.\nIn reality, they aren't meant to actually defeat anything in the city on their own, or somehow come to the rescue of the party. If the player wants to kill a troll, or a rakshasa, or a golem, these elves can't do it on their own. They can't even hit a golem or raksasha with their melee weapons, nor kill a troll since they have no fire or acid attack (although the &lt;a href=\"Elven%20Battle%20Mage\"&gt;Elven Battle Mage&lt;/a&gt; can kill a troll.\nThey will actually take a swing or two if they see an enemy creature.\nIf any of the warriors are killed, they drop a bit of equipment. Accidentally, or even on purpose, the player can kill any of these elves. There are no repercussions other than for role play reasons.\nThe Elven Warrior that is guarding the main gates and pathway to the Palace after the &lt;a href=\"Avatar%20of%20Rillifane\"&gt;Avatar of Rillifane&lt;/a&gt; is awakened, and the &lt;a href=\"Elven%20Spirit\"&gt;Elven Spirit&lt;/a&gt; guardians of Rillifane have purged the enemy from the city streets - will some congratulatory comments about this."}
