{"id": "48887", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48887", "title": "Elyme", "text": "Elyme is a &lt;a href=\"dryad\"&gt;dryad&lt;/a&gt; found on the first floor of &lt;a href=\"Irenicus%27s%20Dungeon%201st%20Floor\"&gt;Irenicus's Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;. She and two of her fellow dryads, &lt;a href=\"Cania\"&gt;Cania&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ulene\"&gt;Ulene&lt;/a&gt;, have been trapped by &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;Jon Irenicus&lt;/a&gt; in the Dryad Grotto that's located between Irenicus's master bedroom and &lt;a href=\"Ellesime\"&gt;Ellesime&lt;/a&gt;'s bedroom. \nWhen you get near them, they will speak to you and &lt;a href=\"Helping%20Irenicus%27s%20captive%20dryads\"&gt;ask you to retrieve&lt;/a&gt; their &lt;a href=\"acorns\"&gt;acorns&lt;/a&gt; from the duergar clan leader &lt;a href=\"Ilyich\"&gt;Ilyich&lt;/a&gt; and give them to the &lt;a href=\"Vaelasa\"&gt;Fairy Queen&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt; area. Doing this will free the dryads from their captivity. If you kill the dryad instead, the Fairy Queen will know about this and attack you when she sees you.\nIf you have already &lt;a href=\"Free%20the%20Djinn\"&gt;dealt with the djinn&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Malaaq\"&gt;Malaaq&lt;/a&gt; and are searching for his &lt;a href=\"The%20Genie%27s%20Flask\"&gt;flask&lt;/a&gt;, they will offer to give you the flask if you promise to take their acorns to the Fairy Queen."}
{"id": "6336", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6336", "title": "Embarl", "text": "Embarl is a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thief&lt;/a&gt; who originally worked under &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var\"&gt;Mae'Var&lt;/a&gt; in the city of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; during the Baldur's Gate II\" Shadows of Amn campaign. He is only found during the side quest to &lt;a href=\"Find%20Proof%20of%20Mae%27Var%27s%20Treachery\"&gt;Find Proof of Mae'Var's Treachery&lt;/a&gt;.\nEmbarl is wanted dead after accidentally over hearing Mae'Var's plan to overthrow &lt;a href=\"Renal%20Bloodscalp\"&gt;Renal Bloodscalp&lt;/a&gt;, so Mae'Var will task &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; with killing Embarl. As proof of the deed, Mae'Var will also require &lt;a href=\"Embarl%27s%20Dagger\"&gt;Embarl's Dagger&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe option to allow Embarl to escape with his life is available if killing him is an undesirable outcome (e.g., party members such as Jaheira and Aerie will not like the becoming \"bounty hunters,\" and Aerie will be relieved if the party does not have \"to kill that poor man\").\nDialogue.\n\"You... you're here to kill me, aren't you?! Please! Tell Mae'Var it was all a misunderstanding!\""}
{"id": "5391", "revid": "285155", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5391", "title": "Embarl's Dagger", "text": "Embarl's Dagger is an item needed to convince &lt;a href=\"Mae%27Var\"&gt;Mae'Var&lt;/a&gt; that &lt;a href=\"Embarl\"&gt;Embarl&lt;/a&gt; has been killed by &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party during the events of the &lt;a href=\"Find%20Proof%20of%20Mae%27Var%27s%20Treachery\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; given by &lt;a href=\"Renal%20Bloodscalp\"&gt;Renal Bloodscalp&lt;/a&gt;. Unlike a normal &lt;a href=\"dagger\"&gt;dagger&lt;/a&gt;, this weapon inflicts 1d6 instead 1d4 points of piercing damage. You can kill Embarl to gain this weapon and obey the orders of Mae'Var or ask him to hand over the dagger and spare his life."}
