{"id": "49469", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49469", "title": "Empathic Manifestation", "text": "The Empathic Manifestation can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20the%20Forgotten%20God\"&gt;Temple of the Forgotten God&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Reaches\"&gt;Lower Reaches&lt;/a&gt;.\nAppearance.\nIt has the appearance of a &lt;a href=\"Tanar%27ri\"&gt;Tanar'ri&lt;/a&gt; demon from The Abyss, however its general form is &lt;a href=\"humanoid\"&gt;humanoid&lt;/a&gt; having no &lt;a href=\"race\"&gt;race&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Classes\"&gt;class&lt;/a&gt; or gender.\nGameplay.\nThe manifestation has no armor or weapons, or any other item in inventory except for a ring. Therefore, its attack with natural weapons only deals 1d2 crushing damage, but with +6 damage from &lt;a href=\"Strength%23Exceptional%20strength\"&gt;Exceptional Strength&lt;/a&gt;, twice per round at a -3 &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus.\nIt wears the &lt;a href=\"MINHP1.ITM\"&gt;MinHP1&lt;/a&gt; ring that prevents its death by any means in the enhanced game . In the classic game there may be a way around the ring (same as with other creatures that wear it). \nIn both versions of the game, the intention is that the manifestation can only be slain by curative magic such as &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Light%20Wounds%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Cure Light Wounds&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lay%20on%20Hands%20%28paladin%29\"&gt;Lay on Hands&lt;/a&gt;, or other spells. \nHowever, this usually requires a character to touch the creature, opening them up to its melee attacks.\nDistracting it may prove difficult. One way to deal with the interruptions is to use &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;'s fast casting &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Light%20Wounds%20%28ability%29\"&gt;Cure Light Wounds (ability)&lt;/a&gt;, if they have it. \nAnother tactic is to cast multiple healing spells from more than one party members at the same time, if the party has the resources to do so.\nFurther within the temple is a non-obvious container that holds a healing spell scroll which can be used for this purpose as well (and a spell cast from a scroll cannot be interrupted).\nOnce healing is applied, the MinHP1 ring is destroyed, and so shall be the manifestation. Then the &lt;a href=\"Avatar%20of%20Amaunator\"&gt;Avatar of Amaunator&lt;/a&gt; will appear and address the party."}
{"id": "56090", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56090", "title": "Emperor (card)", "text": "The Emperor card, can be drawn from the deck of many things when agreeing to play a game with &lt;a href=\"Aesgareth\"&gt;Aesgareth&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis page is to document the potential spell effects of this card when it is drawn.\nGameplay.\nWhen a party member character engages in the third card draw contest with Aesgareth, there is an even chance of drawing the Emperor card, or the &lt;a href=\"High%20Priestess%20%28card%29\"&gt;High Priestess (card)&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf this card is drawn, the script controlled by Aesgareth's dialogue will apply this spell to the party member who drew the card.\nThe spell will animate a graphic visual effect and color glow over the character, and a sound effect will be audibled.\nA \"Mind Shield\" icon is placed in the character's portrait.\nThe target is now affected by a unique series of protections that last for one week.\nThe character will be immune to &lt;a href=\"Confusion\"&gt;Confusion&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Creature\"&gt;Charm Creature&lt;/a&gt; status effects.\nThis spell is unaffected by magic resistance, and all of its internal components have a 0 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt;.\nA &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect won't work on this spell."}
{"id": "56088", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56088", "title": "Empress (card)", "text": "The Empress card, can be drawn from the deck of many things when agreeing to play a game with &lt;a href=\"Aesgareth\"&gt;Aesgareth&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis page is to document the potential spell effects of this card when it is drawn.\nGameplay.\nWhen Aesgareth takes a turn in the second draw contest, there is an even chance of drawing the Empress card, or the &lt;a href=\"Defiance%20%28card%29\"&gt;Defiance (card)&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf this card is drawn by the fiend, the cambion is affected by this spell.\nThe spell will display a &lt;a href=\"True%20Seeing\"&gt;True Seeing&lt;/a&gt; 3D effect animation and similar spell effects. \nThe cambion will now automatically be able to destroy illusionary creatures in its sight range. \nCoupled with its innate &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt; power, this spell effect grants a permanent True Seeing effect that lasts one week. \nOther than the initial graphic and lighting effect when the spell takes hold, the player won't know the cambion has this extra power. \nIt can't be dispelled."}
