{"id": "7874", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7874", "title": "Ender Sai", "text": "Ender Sai is a spy in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". He's interested in the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt;, and for that reason he was captured and imprisoned within &lt;a href=\"Tazok\"&gt;Tazok&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Tazok%27s%20Tent\"&gt;tent&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Bandit%20Camp\"&gt;Bandit Camp&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter dealing with the four mercenaries within the tent, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; can free Ender, who will proceed to relay everything he knows, although most everything he says will also be detailed in the \"papers\" within the nearby trapped chest."}
{"id": "49937", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49937", "title": "Endless Watcher", "text": "The Endless Watcher is a specter, which has stood watch over the trapped lich &lt;a href=\"Zhadroth\"&gt;Zhadroth&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Kanaglym\"&gt;Kanaglym&lt;/a&gt; for centuries, and will only appear if the lich is released.\nIt will be greatly angered over the freed lich and attack, the battle ends by Zhadroth trapping the Watcher with a spell, leaving the &lt;a href=\"Astral%20Crossbow\"&gt;Astral Crossbow&lt;/a&gt; on the ground. The fight can be avoided if told Zhadroth is destroyed, then it will reward the same crossbow, and be released from the endless watch."}
{"id": "40786", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40786", "title": "Enegar", "text": "Enegar and &lt;a href=\"Kastulor\"&gt;Kastulor&lt;/a&gt; are &lt;a href=\"Bhaalspawn\"&gt;Bhaalspawn&lt;/a&gt;s raised by a Bhaal cult. They have trained since childhood to make use of the power coursing through their veins. As a Berserker, Enegar was so good at controlling the rage that he became able to transform at will into &lt;a href=\"The%20Ravager\"&gt;The Ravager&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe was provided with high-end equipment like &lt;a href=\"Enkidu%27s%20Full%20Plate\"&gt;Enkidu's Full Plate&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Ravager\"&gt;Ravager +6&lt;/a&gt;, and was trained in combat tactics well enough that he knew to take a normal weapon to harm a mage using &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, or to cover his Ravager form's only vulnerability with a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Magic%20Shielding\"&gt;Potion of Magic Shielding&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs the Ravager, his attacks can amongst other things destroy ."}
{"id": "4318", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4318", "title": "Enemies", "text": "This is the list of most enemies found in Baldur's Gate series, along with XP and HP values."}
{"id": "38321", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38321", "title": "Enemy", "text": ""}
{"id": "21674", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21674", "title": "Energy Blade", "text": "An Energy Blade is a weapon materialized by the &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;high-level class abilities&lt;/a&gt; \"Energy Blades\" &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Blades%20%28priest%29\"&gt;for priests&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Blades%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;for wizards&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is a special kind of dart that doesn't require or benefit from &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Proficiency\"&gt;proficiency&lt;/a&gt; in darts, and whose physical damage is &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing&lt;/a&gt; instead of &lt;a href=\"Missile%20damage\"&gt;Missile&lt;/a&gt;.\nBugs.\nPer their description, Energy Blades should do missile damage, not slashing. This issue is already identified and revised by &lt;a href=\"The%20Enhanced%20Edition%20Fixpack%20%28EEFP%29\"&gt;The Enhanced Edition Fixpack (EEFP)&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod changes the discs to have a 5-turn duration and implements an internal control to limit the Improved Haste effect to not apply the movement modifier boost, or any additional APR boosts as long as the discs are equipped. The electrical damage applied as an on-hit effect is now level 0 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; and non-magical, so is unaffected by magic resistance, and won't interact with a spell protection (such as Spell Trap) the target creature has active. It is simply a hurled missile weapon now, with a range of 20 feet.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod recodes the Energy Blades to have no assigned Spell school or Secondary type. SCS leaves the blades to inflict slashing damage (they are a blade, not a dart). If SCS and SR mods are installed together, the SCS blade version will be present in the game. SCS also uses the same 0 power level electrical damage and bypasses magic resistance that SR uses."}
{"id": "22196", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22196", "title": "Energy Blades", "text": ""}
{"id": "30580", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30580", "title": "Energy Blades (arcane)", "text": ""}
{"id": "21675", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21675", "title": "Energy Blades (disambiguation)", "text": "Energy Blades may refer to:"}
{"id": "30581", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30581", "title": "Energy Blades (divine)", "text": ""}
{"id": "21673", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21673", "title": "Energy Blades (priest)", "text": "Energy Blades is a &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; usable by &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"druid\"&gt;druid&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"shaman\"&gt;shaman&lt;/a&gt;.\nCreates the weapon &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Blade\"&gt;Energy Blade&lt;/a&gt;, tied to the caster. As long as at least one blade remains, the caster is under the &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Improved Haste effect&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nAfter creation, the blades have a duration of 240 seconds (4 turns). If not used by then, they expire and disappear.\nAlthough available to arcane casters as well, this spell is particularly interesting for divine casters, due to its long-lasting haste (an effect that's normally unavailable to priests, other than Stalker/Clerics, except through the use of items) and the availability of the &lt;a href=\"Regeneration%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Regeneration&lt;/a&gt; spell along with it. When combined, the two spells allow for not only great offensive capabilities (Energy Blade), but also great defensive capabilities as well, due to a regeneration of 6hp/second (originally 3hp/second but doubled by the Energy Blade's &lt;a href=\"haste%20effect\"&gt;haste effect&lt;/a&gt;). Since the Energy Blades last for a long time (40 rounds), a spellcasting-focused priest may even choose to hold on to the last blade instead of using it, making the haste effect persist for all those rounds.\nBugs.\nPer their description, Energy Blades should do missile damage, not slashing. This issue is already identified and revised by &lt;a href=\"The%20Enhanced%20Edition%20Fixpack%20%28EEFP%29\"&gt;The Enhanced Edition Fixpack (EEFP)&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this High-level class ability spell, revising its casting time, duration, effects, school, and description. See below:\nEnergy Blades\nLevel: Epic\nSchool: Evocation\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 5 turns\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nAn energy blade is a discus made of pure energy. The discs are thrown with a +10 bonus to THAC0, inflict 1d4+5 missile damage as well as 1d10 additional electrical damage, and are considered to be of +5 enchantment to determine what they can hit. This spell creates 20 energy discs and sets the caster\u2019s number of attacks per round to 9 as long as the discs are held."}
{"id": "4769", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4769", "title": "Energy Blades (wizard)", "text": "Energy Blades is a &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; usable by &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"sorcerer\"&gt;sorcerer&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; to self only.\nAfter the HLA's casting is finished, it replaces currently equipped weapons with a number of &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Blade\"&gt;Energy Blade&lt;/a&gt; missiles, which are implemented as a \"dart\" that don't require proficiency in darts. As long as the mage has at least one such dart left in-hand, the caster is also under the &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Improved Haste effect&lt;/a&gt;.\nA mage with high wisdom and access to the spell &lt;a href=\"Wish\"&gt;Wish&lt;/a&gt; is able to maximize the elemental portion of the Energy Blades' damage via the intoxication wish, that inflicts -12 luck on everyone in the area (though one should protect oneself against it or cure the intoxication afterwards, so that the physical portion of the Energy Blades' damage isn't minimized). And, of course, spells and abilities such as &lt;a href=\"Kai\"&gt;Kai&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Righteous%20Magic\"&gt;Righteous Magic&lt;/a&gt; can maximize the physical portion, meaning that Kensai/Mages and Cleric/Mages are able to consistently do 9 missile + 10 electrical damage per hit under the right conditions.\nUnlike &lt;a href=\"Melf%27s%20Minute%20Meteors\"&gt;Melf's Minute Meteors&lt;/a&gt;, Energy Blades:\nBugs.\nAs of BG2EE 2.6, per their description, Energy Blades should apply missile damage, not slashing. This is identified for correction in the pending Enhanced Edition Fix Pack (EEFP). Ref: (eneblade.itm)\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this High-level class ability spell, revising its casting time, duration, effects, school, and description. See below:\nEnergy Blades\nLevel: Epic\nSchool: Evocation\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 5 turns\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nAn energy blade is a discus made of pure energy. The discs are thrown with a +10 bonus to THAC0, inflict 1d4+5 missile damage as well as 1d10 additional electrical damage, and are considered to be of +5 enchantment to determine what they can hit. This spell creates 20 energy discs and sets the caster\u2019s number of attacks per round to 9 as long as the discs are held.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod, which is usually installed late in any multiple mod installation order actually revises the ENEBLADE.itm and it still inflicts Slashing damage rather than missile damage. This means if the player has SCS plus SR, the blade will not inflict missile damage, but slashing. However the SCS version is a power level 0 item with a 1d10 non magical electrical damage add-on that bypasses magic resistance."}
{"id": "30114", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30114", "title": "Energy Cells", "text": "Energy Cells are a reward from &lt;a href=\"Rielev\"&gt;Rielev&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Free%20Rielev%20from%20his%20life%20support\"&gt;Free Rielev from his life support&lt;/a&gt; quest."}
{"id": "4788", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4788", "title": "Energy Drain", "text": "\"Energy Drain\" lowers the victim's total experience level by two whole levels.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a single-target creature to apply this spell to, at touch range.\nThe caster doesn't need to roll to hit the target.\nThe victim is exposed to a &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt; effect, similar to that which a occurs when a &lt;a href=\"Vampire\"&gt;Vampire&lt;/a&gt; strikes a target.\nTwo experience levels are drained from the victim, and there is no saving throw allowed.\nThe spell bypasses &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe spell can be blocked with a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20protections%20type\"&gt;Spell protections type&lt;/a&gt; that has a capacity to absorb a 9 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; spell, such as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;.\nAdditionally, a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Necromancy&lt;/a&gt; will negate the spell.\nIf the spell is successful, the target creature has a lighting effect and brief color fade graphic effect rendered on their sprite, as well as a sound effect is audibled.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons Wizard spell \"Energy Drain\" requires a successful touch attack in melee. A victim drained of all hit dice will animate into a \"juju zombie\" controlled by the caster. The caster always has a 5% (1 in 20) chance to be affected by the spell's component dust, losing one point of Constitution at the same time as the victim is drained. The Pen and Paper game version spell only affects living creatures, unlike the BG game's implementation.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has replaced Energy Drain with the spell described below:\nLarloch\u2019s Energy Drain\nLevel: 9\nSchool: Necromancy\nRange: Short\nDuration: Special\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nThe casting of this spell opens a channel between the caster\u2019s plane and the Negative Energy Plane. The caster of the spell acts as a conduit between the two planes, sucking life from a living creature and transferring it to the Negative Energy Plane, draining him of 4 levels of experience. The target of this spell loses levels, Hit Dice, hit points, and abilities permanently. These levels can only be restored by a priest\u2019s Restoration spell. As the life force passes through the caster, it temporarily invigorates him, granting him an additional 20 hit points, a +4 bonus to attack rolls and saving throws, and +20% bonus to every skill. These effects last for 1 hour. The target\u2019s magic resistance, if any, does not affect this spell."}
{"id": "8492", "revid": "283433", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8492", "title": "Enge", "text": "Enge is a fruit merchant in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign, however, also he sells mundane melee weapons, armor, shields and an unlimited supply of &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Healing\"&gt;Potions of Healing&lt;/a&gt;.\"'Allo you again! Eng is wavink 'allo! You be wantink to see everythink, ja? Ah. gut! Ve be havink much fruit, yes? But you no be wantingk fruit, I be sure! I show you vat else I be havingk! Come! I show!\"Enge does not speak proper Common."}
