{"id": "12071", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12071", "title": "Enna Hendrick", "text": "Enna Hendrick is a farmer's wife who has fled to the town of &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale\"&gt;Imnesvale&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt; with her husband &lt;a href=\"Erlin%20Hendrick\"&gt;Erlin&lt;/a&gt; and a number of their chickens during the \"\" campaign.\nThough she and her husband claim the chickens are for eating, killing them reveals that one contains a &lt;a href=\"Beljuril\"&gt;Beljuril&lt;/a&gt; gemstone. Attacking the chickens will turn her hostile, but her husband will soon calm her down, so try to avoid killing her. A more peaceful route is to offer Erline for the chicken."}
{"id": "15471", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15471", "title": "Enrage", "text": "Enrage is a class ability available to &lt;a href=\"Berserker\"&gt;Berserker&lt;/a&gt;s, who get one extra use per day every 4 levels starting from the first.\nGameplay.\nRundown of events:"}
{"id": "55317", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55317", "title": "Enslaved Genie", "text": "Enslaved Genie is present when the party descends stairs leading below to the &lt;a href=\"Greed%20%28Abyss%29\"&gt;Greed (Abyss)&lt;/a&gt; area during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%207\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 7&lt;/a&gt;, part 2.\nGameplay.\nThe Greed Fiend will direct the bhaalspawn to speak with the genie, and then the fiend will disappear from the area. \nWhen the PC nears the genie, it will initiate dialogue. Through this conversation the tormented genie will answer questions, but only in so far as it is allowed. Some information is not permitted to be revealed.\nThe protagonist must decide if what to do with the &lt;a href=\"Blackrazor\"&gt;sword&lt;/a&gt; obtained from the fiend. Use it for good and in a charitable manner, or retain it as his own possession, which is deemed the greedy path.\nIf the player decides to take the \"evil\" path and try and destroy the genie, then the creature will acknowledge this decision and fight back.\nThe genie (who behaves similarly to an &lt;a href=\"Efreeti%20%28Noble%29\"&gt;Efreeti (Noble)&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Noble%20Djinni\"&gt;Noble Djinni&lt;/a&gt; hybrid) has a wide array of arcane magic of which some is \"force cast\", and those spells aren't interruptible. Many spells, especially those with extended casting times can potentially be interrupted.\nIt's possible a &lt;a href=\"Gate%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Gate (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; spell will be attempted which is interruptible.\nSee the InfoBox for a breakdown of scripted spell use.\nThe genie can also attack with its melee weapon twice per round, dealing crushing damage. The weapon is classified as non-magical and has no enchantment value.\nWhen the genie is destroyed, it drops the necessary &lt;a href=\"Tears%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;Tear of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt; the party seeks.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Afaaq%20the%20Djinni%20Companion\"&gt;Afaaq the Djinni Companion&lt;/a&gt; mod adds a special interaction element during the Test of Greed. Gorion's Ward, Afaaq and the Enslaved Genie have a dialogue exchange here. By taking the \"good\" path, it is possible to not only free the Enslaved Genie, but to also free Afaaq as well (as long as the PC possesses Afaaq's \"Soul Cage\" gem obtainable during Chapter 5).\nThis mod bestows scripted use of three unique spells for this creature to employ including \"Whirlwind\" and \"Air Shield\". It also has a special mod version of \"Conjure Air Elemental\" scripted to add an ally to the genie. This works alongside &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;SCS&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;SR&lt;/a&gt; mods as well.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; makes some revisions to this creature, particularly it's spell script and AI. The mod also reorients the genie into a Noble Djinni and backs off the Efreeti design - not focusing on Fire based immunities and spells.\nThe creature's resistances are changed to 50% fire damage, 100% electricity damage, and 25% cold and acid resistance. The Djinni is immune to &lt;a href=\"Paralyze\"&gt;Paralyze&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Webbed\"&gt;Webbed&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Entangle\"&gt;Entangle&lt;/a&gt; effects.\nThe enslaved genie can &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; an opponent, and it also is scripted to use &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt; as well as a &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt;. It deals offensive damage spells via lightning and various disablers via Symbol spells. Expect more staying power from this creature, with several instantly applied buffs and reapplication if those are removed/expire. \nIt will be able to disappear via &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Invisibility\"&gt;Improved Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; spells."}
{"id": "5046", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5046", "title": "Entangle", "text": "Entangle is a 1st level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"druid\"&gt;druid&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"shaman\"&gt;shaman&lt;/a&gt;s, and &lt;a href=\"ranger\"&gt;ranger&lt;/a&gt;s. In the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\", it could also be used by &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s. It causes vines to spring from the ground, rendering creatures within the affected area immobile.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this divine spell, revising its effects, casting time, area of effect, saving throw and description. See below:\nEntangle\nLevel: 1\nSchool: Alteration\nSphere: Plant\nRange: Long\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: 30\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: Breath partial\nBy means of this spell, the caster causes plants to entangle all creatures in the area of effect. The grasses, weeds, bushes, and even trees wrap, twist, and entwine about the creatures, holding them fast for the duration of the spell. Those held receive a -2 penalty to attack rolls and a +2 penalty to AC. Creatures that make a successful saving throw vs. breath temporarily avoid entanglement and can move at half speed through the area but must make additional saving throws each round they remain in the area of effect. An entangled creature can attack, provided it does not have to move to reach an opponent. Incorporeal and flying creatures are unaffected by this spell, as are elementals and exceptionally large and strong creatures who suffer little to no distress from the entangling plants."}
{"id": "8246", "revid": "35642161", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8246", "title": "Entar's Son", "text": "Entar's Son, also known as Kagain's Quest, is a &lt;a href=\"companion%20quest\"&gt;companion quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\", available from &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20One\"&gt;Chapter One&lt;/a&gt; on.\nWalkthrough.\nKagain.\nUpon entering &lt;a href=\"Kagain%27s%20Shop\"&gt;Kagain's Shop&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt; and asking &lt;a href=\"Kagain\"&gt;its owner&lt;/a&gt; \"what kind of shop\" this may be, the &lt;a href=\"dwarf\"&gt;dwarf&lt;/a&gt; states that he is running an escort business and hires mercenaries to protect \"caravans on route from &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. Right now I'm lookin' for some strong sword arms\" and he offers up the job to find out what happened to one of his caravans that didn't make it to the Gate.\nIf asked for more information, Kagain reveals that he's \"been having a lot of problems\" with &lt;a href=\"bandit\"&gt;bandit&lt;/a&gt;s recently, but that they usually would let the caravans go. Not in this case, however, about which he normally \"wouldn't give one damn\" \u2013 wasn't it for &lt;a href=\"Entar%20Silvershield\"&gt;Entar Silvershield&lt;/a&gt; being the father of one of the missing passengers.\nIf accepting the job and Kagain's payment, he will join as a &lt;a href=\"companion\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt;, and an eight day counter starts until he will remind &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;. If then a further seven days pass without finding the caravan, Kagain will leave the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt;, canceling the job.\nCoast Way.\nThough nothing points directly to that &lt;a href=\"Areas%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;area&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Coast%20Way\"&gt;Coast Way&lt;/a&gt; is at least part of the route to &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, and thus may be a good start for the research.\nOriginal game.\nSimply arriving at the Coast Way together with Kagain marks in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" the end of this &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;, without any &lt;a href=\"%23Rewards\"&gt;reward&lt;/a&gt; (not counting Kagain as a &lt;a href=\"companion\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt;).\n\"Enhanced Edition\".\nDepending on how much of the Coast Way wilderness has been explored earlier \u2013 on the way from the &lt;a href=\"Friendly%20Arm%20Inn\"&gt;Friendly Arm Inn&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt;, for example \u2013, the two \"raided caravans\" may already have been noticed, even relieved of whatever was there to take. Anyway, to the east and up the hillside, past the single overthrown wagon, &lt;a href=\"Kagain\"&gt;Kagain&lt;/a&gt; will recognize the body of Entar's son among the victims of a larger caravan \u2013 unless it took more than one day to find it since having arrived here. In the latter case, he will have lost interest in the task, with job and &lt;a href=\"%23Rewards\"&gt;reward&lt;/a&gt; canceled.\nIf found in time, Kagain now believes that, with &lt;a href=\"Entar%20Silvershield\"&gt;Silvershield's&lt;/a&gt; son being under his responsibility when killed, he is a wanted dwarf, and as he deduces that &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; is after the &lt;a href=\"bandit\"&gt;bandit&lt;/a&gt;s too, he offers to help them gain revenge \"on those scumbags\" and accompany the party permanently. Depending on how he &lt;a href=\"Reaction\"&gt;reacted&lt;/a&gt; to the person who negotiated this job with him, he might even have some payment, in addition to the few items that can be found on site.\nIf you manually speak to Kagain at the 3 wagon site he will finish the quest.\nIf Skie is present upon completion of the quest she will mourn: \u201c*sniffle* I can\u2019t believe he\u2019s dead.\u201d\nRewards.\nBesides having gained a &lt;a href=\"companion\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt;, there's no reward for this &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". \"(See also &lt;a href=\"%23Bugs\"&gt;bugs&lt;/a&gt;.)\"\nIn the \"\", the exact material reward depends on &lt;a href=\"Kagain\"&gt;Kagain&lt;/a&gt;'s reaction to the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; member who made the deal with him. There's no &lt;a href=\"experience\"&gt;experience&lt;/a&gt; gained."}
{"id": "6122", "revid": "274599", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6122", "title": "Entar Silvershield", "text": "Entar Silvershield is the husband of &lt;a href=\"Brilla\"&gt;Brilla&lt;/a&gt;, father of &lt;a href=\"Skie\"&gt;Skie&lt;/a&gt;, and, along with &lt;a href=\"Duke%20Eltan\"&gt;Duke Eltan&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Duke%20Belt\"&gt;Belt&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Liia%20Jannath\"&gt;Liia Jannath&lt;/a&gt;, one of the Grand Dukes of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; before he was assassinated by &lt;a href=\"Slythe\"&gt;Slythe&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Krystin\"&gt;Krystin&lt;/a&gt;. He lived in an estate in &lt;a href=\"northwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;northwest Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; with his wife and daughter. He is only ever mentioned, never seen during the course of the original \"Baldur's Gate\".\nIn the \"Enhanced Edition\" he is present upstairs in his estate and, if Skie is in your party, he angrily berates her upon finding out about her \"friends\" being present in the house, before leaving in a huff. If Skie isn't in your party, Entar calls for his guards and disappears.\nFollowing his assassination, he reappears in \"Siege of Dragonspear\". which takes place several weeks after the death of Sarevok. Following the failed assassination of the protagonist in the Ducal mansion, Entar Silvershield reveals that it took all of Fenster's skills to restore him back to life, but does not divulge any further details."}
{"id": "10812", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10812", "title": "Entar Silvershield's Estate", "text": "Entar Silvershield's Estate is the large mansion located in the district of &lt;a href=\"Northwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Northwest Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and is where the Silvershield family resides. The house has its own private inner wall and gate which separate it from the rest of the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;city&lt;/a&gt;. The front door is locked.\nGround Floor.\nLayout.\nThe front door opens into a furnished grand foyer where a &lt;a href=\"servant\"&gt;servant&lt;/a&gt; can be found staring at the painting on the back wall. To the left of the foyer, through a set of double doors, is a large formal living room furnished with a pair of couches and large overstuffed chairs situated around a circular coffee table in front of a fireplace. A wide, \"T-shaped\" staircase, located against the back wall, leads to the second floor and a &lt;a href=\"guard\"&gt;guard&lt;/a&gt; is standing at the foot of the stairs.\nTo the right of the foyer, through another set of double doors, is a small living room furnished with a couch and an overstuffed chair situated around a rectangular coffee table in front of a fireplace. A dining table and six chairs are located between the couch and the front wall of the house. A second servant is standing between the head of the table and a lootable credenza. A third set of double doors leads to the final room which also features a wide, \"T-shaped\" staircase located against the back wall that creates two separate, small, private meeting areas within the room. Both of these areas are furnished with a couch and two overstuffed chairs. A second guard is found standing at the foot of the stairs in this room too.\nPeople.\nDepending upon their &lt;a href=\"reaction\"&gt;reaction&lt;/a&gt;, talking to either of the two servants will result in being unchallenged or having them call for the guards standing near each set of stairs.\nAs for the guards, depending upon their reaction, they will either let you pass unchallenged or declare you as thieves and attack. If your &lt;a href=\"charisma\"&gt;charisma&lt;/a&gt; is high enough, giving the excuse of being from Waterdeep and needing to talk to &lt;a href=\"Entar%20Silvershield\"&gt;Entar Silvershield&lt;/a&gt; will get them to let you pass while the other three dialogue choices all lead to fighting. Killing these two guards doesn't result in a loss of reputation or further consequences. The guards can also be avoided with &lt;a href=\"invisibility\"&gt;invisibility&lt;/a&gt;.\nLoot.\nIn the large living room there are two locked chests located on either side of the fireplace. The left side chest contains a &lt;a href=\"Star%20Diopside%20Gem\"&gt;Star Diopside Gem&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Gold%20Necklace\"&gt;Gold Necklace&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Studded%20Necklace%20with%20Ziose%20Gems\"&gt;Studded Necklace with Ziose Gems&lt;/a&gt;, and 386 . The right side chest contains 254 , a &lt;a href=\"Moonbar%20Gem\"&gt;Moonbar Gem&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Magic%20Blocking\"&gt;Potion of Magic Blocking&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Potion of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;. The bookcase contains a copy of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20VII\"&gt;History of Shadowdale VII&lt;/a&gt;. Both of the lootable credenzas in the small living room are empty and the bookcases near the stairs contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Dambrath\"&gt;History of Dambrath&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Cormyr\"&gt;History of Cormyr&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Shadowdale%20IX\"&gt;History of Shadowdale IX&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Calimshan\"&gt;History of Calimshan&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf you open the two chests with the guard still in the room, &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Enforcer%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23FLAMEN\"&gt;Flaming Fist Enforcers&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Guard%20Enforcer\"&gt;Guard Enforcer&lt;/a&gt;s will be summoned.\nSecond Floor.\nLayout.\nDepending on which set of stairs you use to access the second floor will determine what room you encounter first. From the living room, the stairs to the front of the house exit into &lt;a href=\"Skie%20Silvershield\"&gt;Skie's&lt;/a&gt; bedroom and the stairs to the back exit into the kitchen. The stairs on the right side of the floor both exit into the master bedroom. Located between the kitchen and the master bedroom is a large formal dining room.\nPeople.\nInside the kitchen is a cook standing in front of a table. Skie can be found in her bedroom which is located adjacent to the kitchen. if you speak to her without &lt;a href=\"Eldoth%20Kron\"&gt;Eldoth&lt;/a&gt; in the party, all dialogue leads to her calling the guards and either attacking the party or disappearing down the stairs. Entar Silvershield can be found standing in the dining room near the fireplace that is closest to the kitchen and he immediately calls for the guards if you attempt to speak with him. A third servant is standing near the other fireplace that is closest to the master bedroom. Entar's wife, &lt;a href=\"Brilla%20Silvershield\"&gt;Brilla&lt;/a&gt;, is in the master bedroom and is the only NPC on the floor that will immediately approach the party upon sight. Her reaction to the party will determine whether or not she calls for the guards.\nLoot.\nThe three containers in the kitchen are empty. In Skie's bedroom, the big armoire is empty. The small armoire is locked and contains 359 , a &lt;a href=\"Pearl%20Necklace\"&gt;Pearl Necklace&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Black%20Opal\"&gt;Black Opal&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Water%20Opal\"&gt;Water Opal&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Freedom\"&gt;Potion of Freedom&lt;/a&gt;, an &lt;a href=\"Elixir%20of%20Health\"&gt;Elixir of Health&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Oil%20of%20Speed\"&gt;Oil of Speed&lt;/a&gt;. The dresser is locked and contains 308 and a &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Protection%20%2B1\"&gt;Cloak of Protection +1&lt;/a&gt;. The chest at the foot of the bed is locked and contains 154 and a &lt;a href=\"Laeral%27s%20Tear%20Necklace\"&gt;Laeral's Tear Necklace&lt;/a&gt;. Both armoires in the master bedroom are empty and the bookcases contain copies of the &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Durpar%20and%20Var%20the%20Golden\"&gt;History of Durpar and Var the Golden&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20Estagund\"&gt;History of Estagund&lt;/a&gt;.\nQuests.\nIf Eldoth is in your party when you first talk to Skie, she will agree to join the party, otherwise no matter which answer you give her, she will call the guards."}
{"id": "42885", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42885", "title": "Entering Dragonspear Castle", "text": "Upon arriving at the &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Exterior\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Exterior&lt;/a&gt;, the way into the courtyard will be blocked by several advanced members of the &lt;a href=\"Shining%20Crusade\"&gt;Shining Crusade&lt;/a&gt;, who will refuse to grant &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; access unless they can prove they are members.\nCompleting you.\nThe player can gain access to the Castle Exterior by either convincing the guards that they have important information about an impending attack, which requires a sufficiently high &lt;a href=\"Charisma\"&gt;Charisma&lt;/a&gt; stat, or by acquiring a &lt;a href=\"Seal%20of%20Caelar\"&gt;Seal of Caelar&lt;/a&gt;, which can be done by successfully completing the quest &lt;a href=\"Slime%20Sickness\"&gt;Slime Sickness&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River\"&gt;Underground River&lt;/a&gt;. You can also get a seal from the cyclops guarding the stockade at the entrance to the underground river or you can pickpocket one from Malden Col in the allied siege camp.\nQuest conflict.\nA &lt;a href=\"Seal%20of%20Caelar\"&gt;Seal of Caelar&lt;/a&gt; is required to complete both this quest and the quest &lt;a href=\"Accessing%20the%20Warrens\"&gt;Accessing the Warrens&lt;/a&gt;. The same Seal acquired from completing &lt;a href=\"Slime%20Sickness\"&gt;Slime Sickness&lt;/a&gt; can be used for both, and it's possible to complete both quests with it. However, if the player completes Accessing the Warrens and then goes straight to the Warrens, they will lock themselves out of being able to visit &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Exterior\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Exterior&lt;/a&gt;, as visiting the &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Basement\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Basement&lt;/a&gt; triggers the shift to the finale of chapter 10."}
{"id": "37502", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37502", "title": "Entertained", "text": ""}
{"id": "53140", "revid": "26028522", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53140", "title": "Entertainer (BG3)", "text": "Entertainer is a character &lt;a href=\"Backgrounds%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;background&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20III\"&gt;Baldur's Gate III&lt;/a&gt;\". It conveys a +3 &lt;a href=\"Skill%20Proficiency%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;Skill Proficiency&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Acrobatics%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;Acrobatics&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Performance%20%28BG3%29\"&gt;Performance&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "8189", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8189", "title": "Entillis Fulsom", "text": "Entillis Fulsom is a &lt;a href=\"Harpers\"&gt;Harper&lt;/a&gt; and friend of &lt;a href=\"Gorion\"&gt;Gorion&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Khalid\"&gt;Khalid&lt;/a&gt;. He can be found in the district of &lt;a href=\"South%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;South Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, standing near the outer rampart gate that leads to &lt;a href=\"West%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;West Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. He will immediately greet &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party upon sight and inform them that &lt;a href=\"Scar\"&gt;Scar&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Duke%20Eltan\"&gt;Duke Eltan&lt;/a&gt; are trustworthy people capable of providing you with some guidance and protection during your investigations of the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt;. \nIf your &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt; is 7 or less, he will think you too similar to your father, the &lt;a href=\"Bhaal\"&gt;Lord of Murder&lt;/a&gt;, and will attack you because of this. Killing him will drop your Reputation by 2 points. If your reputation is currently 5, it will trigger reputation traps within the city that spawn hostile &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; troops. In that case it is better to avoid killing him.\nQuotes.\nIf only Jaheira \"or\" Khalid is in the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt;, Entillis has unique greetings."}
{"id": "9245", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9245", "title": "Entropy", "text": "&lt;a href=\"Haer%27Dalis\"&gt;Haer'Dalis&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0joins the party dual wielding Entropy and &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Blade\"&gt;Chaos Blade&lt;/a&gt;.\nEntropy poisons the target on hit, &lt;a href=\"save\"&gt;save&lt;/a&gt; vs. death neg, curable, for 1 damage per second for 3 seconds, the effects are cumulative.\u00a0\nThis shortsword is only usable by Haer'Dalis. In the \"\", even rogues with &lt;a href=\"Use%20Any%20Item\"&gt;Use Any Item&lt;/a&gt; may not wield it."}
{"id": "20308", "revid": "978785", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20308", "title": "Entropy +2", "text": ""}
{"id": "48736", "revid": "284703", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48736", "title": "Entu", "text": "Entu is a vicious, cannibalistic, psionic Halfling from &lt;a href=\"Athas\"&gt;Athas&lt;/a&gt; who resides (willingly or not) along with his fellow halflings within the &lt;a href=\"Inside%20the%20Planar%20Sphere%23The%20Caverns\"&gt;Caverns&lt;/a&gt; inside the &lt;a href=\"The%20Planar%20Sphere\"&gt;Planar Sphere&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlong with his fellows, &lt;a href=\"Kayardi\"&gt;Kayardi&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mogadish\"&gt;Mogadish&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Togan\"&gt;Togan&lt;/a&gt;, Entu can present even a high-level party with quite a challenge.\nGameplay.\nEntu is capable of launching &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Ability\"&gt;Psionic Ability&lt;/a&gt; powers at enemies. He is scripted to use one of his psionic abilities every two rounds, against any detected enemies in range. There is an 89% chance he will shout for help. He'll start the battle with a &lt;a href=\"Magic%20attack%20type\"&gt;magic attack&lt;/a&gt;, a special &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Domination\"&gt;Psionic Domination&lt;/a&gt; aimed at the nearest enemy. In between Psionic ability use, he'll be trying to close in melee combat with his mace. He packs a wallop with his magically augmented strength and can strike twice per round. In the EE editions, Entu has the following Psionic Ability powers, which are memorized as innate abilities:\n&lt;a href=\"Ballistic%20Attack\"&gt;Ballistic Attack&lt;/a&gt; : With a 10 feet range, this instantly cast attack delivers a 5d12 crushing attack to a single target. It is a level less spell power effect with no spell school. This creature may use this power once per 12 seconds. It is unaffected by spell protections or magic resistance. There is no saving throw. (reference SPIN911.SPL)\n&lt;a href=\"Ego%20Whip\"&gt;Ego Whip&lt;/a&gt;: With a range of 10 feet, this instantly cast attack delivers a 24 second stun effect to one target, unless a save vs. Death is made. It is a level less spell power effect with no spell school. The creature may use this power once per 12 seconds. It is unaffected by spell protections or magic resistance. As this is a non-magical attack, it cannot be dispelled. (reference SPIN909.SPL)\n&lt;a href=\"Detonate\"&gt;Detonate&lt;/a&gt;: With a range of 40 feet, this instantly cast attack delivers a 1d10 magical energy to all enemy creatures in the area of effect (the area of effect is quite large). It is a level 3 spell power effect with no spell school. The creature may use this power once per 12 seconds. It is unaffected by magic resistance, and there is no saving throw. (reference SPIN912 and SPIN912D.SPL)\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; did not revise Entu's script. It did change weapon proficiencies to 5 pips with mace, and also assigned 2 pips in single-weapon fighting style. This increases Entu's damage output and APR. Armor class is also improved as well as critical hit percentage."}
