{"id": "51005", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51005", "title": "Ercias", "text": "Ercias is a human male thief in the &lt;a href=\"Five%20Flagons%20Inn\"&gt;Five Flagons Inn&lt;/a&gt; located in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt;, skulking in the shadows of the 2nd Floor. He does not initiate conversation if you approach. \nIf anyone in the party speaks with him, he'll avoid saying too much. However, if &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; is on the floor at this time, then this thief will be recognized by her, probably from some past Harper encounter, and the thief will beat feet and leave for good, as he has been exposed. Jaheira says: \"Hmm... wait one moment... do I know you?\", to which Ercias replies: \"Er... no, no, I don't think so. I must be going, actually\". And finally Jaheira says: \"\"I see. A Zhentish agent, if I recall, but one of no consequence. Pay him no heed, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;\u00abCharname\u00bb&lt;/a&gt;\".\"\nHe'll have some other interjections if a halfling is present or if &lt;a href=\"Yoshimo\"&gt;Yoshimo&lt;/a&gt; is in the party. There are some other lines as well. It all depends on the dialogue choices made, and who is talking. With &lt;a href=\"Haer%27Dalis\"&gt;Haer'Dalis&lt;/a&gt; in the party, Ercias says: \"Aye now, yer back, are ye?\", to which the &lt;a href=\"Haer%27Dalis\"&gt;Tiefling&lt;/a&gt; replies: \"Yes, well... I was rather tied up back there for a while, my friend.\"\nIf you desire to, the party could preemptively try and slay this unsavory lurker. There are no witnesses. Act as deemed necessary. The party is in Athkatla, City of Coin (and unprovoked murder). If the party is concerned about clean-up or body disposal, just remeber that sleeping somewhere - somehow - makes all corpses disappear. Its \"magic\". \nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; revises Ercias by assigning an SCS default thief AI script for smarter tactical behavior and backstabbing. Weapon proficiency is changed to 1 pip with Short Sword and 1 pip in single weapon style. "}
{"id": "3844", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3844", "title": "Erdane", "text": "Erdane is a &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; who serves as a merchant at &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28Area%29\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt;. He sells items which come in handy for the dungeon. He sells item for 150% of their value and buys them from you for only 50% of their value. He can be killed with no &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt; loss. In he can act as a &lt;a href=\"fence\"&gt;fence&lt;/a&gt;, allowing you to sell stolen goods to him.\nDialog.\n\"Step right up, step right up! Welcome to the brave new age of mercantile expansionism, ladies and gentlemen, a brave new age where we make money off of death itself! Money off of horror, my poor children, money off of loss and pain and longing, money off of ravaged beauty and tainted honor, money off of a man gone mad! Now, all my dear voyeurs, ask not what you can do for me but what I can do... for you.\""}
{"id": "53112", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53112", "title": "Eric Vanstraaten", "text": "Eric Vanstraaten is an NPC during the \"\" campaign, and especially during the &lt;a href=\"The%20final%20battle%20with%20Bodhi\"&gt;The final battle with Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; questline in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nIf the party visits &lt;a href=\"Prelate%20Wessalen\"&gt;Prelate Wessalen&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Most%20Noble%20Order%20of%20the%20Radiant%20Heart%20building\"&gt;Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart building&lt;/a&gt; in Athkatla and asks about obtaining help to fight a \"vampire coven\" then help may be offered. However, it is not automatic if the protaganist had sided with &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; earlier in the saga in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%203\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 3&lt;/a&gt;. The Paladins are not pleased in the least with that decision.\nIf that is not applicable, then the prelate will agree to send some paladins ahead to provide assistance in your struggle.\nThe Paladin Vanstraaten, &lt;a href=\"Sir%20William%20Reirrac\"&gt;Sir William Reirrac&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Nerit\"&gt;Nerit&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Branet%20Al-Thon\"&gt;Branet Al-Thon&lt;/a&gt; will already be in the catacombs awaiting the party to battle &lt;a href=\"Bodhi%27s%20Vampire%20Coven\"&gt;Bodhi's Vampire Coven&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe paladin warriors are not configured with any of the Paladin passive resistances or use of innate abilities such &lt;a href=\"Lay%20on%20Hands%20%28paladin%29\"&gt;Lay on Hands (paladin)&lt;/a&gt;, nor do they have use of any Cleric spells.\nEric is actually equipped with a sword that bears a resemblance to &lt;a href=\"Harbinger\"&gt;Harbinger&lt;/a&gt;, but it is an undroppable version that does not have the random &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt; ability of the original. During the battle it is essentially just a &lt;a href=\"Two%20Handed%20Sword%20%2B3\"&gt;Two Handed Sword +3&lt;/a&gt;. If Eric is slain, and his corpse looted, then the creature drops a &lt;a href=\"Two-handed%20Sword%20%2B2\"&gt;Two-handed Sword +2&lt;/a&gt;.\nMore information about this encounter is covered in the &lt;a href=\"The%20final%20battle%20with%20Bodhi\"&gt;The final battle with Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; quest page, which is the primary purpose for the party to be in this area.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a revised fighter style AI script to the paladin in Chapter 6. It allows for application of several SCS potions readied for quaffing during hostilities. Additionally, 2 pips in two-handed weapon fighting style are added to the creature's weapon proficiency."}
{"id": "2258", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2258", "title": "Erik", "text": "Erik is a resident of &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt;, and friend of &lt;a href=\"Jondalar\"&gt;Jondalar&lt;/a&gt;. He is part of one of the many optional tutorials at the beginning of the game. His purpose in the game is to get the player used to being shot at with missile weapons."}
