{"id": "50241", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50241", "title": "Erinyes", "text": "Erinyes are beautiful and striking female Devils, skilled in missile fire and seduction. They are in certain areas of &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt; and some may be found in Yaga-Shura's lair. Although classified as Demonic by the game, they are in fact &lt;a href=\"Baatezu\"&gt;Baatezu&lt;/a&gt; devils.\nGameplay.\nErinyes will attempt to engage with bow and arrow fire. With their superior dexterity, &lt;a href=\"Elven%20Court%20Bow\"&gt;Elven Court Bow&lt;/a&gt; clone and Enchanted Arrow bonuses to hit, they are much more likely to successfully strike with missile fire than melee. They strike twice per round by bow, and only once with their long sword. Once in melee range, the creatures are very vulnerable to being overwhelmed.\nThese she devils have a number of magics that can be \"ForceSpell\" cast during combat. See the InfoBox for a breakdown of those.\nThis devil has an assigned Racial Enemy of &lt;a href=\"Human\"&gt;Human&lt;/a&gt; and receives a 4-point &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; and damage bonus versus that race.\nWhen the creature is wounded it will apply healing spells to itself at certain thresholds, and onto allies in range. The creature may teleport out of the battle and be gone for good if severely wounded.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some revisions to this creature, in part to make the creature closer to the 2nd Edition D&amp;D ruleset description.\nThe devil is reconfigured to a level 12/12/12 creature. The creature has some added spell immunities, some of which are to ensure that other devil's area of effect spells won't affect them by accident.\nThe devil no longer has healing spells and uses three innate spells to include instant cast versions of Invisibility, &lt;a href=\"Unholy%20Blight\"&gt;Unholy Blight&lt;/a&gt;, \"Teleport without error\" to jump around the battlefield, and frequent use of the potent \"Erinyes charm\" (if the target meets certain vulnerability criteria). \nUses &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt; instead of Mantle.\nHas a more adaptive AI to focus on maneuvering so to be able to avoid melee combat and use bow and arrow attacks. \nThe random treasure carried by the devil is replaced with an SCS random scroll item."}
{"id": "55876", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55876", "title": "Erinyes Charm", "text": "Erinyes Charm is a quick casting Enchanter spell with the disabling secondary type. It is scripted for use by &lt;a href=\"Erinyes\"&gt;Erinyes&lt;/a&gt; creatures.\nGameplay.\nThe she devil casts this spell, typically at the closest enemy target to herself, although it might be another as well.\nIf the spell exposes the target creature to a &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Creature\"&gt;Charm Creature&lt;/a&gt; effect, and a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Spell will negate it, but there is an 5-point penalty.\nThe charmed target will be hostile after the dire charm effect is ended.\nThis charm spell can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, and spells/abilities/items which provide immunity to charm. Additionally, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Enchantment&lt;/a&gt; will block this magic.\nSpell protections like &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; can block this spell.\nThe entire spell and all its effects can be removed by &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects."}
{"id": "48052", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48052", "title": "Erlin Hendrick", "text": "Erlin Hendrick is a farmer who has fled to the town of &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale\"&gt;Imnesvale&lt;/a&gt; with his wife &lt;a href=\"Enna%20Hendrick\"&gt;Enna&lt;/a&gt; and a number of their chickens during the \"\" campaign. They are part of the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt; area.\nThough he and his wife claim the chickens are for eating, killing them reveals that one contains a &lt;a href=\"Beljuril\"&gt;Beljuril&lt;/a&gt; gemstone. Attacking the chickens will turn Enna hostile, but Erlin will soon calm her down, so try to avoid killing her. A more peaceful route is to offer him for the chicken."}
{"id": "8562", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8562", "title": "Errard", "text": "Errard is a lawful &lt;a href=\"lawful%20evil\"&gt;evil&lt;/a&gt; / &lt;a href=\"lawful%20good\"&gt;good&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Saradush\"&gt;Saradush&lt;/a&gt;, responsible for managing the city's defences. You will need to speak with him in order to complete the Good path of the &lt;a href=\"Betrayal%20at%20the%20Gates\"&gt;Betrayal at the Gates&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nIf you opt to take the Evil path, then you either must kill Errard yourself or allow Kiser to do it while you kill the Countess."}
{"id": "48474", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48474", "title": "Ertof Dand", "text": "Ertof Dand is the leader of a group of bandits during the events of \"\". He has heard that &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; has amassed many valuable items worth stealing.\nGameplay.\nIf Gorion's Ward is a male &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"elf\"&gt;elf&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"half-elf\"&gt;half-elf&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"halfling\"&gt;halfling&lt;/a&gt;, and the romance with &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; has reached a certain point (Jaheira's Local variable LoveTalk = 27), Ertof and his band might appear any time the party is resting outdoors. Otherwise, this encounter will never happen.\nErtof's band wake the party with a blade at Jaheira's throat, and an ultimatum to hand over all their possessions or else. Gorion's Ward will then have a few different dialog options, which may affect the outcome of the romance.\nIf the protagonists chooses the options \"Alright, no one do anything...\" and \"...Leave her be, I'll be your hostage\" and \"..take me instead...let's make this easy\" then, Ertof will agree, \"Yes, let's make this very easy indeed! Kracer, take the shot!\" Gorion's Ward then receives \"the shot\" that inflicts damage equal to half of current hit points. This shot is delivered by an unseen assailant, Kracer. However, there is no creature file for Kracer; it is only a dialog/story element, and not anyone upon which Jaheira or the Ward can avenge themselves. After Jaheira's outrage and Ertof's delightful response, the battle is on.\nAlong with Ertof are two more &lt;a href=\"Fighter\"&gt;fighters&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"Jarden\"&gt;Jarden&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Turg\"&gt;Turg&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"Tamile\"&gt;Tamile&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"Wurn\"&gt;Wurn&lt;/a&gt;. Each bandit is worth , except for Tamile ().\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises all of these bandits. Each is assigned new default SCS AI scripts for smarter tactical behavior. Wurn will self-buff at the outset of hostilities. The thief Tamile will attempt to backstab after quaffing a invisibility potion - watch out if you are a mage or have a mage in the party as that is the priority target. All of the bandits have reworked weapon proficiencies and weapon fighting styles commensurate with their experience levels and class.\nErtof Dand will quaff a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Hill%20Giant%20Strength\"&gt;Potion of Hill Giant Strength&lt;/a&gt; at the outset of hostilities, and then engage in melee. Ertof has 5 pips in long sword proficiency and 2 pips in single weapon fighting style, so he'll have an improved APR, THAC0. damage and armor class from the unmodified game creatures. This is SCS upping the challenge factor."}
{"id": "35072", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35072", "title": "Escaping the Asylum", "text": ""}
{"id": "34947", "revid": "285456", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34947", "title": "Escaping the asylum", "text": "Escaping the asylum is a Main Quest in and its Enhanced Edition. It takes place during Chapter 4 and begins once the player enters &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Main%20Floor\"&gt;the main floor&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt; for the first time.\nQuest summary (abbreviated - main points only).\nEnter Spellhold.\nEntering Spellhold results in the party being taken captive by &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;Jon Irenicus&lt;/a&gt;. See &lt;a href=\"Getting%20inside%20the%20asylum\"&gt;Getting inside the asylum&lt;/a&gt; for methods to do so. Also see &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Main%20Floor\"&gt;Spellhold Main Floor&lt;/a&gt; for details once inside.\nIrenicus strips the PC's bhaalspawn soul essence.\nIn a cutscene the player will resume the quest within a laboratory located in the &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Basement\"&gt;Spellhold Basement&lt;/a&gt; - a scene plays out involving the death of several shadow thieves whose extermination is used to power some kind of sophisticated apparatus; resulting in the protagonist being drained of certain essential forces while trapped in a glass tube/cage.\nIrenicus will reveal that he stole some fundamental part of Gorion's Ward's soul, using it to heal himself of some unknown affliction (this causes you to lose all of your special bhaalspawn innate abilities). \nCandlekeep Bhaal dream.\nThe protaganist then is transitioned to a cut scene scenario detailed on the &lt;a href=\"Dreams%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;Dreams (Shadows of Amn)&lt;/a&gt; page.\nAfter the dream sequence the player will also learn that the same thing happened to Imoen, and also, that she is a bhaalspawn as well. After some banter, threats, vows of vengeance etc. he will depart the lab to continue with his master plan, leaving the PC a drained and soulless husk. The PC and the rest of the party are handed over to &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; to do with as she pleases.\nBodhi initiates the asylum hunt.\nBodhi will transport the party to the &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Bodhi%27s%20Hunt%20Level%201\"&gt;Asylum Dungeon's first floor&lt;/a&gt;, declaring that she wants the party to try and solve their way through this labyrinth of monsters, traps and trials, whilst she will intermittently hunt them down. She then departs, but not before reuniting Gorion's Ward with Imoen at long last. If the party lost Yoshimo, she will immediately join the party to fill the slot. If the party did not include Yoshimo, the player can choose to add Imoen to the party or instruct her to escape on her own. If that option is taken expect a poor verbal reaction from some core party members. Imoen will then depart the dungeon level (somehow) and can be located later in the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt; (somehow). If the party already has six party members and the player wants to add Imoen, then one party member will have to be dismissed, and if so, will depart spellhold and then be recruitable again at their usual place (somehow).\nThe party must make their way through all three levels of the Asylum Dungeon, then navigate the &lt;a href=\"Apparition%20%28Spellhold%29\"&gt;Arbiters examination&lt;/a&gt; until they finally return to the main floor of Spellhold. Thanks to Irenicus stealing their soul, Gorion's Ward has lost their original &lt;a href=\"Bhaalspawn\"&gt;Bhaalspawn&lt;/a&gt; abilities - but, on the third level of the labyrinth dungeon, in a scripted encounter, they will gain a replacement power; &lt;a href=\"Slayer%20Form\"&gt;Slayer Form&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce the party has convinced the arbiters that they should be released from the asylum, they must deal with &lt;a href=\"Lonk\"&gt;Lonk&lt;/a&gt; in order to acquire the keys to the inmates' cells. As Imoen explains, Irenicus is too powerful and too well protected to be defeated by a conventional assault, but an onslaught of insane spellcasters would be something else entirely. Additionally, &lt;a href=\"Saemon%20Havarian\"&gt;Saemon Havarian&lt;/a&gt; will also make an appearance and advise that the inmates are a resource to exploit against Irenicus. If the party decides to kill Saemon at this juncture, which is possible, then the player will shutter their path forward. They will be limited to using the portal to the underdark and the entire leaving the island quest as well as the &lt;a href=\"Underwater%20City\"&gt;Underwater City&lt;/a&gt; adventure will not happen. \nFight Irenicus.\nThe newly expanded party must then fight a battle against Irenicus, covered in the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20with%20Irenicus%20in%20Spellhold\"&gt;Battle with Irenicus in Spellhold&lt;/a&gt; article. When Irenicus is reduced to \"Near Death\" status, he will teleport away, but the asylum inmates will be killed in a scripted event. This then activates the second phase of the battle, against a number of enemy assassins, whose ability to hide in shadows and then backstab is a threat not to be underestimated. At the same time, if Yoshimo was brought to Spellhold, he will also appear and fight the party to the death, asking that if he dies, Gorion's Ward will take his heart to &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Ilmater%20%28Slums%20District%29\"&gt;the Temple of Ilmater in Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Freeing%20Yoshimo%27s%20Soul\"&gt;so his soul can be freed&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce the last of the &lt;a href=\"Murderer\"&gt;Murderer&lt;/a&gt; thieves are killed, the party is free to explore Spellhold. In the entry hall, the party will re-encounter &lt;a href=\"Saemon%20Havarian\"&gt;Saemon Havarian&lt;/a&gt; again (unless killed earlier), who offers a way to leave &lt;a href=\"Brynnlaw\"&gt;Brynnlaw&lt;/a&gt;; there is a key to a portal to the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt; in the Director's study, available via a door nearby, or the party might be able to set sail on Saemon's ship. If the party tries to attack Saemon, then they are forced to take the portal.\nEntering the Director's Chambers requires slaying a &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Golem\"&gt;Stone Golem&lt;/a&gt; left behind to guard them. The party can find two of Irenicus' journals in these chambers, which provide some clue as to what he was doing, as well as a &lt;a href=\"Staff%20of%20Thunder%20and%20Lightning\"&gt;Staff of Thunder and Lightning&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Stone\"&gt;Rogue Stone&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Horn%20of%20Silence\"&gt;Horn of Silence&lt;/a&gt;. If they have declined Saemon's offer they must take Jon's Key and return to the lower floor to open the hidden door to a portal to the Underdark, gaining 20,000 Quest EXP and completing Chapter 4 by immediately beginning Chapter 5.\nIf the party chooses to accept Saemon's offer of help, they must instead complete a miniature quest, &lt;a href=\"leaving%20the%20island\"&gt;leaving the island&lt;/a&gt;. This will result in them receiving the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Blade\"&gt;Silver Blade&lt;/a&gt;, as well as 20,000 Quest XP, and being taken to the &lt;a href=\"Underwater%20City\"&gt;Underwater City&lt;/a&gt;. This is where they must &lt;a href=\"The%20prophecy%20of%20Sekolah\"&gt;end the sahuagin civil war&lt;/a&gt; before they can reach the Underdark and begin Chapter 5. An advantage to going this route is being able to visit stores and temples on the island in between adventures, relieving inventory pressure. Much unique treasure and further gameplay with XP rewards is also presented. Bypassing this route is possible, but the party will miss out on all the offerings of that path, while they will not miss out on any of the other, cause if they want they can re-enter the Asylum, kill the Stone Golem and get the Staff of Thunder and Lightning, the Rogue Stone and the Horn of Silence before leaving the island.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Asylum\"&gt;Improved Asylum&lt;/a&gt; adds further content to Bodhi's hunt in the asylum.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod component that is optionally installed (for challenge and realism) that disarms the party's equipment (they are captive prisoners after all) takes place just before resuming the quest in the &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Bodhi%27s%20Hunt%20Level%201\"&gt;Spellhold Bodhi's Hunt Level 1&lt;/a&gt; area."}
{"id": "31578", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31578", "title": "Essence of Clarity", "text": "Essence of Clarity is a that can be found in \"\".\nAcquisition.\nTwo possible bottles can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Repository%20of%20Undeath\"&gt;Repository of Undeath&lt;/a&gt;. One is on a shelf to the west of the wooden chair hanging over the mists in the laboratory, and the other held by one of the undead horde behind the hidden door near the center of the map.\nFunction.\nOnce the Scrying Pool in the Repository of Undeath is made functional by the installation of three &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Scepter\"&gt;Silver Scepter&lt;/a&gt;s, each can be used to see an additional possible vision."}
{"id": "11671", "revid": "6896023", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11671", "title": "Estate of Oberon", "text": ""}
{"id": "48291", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48291", "title": "Estate of Saerk Farrahd", "text": "The Estate of Saerk Farrahd is a large house that dominates the center of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign.\nWalkthrough.\nOutside.\nIts unconventional lock on the front door prevents entry from street level. The stairs to the right of the front door lead up to the roof where another door can be used to gain entry to an L-shaped hall.\nUpstairs.\nInside, the door to the left leads to an outside balcony. Around the corner of the \"L\" a female &lt;a href=\"Guard%20%28Saerk%27s%20House%29\"&gt;House Guard&lt;/a&gt; is stationed between two columns.\nIf the Guard sees you, she asks, \"Who in the blazes are you?\" Although hostile, she does not immediately attack, giving you a brief chance to leave. If you do not leave immediately, or you attack, she and the rest of the house guards will automatically attack without waiting. When she attacks, two House Guards come in behind you from the roof door to the outside stairs.\nWith a few exceptions, &lt;a href=\"Guard%20%28Saerk%27s%20House%29\"&gt;House Guards&lt;/a&gt; carry Chain Mail, Helmet, Long Sword, Long Bow, Arrows , and some carry &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20%2B1\"&gt;Arrows +1&lt;/a&gt; , as well as minor treasure (gold, scroll, etc).\nThe initial Guard is worth (at no Reputation loss), and the two she summons from the outside are worth .\nDetecting traps reveals secret doors in both columns, leading to the rest of the upper floor.\nThe four-bed room to the northwest of the hallway has 4 chests (2 locked), an armoire and two bookshelves. The bedroom to the southeast of the hallway has 2 locked armoires. Containers in these rooms have minor random treasure.\nEast of the hall and bedrooms is a big central living room with a Standing Harp and Grand Piano. One male Guard hails you before saying, \"What th...! You're not supposed to be here! Men!! Intruders!!\" With another voice-over, \"I'll test your mettle with cold steel\" the battle is on. He wears Plate Mail Armor, Large Shield, Helmet and carries a &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword%20%2B1\"&gt;Bastard Sword +1&lt;/a&gt;. He is worth , while his men, 4 other House Guards, are equipped as mentioned above and worth . House Guards will fire their Arrows +1 first, unless you close to melee. \nEast of the Living Room, to the southeast, is another Bedroom with two bookshelves, one of which contains a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Invisibility\"&gt;Potion of Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Master%20Thievery\"&gt;Potions of Master Thievery&lt;/a&gt; . A small end table holds &lt;a href=\"Elixir%20of%20Health\"&gt;Elixirs of Health&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Antidote\"&gt;Antidotes&lt;/a&gt; \nThe Safe.\nAnother Secret Column Door is hidden in the corner and leads to a Secret Room with a trapped, locked Safe and one female Guard. This guard is worth and carries the same equipment as others, including &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20%2B1\"&gt;Arrows +1&lt;/a&gt; . Clicking on an Archway to the left gives you the message \"This passage leads below to a small cellar of no interest.\" \nThe Safe is locked and contains , a &lt;a href=\"Star%20Sapphire\"&gt;Star Sapphire&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Ruby%20Ring\"&gt;Ruby Ring&lt;/a&gt;. The two tables to the right of the safe contain a &lt;a href=\"Flail%20%2B1\"&gt;Flail +1&lt;/a&gt; and mundane weapons. Another Secret Column Door leads out to a storage room.\nStorage Room.\nThere are three containers here, all with random treasure.\nDownstairs.\nThe northeast part of the Living Room has a double stairway leading down to the First Floor, where two more House Guards stand ready at the bottom of the stairs. These two both have &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20%2B1\"&gt;Arrows +1&lt;/a&gt; each, and are worth . Crossing this central room you'll find another Grand Piano and another Guard, who despite you having just killed two of his men at the stairs, hails you with the voice-over, \"I trust you have no hostile intentions.\" Dialog auto-initiates as soon as you come into his view, saying \"Excuse me, sir, but this is a private estate. I'm afraid you will have to leave immediately\" with the following options:\n1:- Who's estate is this?\n\"This is the estate of the merchant Saerk yn Muham el Farrahd, if you must know. The merchant and his family are not home at the present, so please leave at once.\"\n2:- You're going to have to force me, because I intend on going where I like.\n3:- All right, I'm going.\nThis guard is worth , wears Splint Mail, and has &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20%2B1\"&gt;Arrows +1&lt;/a&gt; . Going pass this last guard you find the front doors which allow you to exit out to street-level, but does not allow re-entry.\nBesides the Guards, there is a &lt;a href=\"Cook%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;Cook&lt;/a&gt; in the Kitchen and a &lt;a href=\"Servant\"&gt;Commoner&lt;/a&gt; serving in the Dining Room. Killing either of these two results in the normal Reputation Loss for Murdering an Innocent. Containers in these two rooms provide random treasure.\nThe southeastern room is a Library with 4 Bookshelves, one of which has a Priest Scroll &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; and a Wizard Scroll &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Person\"&gt;Charm Person&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe southwestern room is a Study. The Desk has a Lightning Trap and contains one &lt;a href=\"Emerald\"&gt;Emerald&lt;/a&gt;.\nNorthwest of the Study is another Bedroom with a locked chest, a small desk and two armoires, all with random treasure.\nWest of the stairs is a Bunking quarters with another House Guard; \"Cross blades with me and die!\" He is worth and carries &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20%2B1\"&gt;Arrows +1&lt;/a&gt; . Next to the Bunks are a total of 6 chests, some of them are locked, containing random treasure.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises the guards in this estate with default SCS Fighter AI for smarter tactical behavior. All assigned weapon proficiencies and weapon fighting styles are updated to reflect the creature's experience level and class."}
{"id": "16688", "revid": "280766", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16688", "title": "Ether Gate", "text": "The Shaman attempts to transport the target through the Ether Gate into the Ethereal Plane.\nGameplay.\nThis spell works like the arcane spell &lt;a href=\"Maze\"&gt;Maze&lt;/a&gt;, except for a few key differences:\n-There's a fixed duration of 5 rounds, instead of a duration based on the enemy's intelligence score (meaning it might have a shorter or longer duration than Maze, depending on said score).\n-The targeted creature is instantaneously cast through the Ether Gate after the spell is cast, as opposed to what happens with Maze, where there's a relatively long animation that needs to finish before the enemy is actually sent away.\n-It's a &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; 7 spell, meaning that, unlike Maze, it won't work against &lt;a href=\"Rakshasa\"&gt;Rakshasa&lt;/a&gt;.\n-It's a spell from the Alteration school, as opposed to Conjuration.\nAnother noteworthy difference is the fact that Shamans will acquire this spell earlier (at 1.5 million XP) than a Sorcerer can acquire Maze (2.25 million XP) and probably much earlier than a Mage, who not only needs the same amount of XP as the Sorcerer, but also needs to find a scroll (with the one in Spellhold being the earliest available).\nMoreover, a Sorcerer must choose between Maze and other (probably better) spells of level 8, whereas Ether Gate will always be available to any Shaman after reaching level 14."}
{"id": "55862", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55862", "title": "Ethereal", "text": "Ethereal is a quick casting spell with no assigned school of magic or secondary type. It is scripted for use by &lt;a href=\"Succubus\"&gt;Succubus&lt;/a&gt; creatures.\nGameplay.\nThe succubus applies this spell, usually through the \"forcecast\" command (not interruptible), typically when heavily wounded.\nThe spell provides normal invisibility that lasts many hours. The invisibility isn't coded as an illusionary protection, so that means some divination spells won't remove it.\nWhen the succubus performs an invisibility breaking action, the succubus will no longer be invisible.\nThe spell also gives two other boons to the creature, each lasting 5 rounds. These are:\nSets &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; to 75%.\nBestows a &lt;a href=\"Regeneration\"&gt;Regeneration&lt;/a&gt; rate of 2 &lt;a href=\"Hit%20point\"&gt;hit points&lt;/a&gt; per second.\nThis spell cannot be dispelled or removed from the succubus.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; revises this spell to an \"Innate\" spell. removing the Wizard type classification."}
{"id": "16720", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16720", "title": "Ethereal Retribution", "text": "Ethereal Retribution summons ghosts to suck life forces off their victims."}
{"id": "11063", "revid": "269341", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11063", "title": "Ettercap", "text": "Ettercaps are hideous creatures that resemble a cross between a gangly ape and a bloated spider.\nGameplay.\nEttercaps attack three times per round. Their primary attack (weapon 1) only does 1d3 damage, but another attack (weapon 2) does 1d8 and forces a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;save vs. poison&lt;/a&gt; to avoid 2 hit points per second from &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt; for 37 seconds unless cured. Ettercaps are immune to &lt;a href=\"Webbed\"&gt;webs&lt;/a&gt;.\nEttercaps have strong saving throws. However as they are below level 6 they are vulnerable to the cleric spell &lt;a href=\"Command\"&gt;Command&lt;/a&gt;.\nSummoned.\nIn \"\" Ettercaps can be summoned by the spell &lt;a href=\"Monster%20Summoning%20III\"&gt;Monster Summoning III&lt;/a&gt;. Summoned versions are virtually identical, having only slightly more hit points (42 instead of 40), but a worse THAC0 (15, not 11). They also do not carry random treasure."}
