{"id": "10237", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10237", "title": "Ettin", "text": "Ettins are lumbering, neanderthal-looking, giant humanoids that possess two heads, but are slow of wit and have very little common sense. They are about half the size of a &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Giant\"&gt;Fire Giant&lt;/a&gt; and have almost the same amount of health (96 HP). They wear no armor and their only weapon is a single club.\nLocations.\nUmar Hills.\nTwo ettins are encountered while protecting the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt; from invasion during the &lt;a href=\"Paladin%20Stronghold%20Duties\"&gt;paladin stronghold quest&lt;/a&gt; and they each drop 100 upon death.\nUnderwater City.\nA single ettin is battled upon reaching the &lt;a href=\"Underwater%20City\"&gt;Underwater City&lt;/a&gt; at the end of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%204\"&gt;Chapter 4&lt;/a&gt;, if the party chooses to accept &lt;a href=\"Saemon%20Havarian\"&gt;Saemon Havarian&lt;/a&gt;s offer of attempting to sail back to &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; from the island of &lt;a href=\"Brynnlaw\"&gt;Brynnlaw&lt;/a&gt; instead of accessing the entrance to the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;. This fellow drops no treasure upon death.\nWild Forest.\nA single ettin is found in the northwest area of the &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Forest\"&gt;Wild Forest&lt;/a&gt;, along with a &lt;a href=\"Gnoll%20Captain\"&gt;Gnoll Captain&lt;/a&gt; and two &lt;a href=\"Gnoll%20Elite\"&gt;Gnoll Elite&lt;/a&gt;s. However, this creature is actually an illusion conjured up by &lt;a href=\"Neera\"&gt;Neera&lt;/a&gt; and her &lt;a href=\"Hidden%20Refuge\"&gt;Hidden Refuge&lt;/a&gt; folks as a method of scaring away enemies that might threaten the Refuge.\nIt will appear to attack the gnolls and then vanish. The gnolls will then turn hostile and attack the party."}
{"id": "41716", "revid": "49746547", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41716", "title": "Ettin Club", "text": "The Ettin Club is a unique &lt;a href=\"Club%20%2B1\"&gt;Club +1&lt;/a&gt; introduced in which can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Ettin%20Ghost%20Cave\"&gt;Ettin Ghost Cave&lt;/a&gt; after speaking to the &lt;a href=\"Ettin%20Ghost\"&gt;Ettin Ghost&lt;/a&gt; and agreeing to find its lost club. It can be found in the ettin's skeleton. As a result of its absurd size, it uses two 6-sided dice for damage instead of one, but has an extremely high Strength requirement, severe THAC0 penalty, glacial speed factor, and heavy weight, making its raw power difficult to take advantage of.\nThe Ettin Club will be lost permanently if returned to the Ettin Ghost, so if one wishes to keep it they must kill or avoid them.\nDescription.\nThis club, fashioned out of a single giant legbone, is as unwieldy as it is heavy. In a giant's hands it would be a formidable weapon."}
