{"id": "5280", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5280", "title": "Eye of Tyr", "text": "Eye of Tyr is a pommel gem that can be used to upgrade a weapon of virtue. As the gem is unique, it can be used by &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt; to upgrade either &lt;a href=\"Carsomyr\"&gt;Carsomyr&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Purifier\"&gt;Purifier&lt;/a&gt;. This item appears in and . When taking this gem to Cespenar, it's important to remember that if you have both swords in your inventory, he will upgrade The Purifier. Therefore, if you wish to upgrade Carsomyr, you will need to remove The Purifier from your inventory before speaking to him.\nLocation.\nThis item is found in &lt;a href=\"Sendai%27s%20Enclave\"&gt;Sendai's Enclave&lt;/a&gt; in the room of the lich."}
{"id": "47363", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47363", "title": "Eyes of the Beholder", "text": "The Eyes of the Beholder is a in . It provides protection against critical hits and a -1 bonus to &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;armor class&lt;/a&gt;. It also allows the wearer to use &lt;a href=\"Domination\"&gt;Domination&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Held\"&gt;Paralyze&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Fear\"&gt;Fear&lt;/a&gt; three times per day each. It's also noteworthy that all three abilities are considered Enchantments and, therefore, carry a save penalty when cast by an Enchanter dualed into another class that allows them to wear this."}
{"id": "30473", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30473", "title": "Eyestalk of an Elder Orb", "text": "The Eyestalk of an Elder Orb is an item demanded for a macabre ritual that will be performed by &lt;a href=\"Matron%20Mother%20Ardulace%20Despana\"&gt;Matron Mother Ardulace Despana&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Lolth\"&gt;Temple of Lolth&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nThe Eyestalk of an Elder Orb is from of one the most powerful subspecies of the &lt;a href=\"beholder\"&gt;beholder&lt;/a&gt; race, freshly hewn from its former owner's scalp. It is taken from the corpse of a specific &lt;a href=\"Elder%20Orb\"&gt;Elder Orb&lt;/a&gt; located in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt; and taking the &lt;a href=\"Beholder%20Cave%20in%20Underdark\"&gt;Southern Tunnels&lt;/a&gt;. Somewhere in the caverns is this creature, lurking and well protected.\nIt is one of three items that 'Veldrin' can choose to present to &lt;a href=\"Matron%20Mother%20Ardulace%20Despana\"&gt;Matron Mother Ardulace Despana&lt;/a&gt; as a component in a demon-summoning ritual that is part of the main Ust Natha storyline quest. \nIts alternatives are the &lt;a href=\"Elder%20Brain%20Blood\"&gt;Elder Brain Blood&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Kuo-toa%27s%20Blood\"&gt;Kuo-toa's Blood&lt;/a&gt;. You are free to obtain one, two, or all three items if desired.\nOnce the item is presented to the Matron Mother, it will be removed from the player's inventory."}
{"id": "51282", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51282", "title": "FAMMY.ITM", "text": "FAMMY.ITM is an undroppable ring equipped to certain &lt;a href=\"Find%20Familiar\"&gt;Familiar&lt;/a&gt; creatures. \nEffects.\nThe Ring provides two abilities unique to familiars. The first is a &lt;a href=\"Wizard%20Eye\"&gt;Wizard Eye&lt;/a&gt; effect so that the creature can explore, plus clear the fog of war like a party member. The second allows the transition if the familiar into and out of the PC's pack inventory, which is handled through speaking to the familiar and directing the familiar to get into the pack (adds to inventory), and vice versa to get it out onto the area map. \nThe item has no other powers or abilities."}
{"id": "51304", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51304", "title": "FIGRING1.ITM", "text": "FIGRING.ITM is an undroppable item placed in one of the ring slots of &lt;a href=\"Joolon\"&gt;Joolon&lt;/a&gt; the Golden Lion.\nThe item serves as a means to provide the creature with a normal &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Haste effect&lt;/a&gt; and a \"glow pulse\" animation effect.\nThe item has no other powers or abilities."}
{"id": "50235", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50235", "title": "FIREELEM.ITM", "text": "FIREELEM.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by various &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Elemental\"&gt;Fire Elemental&lt;/a&gt; creatures.\nIt is considered a magical and +4 enchanted item and deals 3d8 damage (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus), and 1d6 fire damage, with a range of one foot, and speed factor of 0.\nIt has no other effects."}
{"id": "51995", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51995", "title": "FIRERING.ITM", "text": "FIRERING.ITM is an undroppable Ring of Invisibility equipped to the &lt;a href=\"Final%20mask%20guardian\"&gt;Final mask guardian&lt;/a&gt; as part of &lt;a href=\"Samia%27s%20Proposal\"&gt;Samia's Proposal&lt;/a&gt; which takes place in &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Maze\"&gt;Firkraag's Maze&lt;/a&gt;.\nIts similar, but not identical to the &lt;a href=\"MAGE01.ITM\"&gt;MAGE01.ITM&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffects.\nIts single effect is &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href=\"Opcode\"&gt;Opcode&lt;/a&gt; 20), on the wearer, of type \"Normal\" (i.e., not &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Invisibility\"&gt;Improved Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;). It can be removed by certain divination attack spells such as &lt;a href=\"Invisibility%20Purge\"&gt;Invisibility Purge&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Detect%20Invisibility\"&gt;Detect Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"True%20Sight\"&gt;True Sight&lt;/a&gt;. The actual result of a creature wearing this ring will provide the creature with invisibility at the start of any potential conflict, without having to cast a spell or otherwise initiate some kind of ability to attain invisibility. \nWhile this item is worn, it allows the wearer to force cast &lt;a href=\"Sunfire\"&gt;Sunfire&lt;/a&gt;, without breaking invisibility.\nThis item is removed from the creature when a specific action occurs, which exposes the being and makes it visible."}
{"id": "56416", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56416", "title": "FSSPIR.ITM", "text": "FSSPIR.ITM is an undroppable item equipped by a few creatures that are meant to be invulnerable to damage, spells, death and similar events/actions. \nThis item is similar to the &lt;a href=\"INVULNER.ITM\"&gt;INVULNER.ITM&lt;/a&gt; in function and complement each other.\nThis item provides immunities to spells of many types, damage types, status effects, and also applies always on \"cures\" to some status effects as well. \nThe wiki isn't listing these as it has no value to the reader or player to dive into the minutiae.\nIn conclusion, this item, along with others, is meant to safeguard the creature from overt and accidental destruction so that the game plot can be presented without glitching the player's game."}
{"id": "49144", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49144", "title": "Faafirah", "text": "Faafirah is a &lt;a href=\"djinni\"&gt;djinni&lt;/a&gt; inside the &lt;a href=\"Dao%20Djinni%20Tent\"&gt;Dao Djinni Tent&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Tradmeet&lt;/a&gt;. He stands guard for &lt;a href=\"Khan%20Zahraa\"&gt;Khan Zahraa&lt;/a&gt;, a Dao noble djinni. \nGameplay.\nAttempting to talk to Faafirah results only in a few responses.\"Heeeee... I do not speak with the lesser mortal creatures, such as yourself. I be not here by choice, indeed.\"\"Begone from me, mortal, lest you serve the Khan... speak to he, if you dare.\"\"Heeee... you will find our little rakshasi, will you? More likely you will die, mortal! Ihtafeer is a ruhk, a knight, and far too much for you!\"\"We be here only as a service to our summoner, mortal! Find this rakshasi quickly, bring her head... I wish to begone!\"\nIf this Djinn is made hostile it will begin combat with a \"force cast\" uninterruptible &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Haste\"&gt;Improved Haste&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, then attempt a &lt;a href=\"Flesh%20to%20Stone\"&gt;Flesh to Stone&lt;/a&gt;. Will engage in melee after that, and possibly try a &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; spell cast as well."}
{"id": "7967", "revid": "4896558", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7967", "title": "Faber", "text": "Faber is one of many slaves found in the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines\"&gt;Cloakwood Mines&lt;/a&gt; during \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". He plays the part of the proverbial 'rat', serving as the inside man loyal to the present authority.\nUpon being discovered, he will hail &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; thinking them to be the guards, claiming a fellow slave - &lt;a href=\"Andarsson\"&gt;Andarsson&lt;/a&gt; - was speaking ill of someone apparently noteworthy - &lt;a href=\"Davaeorn\"&gt;Davaeorn&lt;/a&gt;. Despite immediately running off to warn the guards, no guards will be alerted by Faber, and he is one of the few slaves that can be killed without penalty to one's &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt;."}
